[{"Name":"Iman Sh","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWY_It5dFbhJ3ahD3y8wnnvsyYECBdVwU0ipYiueTLf-0IgvGbE=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"The new Popeyes restaurant in the UBC area is finally open! I've been waiting for almost five months since I first saw their signs, and it officially opened about a week ago. It's located inside the Lelem Village, which is great because there's a nice outdoor space where you can sit and enjoy the summer. There are also outdoor games available there.

The staff are nice and kind‚ÄîI asked for additional sauce, and they happily gave it to me, so I'm giving them a 10/10 üòõ. The quality of the food is the same as at all other Popeyes locations: it's nice and tasty, perfect if you enjoy fast food. Everything is orderly and clean, and you can order ahead using the app and pick it up when you get there.

I definitely recommend their hot wings and butterfly shrimp; both were really nice and tasty. Try all the different sauces‚Äîpersonally, I prefer the buttermilk ranch, but I also like the Cajun cocktail sauce, which is pretty unique to me.

I'll definitely try more and update my review if anything changes. üç§ üçó üçü

[Update, 2024, September]
It's been a while since I posted another review, but everything is still just as good. They‚Äôre now available on their website, and you can order ahead. The rewards in the app could be improved‚Äîthey don‚Äôt quite match up to others, but still better than nothing. This time, I ordered the classic chicken burger along with fried onions and mashed potatoes. The onions are on another level‚ÄîI really love them. The mashed potatoes are a bit spicy but still tasty. As for the burger, I personally prefer it with a bit of ranch, but honestly, with or without, it's still delicious. Be careful, the individual spicy chicken is spicier than I thought it would be, Can‚Äôt decide if I like the Spaghetti or Palabok Fiesta better - the Palabok reminds me of my Lola‚Äôs dish that I love. Looking forward again","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNIVqpOL0C_RWpaBe79XI7v8ggpVBwis1GBGebC&fid=0x0:0x36ece58a6332843"],"When":"2024-12-22"},{"Name":"Geraldine Sangalang","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUcAsqfNVs6uRfmsJ5FtsU66GdsPGBE4zo_tn8DnG79e7VADqel9Q=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"The fried chicken at this location surpassed my expectations. This was my first taste of Jolibee in Canada. It was fresh, seasoned well, crispy on the outside and juicy on the inside. It was the best fried chicken I've had in a long time.

We ordered a 6-piece bucket with regular and spicy chicken. I appreciated the labels added to the hot chicken, and the parchment paper used to separate the hot and regular fried chicken in the container.

The gravy was also seasoned well. Not too salty at all.

We also tried the peach and mango pie. Wonderfully sweet, hot and satisfying. They were a perfect end to lunch.

There isn't much seating, but tables do open up. It helps for one person to order food while another keeps an eye out for tables to become available.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPLHURZ0ck25KVrg_PlaYZ8HS10Cb-NXnW5pmZh&fid=0x0:0x36ece58a6332843"],"When":"2024-10-15"},{"Name":"Leo Bangco","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWYfCCpirtE-rfmwC1-LZcBx4fcjtnHR0xsdXbkqh-pyjTVUIMB=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Jollibee food has always been my comfort food since when I was young, and this place was able to replicate that nostalgia feel, food-wise! Please bring back original spoons or use recyclable plastic spoons (they are little bit more soft but still possible to use with food).

Wooden spoons are still horrible.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPjKVGHIE3vtWOOCdMe1GRjKF_mJNN06oDaaPkW&fid=0x0:0xe193d027abf6599a"],"When":"2024-6-6"},{"Name":"Jerry Plante","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVA-tGJD9Pc1BTrWk6OMOR05mgjS7zRKSy1Y02cNTLfyuaBL-w=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"We had each ordered a different burger
And will not make that mistake again of ordering anything on a bun!

Miss the old days when Dairy Queen simply stuck with great basic Dairy Queen Brazier burgers !

We had each ordered a different burger with fries and onion rings and a soft drink
Even with my six dollars off in app special coupon our order still was over $30!

We‚Äôll remember to stick with other places like Wendy‚Äôs for burgers next time and leave my ice cream cravings to DQ!

The staff were super friendly and pretty quick helping me place my order for us, but they were swamped as they were understaff.
It was a nice day, but not a hot one!
Our order had came up and was sitting in the pass through window for at least 5<8 minutes. The two staff ran crazily back-and-forth, preparing and serving ice cream cones, etc.. which were mostly simple orders for those who had come in for an after dinner treat
While we simply waited to have our dinner which had been delayed and is why we chose to come to thinking we get better service.

Our burgers appear to have been hastily thrown together
Drowning in an over abundance of chopped green iceberg, lettuce, and ranch sauce on the other burger.

Our orders sat on the side while they continue trying to catch up with the sudden onslaught of after dinner customers looking for a quick sweet treat.

I still finished my meal by purchasing a large pumpkin pie blizzard, which I look forward to every year !
This year has been extra special as it is one of my first times out eating in public since I have been in chemotherapy for over five months!

I can partially forgive the overpriced burgers as we do not feel like we got value for what we eight especially given, seen the much smaller various ice cream orders customers were placing and receiving while our food continue to sit in the takeout window.

The 2 DQ staff personnel were super friendly as I had said ‚Ä¶
I just don‚Äôt feel as if our whole meal deal was as valued as the dipped ice cream üç¶ cones or a sundae!  Although temperature wise, I have my doubts that there was not much temperature variance between what we ate and those sweet treats.

We would have left the food and simply asked for a refund, except that we had both been very hungry due to our delayed dinner start time because we had been shopping üõí at a busy place.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Kelly Dame","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVdmskNmGZiKdnAju8r_NhxeNcbwmaYFJcZ1fSl-C4TXt9hptg=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"My husband and I love the Dairy Queen and have recently started going to this location. The portions are quite generous, and even the mini bowl is enough to make sure you‚Äôre not hungry.

The salmon is my go-to pick, the shoyu is a must hahaha.

There is not much seating near the place itself, so definitely just sit on some bench if it‚Äôs not raining.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOUL3NqhZUds1uCJFHjqiEfzEWo0vnCvKMwPjhe&fid=0x0:0x408ff42ba8c24b07"],"When":"2024-10-20"},{"Name":"Nicole Villalon","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVvX-NXEAvIz9hfeDmCLJbpqDwAUM7ozgrgH4vZTSomKf59ULGv=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"STEVE‚ÄôS POKE DOES IT AGAIN!!!
I‚Äôve eaten here 4 times so far and every single time the service has been phenomenal. Today‚Äôs experience, however, absolutely takes the cake.

I ordered a mini BYOB with one scoop of poke online, coming up to ~$15 after tax and tips. The people at checkout were very attentive and made sure to check in and let me know my order was being prepared, and would be ready in a couple minutes. And then, the girl preparing my poke misread my order‚Ä¶ and accidentally made me a large instead of a mini BYOB!!! She apologized multiple times, but how could I complain? More poke! And when I let it slip my birthday had been a week ago, the staff offered to throw in an iced tea, free of charge!

The poke was delicious, the service was stellar, and staff‚Äôs kindness absolutely made my day. I‚Äôll be happy to visit Steve‚Äôs Poke again very soon!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOmSF-4CMT-TmWd3-H-5XYvs2169hWwMLVwRpNj&fid=0x0:0x408ff42ba8c24b07"],"When":"2024-11-22"},{"Name":"Tresa Horney","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVlCxWd5ESmqb9bOtTVn1nxYHpHQadHnSQ3MsNKRjtwrjVvD0jPDQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Easy to order, friendly service, and a great meal. Pleased to have a vegetarian option. I‚Äôll return.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPy2Vjy3vWoV_UVTxuZk8COaNosX0DfibJOIhOD&fid=0x0:0x408ff42ba8c24b07"],"When":"2024-11-12"},{"Name":"Ben K","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIkChymkBEqoHC-DSLY-BlpEm3X8tgGaeAvEy7G17xjM-zfjw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"$20 for this poke bowl, comes with 4 different choices of fish/poke, and any number of free ‚Äútoppings‚Äù. The rice is ‚Äúregular‚Äù white rice, not really flavored with mirin or anything. The fish come with sauce, but I should have asked for extra sauce on it because it had either dried up a bit or soaked into the rice. Considering the other choices around UBC, this is probably pretty good value for money.

I ordered takeout, but they have a few seats inside and outside if you prefer. The street currently has a bunch of (summer) construction, though.

[Update July, 2024]
I ordered the burger, which had two patties, and oh boy, it was really tasty. Maybe I was super hungry, but I enjoyed it so much. The combination of sauces I selected and the pickles was so tasty. This is still my favorite beef burger among the chain restaurants so far. üçî üçü

The portion was good enough. I'm still trying to understand their fries, but they aren't in my top 5 list.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMsW1-vSLY5SlXFFVB8adPE4vTC1E_NC6ky7xU-&fid=0x0:0xb71d37c77cc9682e"],"When":"2024-3-19"},{"Name":"Danbe Seo","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjW1EMjN2eOd4WZ0pelt9_7zn4kXcAJdRE16SwPyaZlAQO4JUHUo=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"I really enjoy the food here, especially the fries cooked in peanut oil‚Äîthey‚Äôre absolutely delicious!

However, one concern I have is that the staff preparing the food often talk to each other without wearing masks. It makes me worry that saliva could get into the food.

Other than that, everything is fine, and I hope this issue can be addressed for an even better experience.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Samuel Barbosa de Mello","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX0peg6-WBhE0EbhzmdEe49pyBGvXkFFn6reIlxa2416ZpRVQKplg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"While Five Guys has gained popularity, I found the experience to be somewhat underwhelming. The burgers, while generously portioned, lacked the juicy flavor I anticipated. The burgers, unfortunately, were often soggy and lacked the juicy flavor I anticipated. For a truly satisfying burger experience, I recommend exploring other local options.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMB-syXMIdVcaD5h_fW4USPDLynss1UWPeesMcP&fid=0x0:0xb71d37c77cc9682e"],"When":"2024-11-20"},{"Name":"Andrew Chan","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJNZ_pvkQlgvJLQf8OH0R8SwU4mnsFF1lvTcdlboJ-4DK-Pr7bb=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Five Guys restaurant is exceptional. The hamburger is truly amazing. The quality of the food is top-notch, with fresh ingredients and perfectly cooked patties. The service is incredibly friendly, making the dining experience even more enjoyable. I will definitely be returning to Five Guys again in the future.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPvMqvEmDV8sSSW1QOkAOtU_rfiMnDCYBXu0ooL&fid=0x0:0xb71d37c77cc9682e"],"When":"2024-2-3"},{"Name":"Hannah Hsiao","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocI5undqv6k1prGO5bK7GLTSz1rgSfSAhZOcrA8P3TjSA6EXYA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"They really know how to make a great hamburger. I ordered bacon cheeseburger, which is so delicious. You can select the topping you like. Highly recommended. The size is quite large so it‚Äôs quite enough for lady without french fries.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipP-GBWNSihV9svY-ddC6siRL7yOab7VrXEF13vE&fid=0x0:0xb71d37c77cc9682e"],"When":"2024-3-30"},{"Name":"John S","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWXqytpKEY7-f7JKKymx1Tg8fiqmA_aam7d7ntMC60_o7ieUTQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Five Guys is a burger paradise in the heart of Vancouver. What sets this joint apart is the fantastic ability to customize your burger just the way you like it. The sheer range of toppings and sauces available ensures that every burger is a unique and personalized experience. The staff's friendly and accommodating nature makes the customization process a breeze.

The burgers themselves are absolute showstoppers. Juicy, flavorful, and made to perfection, these burgers are a testament to the quality of ingredients used. The melt-in-your-mouth experience is unmatched, and it's evident that a lot of care goes into preparing each burger.

Now, let's talk about the fries - they're more than just a side dish, they're an experience on their own. Crispy on the outside and perfectly tender on the inside, these fries are simply addictive. The fact that they're hand-cut and made fresh right there adds an extra level of deliciousness.

The ambiance is lively and inviting, adding to the overall enjoyment of the meal. Whether you're a solo diner or with a group of friends, the welcoming atmosphere makes every visit enjoyable.

For a truly customizable and mouthwatering burger experience paired with some of the best fries around, Five Guys in Vancouver is the place to be. The quality, flavor, and the ability to make your burger your own truly sets it apart. A must-visit for burger enthusiasts.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMUE7GkyPio3PXGv0bLhCU_LLmCdFlr_kiCIehM&fid=0x0:0xb71d37c77cc9682e"],"When":"2023-11-12"}]

user_reviews: [{"Name":"katelynn c","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVoqcwb_gcSeJsQp6Fk0xxFfLaz6Ca58KOlakGeP011yHdUWdF9=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"the portions were huge for the price, like even the medium and small were pretty big and loaded with fries and toppings. it was basically a mountain of fries, gravy, and meat, so pretty much heaven. i loved how you could customize your toppings, and there was also a bunch of other sauces and other add-ons on the side that you could add to shake it up a little bit. no complaints, but i wouldn‚Äôt say it‚Äôs the best poutine i‚Äôve ever had. the meat was really good and paired well with the gravy and fries though !","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile\u0026image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMCDniSkdJVw4GvPS9JXl5XvgCvCy4PQsSNdKfd\u0026fid=0x0:0x349d349c0326e5f2"],"When":"2024-12-25"},{"Name":"Cody Li","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLa2VUtv7DC_i8Wnp5Uag1FXkYZtN3PqArBTVfGIi_c0ZmX_uI=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"If you‚Äôve got a gluten intolerance dietary restriction or lactose intolerance where dairy makes you poot nonstop, this is the place to be for poutine! The gluten free gravy and vegan cheese didn‚Äôt taste off at all and blended in well with the flavors. Crispy fries, well salted gravy, soft \u0026 tender smoked meats, overall very yummy!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile\u0026image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMhZVBYbBETphvSUeJBPU-LWY5H-vacrYE-d_Jr\u0026fid=0x0:0x349d349c0326e5f2"],"When":"2024-9-23"},{"Name":"Reuben James","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVGIYVAAO3rRMgU2q-a5Xu4Z-78qZw-JIrzOfyxzv_YXsiC35M=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Legendary Stuff - easily the best french fries I've ever eaten. They make it fresh and it has just the perfect amount of crisp. The wasabi garlic dip (only for $1 as of Nov 2024) was also insane. Can't believe I've been in Vancouver this long and haven't been here before. I'm definitely gonna be a regular from now!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile\u0026image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMJDqBwxtk6oZWJdh_21xnVI-vgywBXXpuwRxY\u0026fid=0x0:0x349d349c0326e5f2"],"When":"2024-11-30"},{"Name":"Alexandra Gaevsky","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVnjItyjfR1qVEZnY6caUOLCi6uNaCD4VjAop9J7DwgHSC2Qmwo=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"The fries were crispy and delicious, and the toppings were full of flavor. I ordered the poutine fries topped with chili, which was fantastic. The shop is small with minimal seating, but it's a great spot for a quick bite!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile\u0026image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPhPuRZYg5B_ojRLzvDNgjNFrGPUv_JGxvlf0EV\u0026fid=0x0:0x349d349c0326e5f2"],"When":"2024-8-12"},{"Name":"Melanie Tam","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXOnCXlUyDGCRthUKehak0_GUp_az2pTQqceWOyRQ-aAN0D6lJP=s120-c-rp-mo-ba7-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Dropped in on a Wednesday at around 1 PM for a quick snack. We had the medium poutine with garlic dip to go, but we asked for the gravy on the side, which was the best move. I've realized that I don't really like poutine because the gravy makes the fries all soggy. But when I have the gravy on the side as a dipping sauce, it is amazing. The fries stayed crispy, even though it was for takeout. The cheese curds were slightly melted, but that's the price you pay for not eating it fresh. 10/10 would do this again.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile\u0026image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOjsvhfY_SuQ_iUbesoztoqiWVb3U9BnCx-191E\u0026fid=0x0:0x349d349c0326e5f2"],"When":"2024-8-13"},{"Name":"D Milburn","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKYTJuyYJNW23XEIhyxDTO5WvOME5ipvEjz0dpndmARnqjZMtDf=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Have a craving for poutine? Because I was. After tonight, I'm not sure how I feel about poutine or fries anywhere else in Canada. The menu looked basic but Fritz European Fry House blew my taste buds away. From start to finish, it was packed full of gravy, bacon bits, melted, oozing cheese curds, with the most exceptional crispy fried fries I've ever tried in my life. Yummy !","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile\u0026image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNbxAxHLJydgSlt-ALmrKUSirrhOkz3iuGb3T9r\u0026fid=0x0:0x349d349c0326e5f2"],"When":"2024-8-4"},{"Name":"Sharon T","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLlvHI_kQcMxugba1226yW-8c1FCiqghQa5XvvsfV5MlbgvIw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"This place serves a killer poutine. Comes with a variety of different toppings and sizes as well. We tried their smoke meat poutine. The poutine has a very good sauce but the sauce was not too much. The fries as a result to that remains crispy. Really good place for poutine.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile\u0026image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOKaHEpgYJ_i4gx4nGAWCYChr8F9Urnn6l8-6Rg\u0026fid=0x0:0x349d349c0326e5f2"],"When":"2024-8-4"},{"Name":"C B","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWbzTQhFKVcqZjQK1pnRxiEVBBOfrvfJM3weCHu6u4IMHg3IQ0Kxg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Great place to grab a traditional poutine and go about your day I think the small is a decent size portion unless you‚Äôre really hungry but for a quick eat it‚Äôs awesome and tastes good. user_reviews:
[{"Name":"Ben K","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIkChymkBEqoHC-DSLY-BlpEm3X8tgGaeAvEy7G17xjM-zfjw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Bottom line: it‚Äôs a great pizza for an affordable price (they often have promotions) on campus.

I got the ‚Äúgrab n go‚Äù: any small pizza and a pop for $10.99+tax. The Deluxe pizza was decent: crust was crispy, toppings filled the pizza, beautifully melted/charred in their XLT speed oven. And around the outer edge of the pizza is a heavy sprinkling of sesame seeds, which lends a texture like crunchy pizza dough. Kind of nice.

The online ordering platform tells you the order will take minimum 20 minutes, which was spot-on for my order. They also sell pizza by the slice for $2.38+tax in-store.

Best thing: they give you your takeout pizza in a cardboard box, so there‚Äôs no $0.25 bag fee!

The restaurant itself has probably 10 small tables‚Äîsome inside, some outside‚Äîfor eating there.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNDOuHiDIZTmdoXWax2rwLSqlNZvYhweoWLQ0nu&fid=0x0:0x860b3a2c6558c7be"],"When":"2024-8-2"},{"Name":"Iman Sh","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWY_It5dFbhJ3ahD3y8wnnvsyYECBdVwU0ipYiueTLf-0IgvGbE=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Uncle Fatih's Pizza is one of the best pizza experiences I've had in Vancouver. When comparing price and taste, it's honestly way better than other chain pizza places. We ordered a medium Meat Lovers and a medium Eggplant Artichoke, and enjoyed both of them. The chipotle dip was a nice addition, though it's not very spicy. The pizza itself is juicy and full of flavors.

If you were to compare it to an authentic Italian restaurant in Downtown, I can't say for sure how it would hold up‚ÄîI haven't tried that yet. But this place serves great pizzas with good quality. As long as the quality stays consistent, it will always be one of my favorite pizza places.

[Update, July 1, 2024]
We ordered an extra-large half-and-half pizza. One half was Sweet & Spicy Lovers, and the other was Eggplant Artichoke. We enjoyed both. The Sweet & Spicy Lovers pizza has pineapple slices, so if you enjoy the sweetness of pineapple on your pizza, it could be really nice. The spiciness comes from banana peppers, which are quite intense‚ÄîI‚Äôd rate the spicy level 9/10 and usually avoid the banana peppers with the last pieces. The meat on the pizza was very nice, though.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipP3LNwcz4Mhb2_rAOeKq6HQ2yu9c_abTPsvF_gY&fid=0x0:0x860b3a2c6558c7be"],"When":"2024-6-27"},{"Name":"Bruno Rodrigues","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXhILuyIb0LIP6MudwbcSE2BAlE-f9U9SKRT2p9lsRwJ4hM0FgDLg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Awesome bang for the buck ‚Äì 20th anniversary deal was any slice for $2.38 plus taxes. Slice was of a regular size and adequately filled. Ingredientes were good quality and the cheese was pretty tasty. Service was friendly, but I guess overwhelmed because there were only two people working at the whole restaurant. Maybe this setup will only last during the summer vacations, but there were some people waiting to make their order on the line even then.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNr_x3LSgypONBL59pcXxllJnkv_odePZ2Iyp46&fid=0x0:0x860b3a2c6558c7be"],"When":"2024-8-25"},{"Name":"Gurleen Mann","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLiPUG0uS2mNXBduiVsY6PVMjHnfxQ7NkDQyzxiXX7WnB_qcg=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I‚Äôm really glad I stopped here with my family for lunch. The staff were helpful and answered all my questions. We ordered a small garlic chicken pizza, small spicy chicken pizza and veggie lovers (gluten free small pizza). The entire order was made quickly and tasted very good with fresh ingredients and a soft dough. They also had some dipping sauces on the side. Would have been awesome if they had small containers to place them in, but that wasn‚Äôt a deal breaker. All in all one of the best pizza places I‚Äôve had in a very long time!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Jessy James","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUYtH31UTkbDUolpuvM8YhvZp6aRqCRrozjZhpKhJHwBksolrRrhQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Went in as they were closing (which nobody likes I know! üôà) but we had no where else that was opened so we gave it a shot!

The last 8-10 slices all assorted and they charged full price for everything. Almost $36 after tip for end of the night pizza was a little crazy IMO. However they did their best to give us a deal anyways, so we left a tip as much as we could.

The pizza was tasty, I would personally recommend the ham and pineapple! The others were great too but not as traditional in taste as they were a little more complicated in ingredients. Not a bad thing, I just like my pizza simple ü•∞

Otherwise felt the food was very tasty and would return if they had better prices, maybe some Italian style/thinner/cheaper made slices could help things as a recommendation? I love my Italian traditional pizza style myself, but I know this place is more westernized and that's also okay.

Otherwise a good experience, just think end of the night slices are typically sold at a reduced rate. They did give us 8 slices and the 9th free, but I feel it could have been half off. Maybe I'm picky, idk üòÜ.

Overall good stuff! üçï Thanks!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"YVR Duke","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVbrjJ5U6gKw7Gn1zE_GlxhUndims9WHlh7sVaHLXVrjOFlYd_B=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I missed the old Pi[e]r¬≤ Pizza.
This is the closest we can get on campus.  Freshslice is ok but it just lacks a character.

Recommended for pizza lovers.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOU3FmBdtQ7LMg_cBIVovU8hZILP6gYcvSoICF2&fid=0x0:0x860b3a2c6558c7be"],"When":"2024-7-3"},{"Name":"Zay R","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIrcv0nbceihjzzaPr2LIIin5v_Tj9YhzMv8cvDTNxNVU0GSA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"I always order from them via Ubereats. Sometimes they do have good offers ‚Äòbuy 1 get 1 free‚Äô on selected pizzas which is definitely better and cheaper, their prices are a bit pricey without the offer.
As for their crusts, they were always well cooked, soft and very tasty. I like their thin crust more.
Their pizzas are freshly made. I tried couple of veggie pizzas, they were all delicious. However, their bbq sauce is not the best (barely taste it)
This time I got pesto chicken pizza and it was good.My favorite is Garlic Lover Pizza!
Also I appreciate the fact they offer Halal chicken :)
Overall very good Pizza place","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNR6RA-QEUZg9mR9rrhkIy-hHpvwt5R5I40hL40&fid=0x0:0x860b3a2c6558c7be"],"When":"2021-3-18"},{"Name":"Marcus Xiong","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWNKHkNu0r9L6u_s13vBOcHGIOl_tisn1xjH9tQbojiCd_NkDw-YQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"This is a quick place to grab a meal, and the food isn't low quality either. The pizza is freshly made and rebaked when someone orders them. The food is brought up quickly. I like the unique sesame seeds on the crust, and adds extra flavor to the pizza. While the chicken meat itself was plentiful and tasty, I found the batter on the outside of the chicken pieces to be somewhat disappointing. It wasn't as crispy as I had hoped, and the texture was a bit soft and greasy. Overall, the chicken was still enjoyable, but I think there is room for improvement in the batter department. Nevertheless, I would still recommend giving Church's Chicken a try if you're in the mood for some tasty fried chicken.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMmeUV1Z60YCSP2z_86B0lsaZcDd3YaqH2v7ZRy&fid=0x0:0xbf07ad645d64bd83"],"When":"2023-3-28"},{"Name":"Galen Linnett","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXNqh6OaD5JO605dhFZ_swUxiWJTWNOmPRydYKWwfPde2gyYndblQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"They need to sell Hot sauce but the service is always great, the hours of operation are helpful. The staff at churches have always been a 10 out of 10 throughout the years.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Camilla Ketib","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX_Nz8WLL8V2o6JSb9uHxa3-2PkgVLnDpGrqIMZV9jTf3LPncAP=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I have a lot to say. However, very upsetting that I can‚Äôt order that. You‚Äôd basically have all my money because eating wings is really good for you actually.
Also, unfortunately today I ordered from there on uber eats and the chicken was not that great. It was dry and chewy and cold. I ordered spicy and it was not spicy at all. When I tried to get help from uber eats no one helped me. Mistakes happen I get it. But sad :( I will be back tho, so step up your game. I don‚Äôt want any free stuff from you, please stop. I love you. Okay maybe a free 20 wings combo with 2 diet cokes and an apple pie.
Freeüáµüá∏üá±üáßüáµüá∏üá±üáß","Images":null,"When":""}]

[{"Name":"Matt E","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUZQfEG_xmBLRy05xS6KbedGsdkDNhef508QuEhW06OHHHM7HPG=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"waiting time was extremely high while it was 10:00 PM and they had nothing to do, but they didn't make my order till 20 minutes the curb in the shift she was leaving so tell her shift finished. She was here for more than 15 minutes and did nothing. There was no other person in the restaurant so I was the only person here waiting for them.
The guy came to the front after 15 minutes he even didn't know I was there because she didn't tell him to make my tacos he did it fast but it took 20 minutes me to go out","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNJ6wntZyF7Cy_uuX2Mg1xtutQn7Wz65UR8ngOg&fid=0x0:0x381f184f3684b65d"],"When":"2024-12-11"},{"Name":"Linda Shirley","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVG59r3kWP38hcNX6eUD6hVVftxrVTzBaaezks4qLPP4s4Up4Ad8w=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"We flew all day and got to our air bnb and we‚Äôre hungry.  Ordered a burrito and nachos.  The delivery driver waited for 45 minutes before he left.  Our food showed up cold soggy and almost looked half eaten.   Soooooooo grossss! Called management back and had no option to get a decent meal. Can‚Äôt believe neither the driver or the manager would rectify this garbage food.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipN5A_ws8gkMTV7MLPPq5bv35k6XSawjBKIM6ZZN&fid=0x0:0x381f184f3684b65d"],"When":"2023-10-20"},{"Name":"Lorcan Whelan","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJmCFiOpRz8ZcazN1A45qaXPfk58Ro8exEBvmkl-Bet-ZuJNg=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"This was the worst burrito I have ever had. It was incredibly bland while also being both dry and soggy at the same time???

We also had a burrito bowl and I can't understand why it was so small and after putting 4 different sauces as well as 2 salsas it was also tasteless and bland.

I would recommend going literally anywhere else.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Gavriel Strauss: Path of Tikk√ºn","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUGiy0XrVugMmovI4l5jMmLE_tMjMEsRP9wKu73v7M7yOTHJQdzVQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"I haven't eaten taco bell since i was a kid, but i would imagine it was of similar quality. I was in a pinch and trying to get my 8-year-old daughter a quick lunch. We ordered a cheese quesadilla with refried beans. What was amazing about it was that it was less than $3, which you can't really find anything like that for that cheap (except probably Taco Bell) anywhere in Toronto!

The problem was the refried beans were spicy and so my kid didn't eat it anyway. It was also difficult to understand the cashier and the place was small and uninviting.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Dana Sullivan","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWQIw-0oOUNgoyniYugTscGkgpKJS8tpx4V0tAajn3ZGkNIfqEk=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"It‚Äôs a build-your-own Tex-Mex joint, Chipotle-style. What distinguishes this one is the variety of protein choices and different sauces/dressings. Some good vegan options. In my picture you‚Äôll see that they added the lettuce last, which wasn‚Äôt the prettiest way to do it, but my bowl tasted better than it looked. The marinated tofu was good. Quality of the other ingredients was okay - not pristinely fresh, not too far past peak either - comparable with Chipotle. Prices are pretty decent for the size - about $12 for the bowl. The eating space in the restaurant was clean. Nothing to remark on about the service, which is fine.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMVyv5hvUp7z4oZOe2wCACz0p2zAPr0WOgfky6b&fid=0x0:0x381f184f3684b65d"],"When":"2023-5-11"},{"Name":"Surinder Pal Singh","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjU2EEncYWv5fnFvmDu4E5o_tq-_lckIfwtd5bASKGsLianAXQ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"The food was so delicious. The staff helped to choose best from the list. Specially i have a word with jashan the way of talking was so gentle
5 out of 5","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMlJJna7J27b_2IJJ46HZWaQ4xJIQPoGZIuPXM&fid=0x0:0x381f184f3684b65d"],"When":"2023-9-28"},{"Name":"Jack Donovan","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKmLezxgkZcIaEazPMOse6RXNapXDIfo8eY1HlcK1dyJ6b6Rw=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Without question the worst burrito I have ever eaten. I have never left a review for any food in my life but I feel obligated to let others know how bad this was. Bland, lifeless, tasteless and dry are all perfect adjectives for describing the quality of the burritos you should expect to find at this Quesada. The food wasn‚Äôt even wrapped properly and the burrito fell apart before I could even eat it. Shocking. Spend your hard earned money somewhere else.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Robin Rivers","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWovYlIj7djNzn1m4IK1AF1AV_A6GA3Id76btcb3tv4uV5esnJjZw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We were very excited to see that a take-away taco place opened in Kitsilano. The tacos are tasty with lots of fresh ingredients at a reasonable price. The staff was welcoming and helpful. The tacos were exactly as we had hoped - simple ingredients, fresh tasting, lots of options, easy for take-away. This will be a regular stop for us on those nights when we want a tasty, quick meal and my high schooler is already a regular.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPqeW4naVn7j8brmE4ZJRoeR9YurevME6ILEeZN&fid=0x0:0x381f184f3684b65d"],"When":"2022-1-10"}]

[{"Name":"Samuel Barbosa de Mello","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX0peg6-WBhE0EbhzmdEe49pyBGvXkFFn6reIlxa2416ZpRVQKplg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Fatburger, you're the holy grail of burgers, a flavor oasis in a fast food desert. Your juicy, generous patty dances a symphony of flavors on your taste buds, while the golden, crispy fries complete the orchestra with a crescendo of satisfaction. Every bite is an explosion of joy! If you're looking for a feast fit for a king, Fatburger is your destination. Get ready for a gastronomic experience that will make you question the existence of all other burgers.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOffOr271YxfPN_gn_e6pkn4IeQtu0BVBhMIz41&fid=0x0:0x84279e12d3f8cc1"],"When":"2024-11-20"},{"Name":"T L","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLPBYh6J4_PE0ZODwQEK3zA7n0RjjOO6-F5azbw9oIUSg3f=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"I had a chicken burger which comes with sauce options like ranch, honey mustard and sweet Thai chili. I had mine with ranch dressing and it was really good. The lettuce and tomatoes tasted fresh and the chicken was nicely breaded and crispy. I liked the retro feel/look of the place, like an old 60s style diner.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNhs-9Y_o_k_RB1E6oFDietNZISLX0g-W7YP_k&fid=0x0:0x84279e12d3f8cc1"],"When":"2024-11-15"},{"Name":"Daith√≠ Kilcourse","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXpB0OmItsLBGGhpfNEcY_0lXbdAla_7jQ1ZQyMfHX5aboK6jFV=s120-c-rp-mo-ba8-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Great big juicy burgers done to your liking. The staff were excellent and the service was great.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNUPpp9rOenbMKAFRD8SAbRbo400OBgBHARpjz_&fid=0x0:0x84279e12d3f8cc1"],"When":"2024-12-25"},{"Name":"Rebecca P.","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWOtv1z9oQXsu_j8G9uE8jVQGZlbdGZfOgnrsP8gOev0iFfifM3=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"Just ok. The patty was dry and the bun was cold and dense. Did not enjoy it as much as I hoped. Although the burger was disappointing, the wings were flavourful and juicy.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNrcw8iNufTDLv1saA6EAWAFzIVOCrql--OnD66&fid=0x0:0x84279e12d3f8cc1"],"When":"2024-9-18"},{"Name":"Fargol","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjV6roV45JzYGP6MOSsGxN3Vgduj2-Ruh3UXpw908HBVRFG4fAw=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Today's team, 29th May, they were energetic and lovely. It was Warm and welcoming.
Our food was delicious. Juicy meat cooked perfectly. We tried their burger last year, but this time was better.
üçî:9/10
üçü:10/10","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipORmd7U7zEZEGvpEzfe_Z7dRzZiasr6GdtwQdc&fid=0x0:0x84279e12d3f8cc1"],"When":"2024-5-30"},{"Name":"puiyin0116","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIZnuB2P3hOgakhWowlai6-DjvJR_H19Kpmsvk9I0OmgCItfQ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"The burgers are gooddd here!
I ordered a 1/4fatburger meal. It‚Äôs a Combo, comes with fires and drink.
For burger, the meat was juicy and the veggies were fresh. I added burger rings(onions rings) in my burger and was impressed with the size and the crunchiness of it.
The shake was creamy. I ordered a mocha shake. A bit sweet,with a hint of coffee after taste and bitterness. Good to hv one after a long day. BUT not too often hahahaa
The staffs were nice, they greet ppl once they came in.
AND They hv self-ordering machines!! Feel super comfortable that i can take time to review what i want ü´∂üèº
Definitely will come back","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNKRDEak8krJjjCTqsmRdeLLzRus4clasubJDbM&fid=0x0:0x84279e12d3f8cc1"],"When":"2024-5-4"},{"Name":"Cole Davis","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVAOU6XCX3s_R0vWndse-P-J59JZDVGZbi6kfyG2pJARhX4qsYzZw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Solid 4 stars.

The burgers here are great, just make sure to get a fatburger/kingburger instead of the extra value burgers, it's considerably smaller and less juicy.

I wouldn't recommend the big buffalo wings, because they're pretty small for what they claim to be and quite dry. Can't speak for the boneless wings or tenders though, haven't tried them

The dining environment is nice, feels kind of like a retro bar.

Service was quick and the lady was quite friendly! She yells orders so the cooks can hear and repeat it. Something you don't see every day

In terms of the view, there isn't much even if you sit at windows.

Their milkshake is also quite creamy.

Would come back again!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOR6mxAESMFVC62z_rshDUMsju_azk_KXpxkqFg&fid=0x0:0x84279e12d3f8cc1"],"When":"2024-2-4"},{"Name":"Jess T","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVIxMt3zPFtXFm-KuReoSWHN4Lb0f3NV07TDZu4dMGV5N-lspY=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Last time I went several weeks ago, the food was amazing! Just slightly not as good as before, but still superb. There was a small issue of the place not running as efficiently, however, I went again about a week ago and the staff on hand were very efficient.

Price point is a little expensive, but so worth it! You get quality food AND you get full for what you pay! Going to other fast food or restaurants these days cost more and you leave still hungry. Not Fatburger!

I also wanted to mention that I saw a kitchen staff member with a bump on his neck. It's potentially lethal and if anyone on the team reads reviews, I kindly ask that he take some time to get that checked out.

Anyway, will be visiting again soon. Thank you as always Fatburger! You guys really have a special place in my heart.","Images":null,"When":""}]

user_reviews: [{"Name":"Salim Khoso","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjW6akCIMssNMGSreWBJt69YfIq5wWOpE6tVrg0PyeWmvQaJL3P5=s120-c-rp-mo-ba7-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I was looking to try a Mexican food and was happy to find this place. I ordered burrito in a bread as well as bowl and it really tastes the same as the real Mexican food. They have many options to either buy separated item or as a combo. Moreover, I was surprised to see that they have Coke in old traditional glass bottles. A nice place if you are looking for a Mexican taste. The staff is also nice and friendly.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile\u0026image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOcX6nGJ2hTJ6Lx4Lsd4nyt2NhY_yJD6-tgZBKy\u0026fid=0x0:0xaca121ccf1236a8b"],"When":"2024-7-16"},{"Name":"Cheryl Stern","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVwu-XLi_Cy7vvEBnQBlibb3OAHKdPS5ElfBh3gtfHKfx5MUfEg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"I got to my hotel past dinner time but after a day of travel, I was hungry.  Not wanting to go out on foot in an unfamiliar city, I opted to Door Dash a burrito bowl from Quesada.  This is the location it came from.  It was actually quite good, full of fresh ingredients.  I was able to order salsa in various sizes to try them out.  The hot salsa was so good I ended up ordering just salsa in another order during my visit.  The only problem?  I ordered and paid extra for guacamole on my bowl and it was left off.  Would definitely return for the fresh food and great salsa.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Chantelle Bartram","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWpWhcGcxryMBIzUOAx2GNm07lNjnqYdCNMW2MxtJxnC_W1Lr_6=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"My friend and I eat at different Quesada‚Äôs quite often. Placed an order through the website for delivery. Kids quesadillas arrived with just plain chicken and no cheese whatsoever and cut in several tiny pieces with chicken falling  out everywhere. Didn‚Äôt have an option to add it but I thought cheese was a given as it states in the info and has been every time we have ordered them. I then tried calling and spoke to someone who didn‚Äôt even try to rectify the problem. Just told me that I had to specify that I wanted cheese (didn‚Äôt have an option) because some people DONT want cheese in them.  Finally remade the quesadilla with our own cheese for the kids. Finally sat down to eat my tacos and opened them but there was sauce all over in between the tacos. Will never order from this franchise location again.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile\u0026image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNHGKD6w74FC34qEeMV9LQQhpNCrcfkJhUaLevp\u0026fid=0x0:0xaca121ccf1236a8b"],"When":"2024-7-21"},{"Name":"Nicole Oyama","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKRzAGow1zb3ScxMeLK0U-RabwAaW4VtSyneaHqK_spmGoDSQ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Have tried the food multiple times because of the convenient location and every time it is a massive let down. The portions are tiny, they are so cheap and frugal with the fillings and you do not get what you pay for. Any good reviews on here are clearly either friends or paid for to counteract the bad reviews. They should definitely take in the feedback and make some big changes rather than try to drown out the reviews. A tiny spread of beans, sprinkle of lettuce and other toppings. Have never had it this bad at any other Burrito restaurant. Many other better options out there. Don‚Äôt waste your money!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Sally K","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVS0FtpQtx3YuqrRFA5HEswfCULjQCZ3bwXSyydNupxhx29S0cd=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"I recently tried out this taco place, and I have mixed feelings about my experience. On the positive side, their sauces are truly amazing ‚Äì they add a burst of flavor to every bite.\n\nHowever, I must admit that I left feeling a bit disappointed with the portion sizes, especially when it came to the quesadillas. It‚Äôs hard to feel full after a burrito and quesadilla here. What surprised me most was that they don‚Äôt provide any sauce on the side for free, which is quite different from some of the more popular brands I‚Äôve visited.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile\u0026image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOraq4tjNXi6X_hBlabVTgj-4OTplPzwyT3Drod\u0026fid=0x0:0xaca121ccf1236a8b"],"When":"2023-9-10"},{"Name":"Ryan Mureithi","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLMaTczrpcUObs7MFvPi1vLyuaZpykiYJdL8UtxnOtOgD3BFw=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Navi and Smriti were very helpful. user_reviews:
[{"Name":"Miss A","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVhdpd3ejdp83C0oxMMoMw_7lDxzdlekwIWzXICA15sokV5arw5=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"This place is an absolute hotspot for donair enthusiasts, and trust me, once you've had a taste, you'll never look at donairs the same way again.

The donairs are a work of art ‚Äì think soft, pillowy pita bursting with the freshest, most flavorful meat that's been spinning on the rotisserie to savory perfection. Each bite is like a flavor explosion that'll have your taste buds doing a happy dance. And the platters, oh man, talk about a feast! They pile on all the good stuff ‚Äì juicy meat, fresh veggies, and sauces that'll make your taste buds tingle with joy.

But what really sets this place apart is the freshness. I mean, we're talking about ingredients that are as fresh as can be. It's like they pluck the veggies straight from a garden and the meat is so tender, you'd think it was carved just for you.

And the location? Right smack dab in the middle of downtown Granville. It's the heart of the city, and this donair joint is like a food oasis in the bustling urban jungle. The vibes are alive, the energy is electric, and the whole experience is just downright unforgettable.

So, if you're on the hunt for super-good donairs and platters that are as fresh and interesting as they come, you'll find your haven right downtown on Granville. Prepare to have your taste buds blown away!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMK25XjMZdBlV3ZFs1E6fm5pdbZNOrbSy9tLd9e&fid=0x0:0x8d9faba0a8d54019"],"When":"2024-7-11"},{"Name":"Matthew Thai","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUVMr_vmwXGYGArq53J1AjhE6pAHK22uBL43X4Qu6KeK35fdmA=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"food is awesome, vibe is super great especially for such a small spot and it opens late! definitely one of the best places for late night munchies after a night out or just to grab a bite, will definitely come back!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMqUTQSKG8noWj1Vf6fw99c34ShpCoYXy5Y3WLb&fid=0x0:0x8d9faba0a8d54019"],"When":"2024-9-28"},{"Name":"Sparkling Ice","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXGIGkmAxfTN5aYqESNn-w7i49eduk5x6QRBC1fSX8BmzH-GIu_=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Fresh Donair in downtown Vancouver is an absolute must-stop whenever you're in the city. I used to live in Vancouver and was a regular at this spot, and even now, living in Ontario, I make it a point to visit every time I‚Äôm back in town, whether it's once a year or every couple of years. The staff are incredibly friendly, and the portions are huge‚Äîdefinitely worth every penny. The food is consistently delicious, with fresh ingredients and flavors that never disappoint. If you're in Vancouver and looking for Donair, this is the place!

[{"Name":"Naveen Handa","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWD04ZrQ8f-zDWg0XcC-c4SgGfJQpHZTHakcYX8HwQZHnAm8I1N=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"Poor Service and Skimpy Portions

I had a frustrating experience at Chipotle. I waited over 15 minutes just to pay, which is ridiculous for a fast-casual spot. When I finally got my food, the chicken and avocado portions were disappointingly small, especially for the price. While the food tasted good, the poor service and lack of value make it unlikely I'll return.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOPvgGcSMi2tm6J29KqFtRzQhFOJEyZJl6UqUHz&fid=0x0:0xc07997e12af3ea64"],"When":"2024-8-18"},{"Name":"Benedict Santos","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjW6PoqDB0s0FZ-wOoleDfCsv0mfJt9Lh41GYqE5v8-k2M8tAauT=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"I‚Äôm not sure if there were some changes but I‚Äôve never had such full portions of the bowl before. I asked for extra rice and the guy was nice enough to not just add one but two extra scoops! The serving for the beef brisket is one spoonful and it was a lot. Struggled finishing it but I managed to. The service was also excellent and the lunch time crew were nice in my opinion. By the way, they didn‚Äôt charge me extra for anything!!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOkJkYDwdjAtl8Xy7-rrgOIkHAXKmIA8jMCoByw&fid=0x0:0xc07997e12af3ea64"],"When":"2024-9-24"},{"Name":"Lia Gaviola","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocL0V_kvCCTHF-4TUbDFSF79NaHlBkdOst-6LjeKd_WttSjNNg=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"My partner and I were sharing a sofritas bowl that he purchased when I noticed that there was a roach laying on the guacamole. In shock, I brought the bowl to the cashier and told them. The first response we got was ‚Äúoh that‚Äôs not a (looks at the bowl) oh‚Ä¶‚Äù. Instead of an initial apology, what we got was doubt until they realize that it was in fact a roach in the food. They offered to make another bowl but I instead requested a refund. Afterwards, I was offered another bowl to which I rejected and asked them to check their ingredients just to make sure. The server said it was probably from the lettuce and barely expressed an apology which was concerning. However, upon examining the photo we took, the roach looked cooked. We then assumed that the roach was fried in one of the display lights and then fell onto the guac. It was also noticeable that this branch was messy, unclean, and did not feel up to standard. This experience was overall upsetting as Chipotle as we usually have a good experience in either downtown or in the Metrotown branches. Hoping that the CFIA does something about this as this is a health and cleanliness issue as confirmed by the other 1 star reviews as well. Informed Chipotle on this as well in hopes that they can fix the issues in this branch.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMmYa_vkr8XawxwXixvDcmFyEtq5LNB-pOayasZ&fid=0x0:0xc07997e12af3ea64"],"When":"2024-6-26"},{"Name":"Luis Alfonso Martinez","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVX1rRRuS7TONO2H4mTDoMCua1ynXdjYChDB6xb826krfp6uL8Ypw=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"The store was a little dirty but the staff were amazing, very friendly and polite. I am giving a one star review because they made me download their app just to order quesadillas. I recognize that is not the staff's fault but it truly makes no sense if I am on site and I have the money, why can't I just purchase there?","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Sophie N","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVHDslCfCMzHyuEzgj5qXRKt6SsEkiOUiykIa1LLNJL4Dh6c7dBxQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Edit, 1 year later : portions are getting smaller and some employees have a very bad attitude as soon as we are asking for more rice or beans. When they put chicken, they literally put 2 thirds of a scoop and when we ask them to put more they say ''ok double proteins'' and they charge us the extra while the final quantity would be what we would initially get in another Chipotle. Also, we always feel rushed when we're ordering, even when there's no one in line behind us which is very stressful and unpleasant.

Great food, I love their burritos, my fav one is the chicken. Service is pretty amazing most of the time but I had one disappointing experience once. I recommend if you're starving and looking to have a good value/price meal!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipN0xHPzG1A10quFoyz-6zpSEZ7S6IAwxlQxOZjZ&fid=0x0:0xc07997e12af3ea64"],"When":"2022-12-16"},{"Name":"Dave Mossop","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWALBQ7F3_B7LADdhDOSOhQzl0CWCtx3_M7oCfXaSHqVbp5aGK6Zw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Tasty food, decent price. Ordering in person is rushed, to the point they're trying to put stuff on your burrito you didn't ask for... And there wasn't even a long line behind me.

And the scoop of guac was more like half the amount it should have been...

But, it's still Chipotle, and hella tasty.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNB7EGqj8g4v9t0RJmm2CAeSaZph3BncrCj3bTb&fid=0x0:0xc07997e12af3ea64"],"When":"2018-2-21"},{"Name":"Jan H","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKglahnKH2eZ90KuwZveIa7U13AKOgFzXtrzmOCmX39xEiJJQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"They try to save money by giving you less/portioning your food less. There‚Äôs been an obvious decline in service in the last 10 years at all the Chipotle restaurants in Vancouver.

The workers have to audacity to withhold an extra portion of rice or beans by saying ‚ÄúNo‚Äù to extra‚Ä¶ when they‚Äôre actually already skimming their spoons to give you a smaller amount.

Never had had I had someone tell me no more beans at a Chipotle before. Poor service quality and seems to declining.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Daman Kahlon","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUuh25KXC_7cIPWMccptMOYMBoRRJ5AXJev837knamWU2Z9KoSX=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Best service you people serve line a roller coaster i love it so fast and on time ‚ù§Ô∏è","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNi-_y7RJojoYsBCaXUetZHJuT69RJCkJVea5fu&fid=0x0:0xc07997e12af3ea64"],"When":"2024-11-2"}]

When we needed to pre-order various food items in larger quantities, Manager Pratik's prompt and accurate order handling was crucial. His and his staff's professionalism, kindness, and thoughtfulness significantly contributed to our set's smooth operation.

I even contacted him later in the day because the chicken fingers we ordered had either gone missing or got lost in transit somewhere, and he had a new batch delivered to our studio.

I cannot recommend this location enough and will be sure to recommend them to any other films that might be looking for help creating burgers or diner scenes in the future!

Thank you!","Images":null,"When":""}]

[{"Name":"Howard Steffey","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXZGnVPqYkmzcz3zzM_kL9DStBZcoCWm58oYzEMRQCa3mqzBzzm5Q=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"While vacationing in Vancouver for 5 nights, we had a few meals at this Chipotle location with the goal of eating more fresh fruit and vegetables.  Like other reviews have mentioned, the individuals preparing our meals were attempting to skimp on the amount of toppings, such as the fresh tomato salsa.  In fact, I ended up having to pay for a side of salsa just to receive the quantity I wanted.  This is the first time I've ever experienced this at a Chipotle and I've eaten at >50 of them.  That said, the food tasted very good.

Dining room cleanliness could've been a little better, but we did arrive after lunch (both times), and they could've had a large crowd.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipM1dDLuvHu_CnR7KJELhpLLgJPU0ua-jOZt1ZR_&fid=0x0:0xf3432ba79c0904ac"],"When":"2024-9-25"},{"Name":"Gerardo Sanchez","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIvzOoUHj625aK7BZayoTHLwstVHAEdUgI1wVDcYE_WCv3cIA=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"The food is very tasty and it‚Äôs really good value. Unfortunately, tables are often dirty  (see pics) and they‚Äôre usually short on some of the ingredients (either steak, veggies, or lettuce).
Very unpleasant experience.
Needs better management!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMuzX7o4WASOTcYUM9G26dfyBklgaSUjvRQfWOR&fid=0x0:0xf3432ba79c0904ac"],"When":"2024-11-24"},{"Name":"Devyn Argue","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVUTz-Uxp_bEih5tCwckqJPdk-LtlnXxQH2AJC5qcPhtOXIFSOl=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"this location is very dirty.  service was below par, especially for the standard other locations have set. staff members did not have their hair tied up in a hygienic way to keep it away from the food, staff was moving hair out of their face while making food with the same gloves they were touching the food with.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNXGFbbiA2R0uHvZ4MKvqGkwOj19wI-Cy9jqOKN&fid=0x0:0xf3432ba79c0904ac"],"When":"2024-8-13"},{"Name":"Ryan","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWhYqHjbxDNd6i2l7iaCYzaMwur0cjqNKDEjKEE2s4ma5oLE4guRw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"My brief, yet increasingly disillusioning encounters with Chipotle‚Äîthree visits that serve as a microcosm of societal decline‚Äîreveal a troubling trend where the theme of ‚Äúself-serve, clean it yourself‚Äù permeates every facet of the experience. My husband, inexplicably captivated by this corporate entity, exemplifies the modern consumer, drawn to the hollow allure of mass-produced mediocrity that ironically demands more from us while offering less.

Over the course of these three weeks, I've observed a consistent reduction in portion sizes, a disturbing metaphor for how global capitalism strips away our substance, leaving us with less while expecting us to do more‚Äîeven cleaning up after ourselves. The notion of value has become an illusion, where the consumer is shortchanged not just in what is served but in every aspect of the experience, including the expectation that we perform tasks once considered basic services.

On my first visit, I dismissed the lackluster service as a one-off, perhaps a day where the corporate machine had temporarily stalled. But by my second visit, it was clear this was not an anomaly; the staff, disoriented and seemingly purposeless, acted as if their only directive was to leave the customer to their own devices‚Äîto serve themselves, both in meal and in maintaining the cleanliness of the space. Their aimless behavior reflects a deeper societal malaise‚Äîone that alienates workers from their labor, reducing their roles to mechanical motions devoid of engagement, while simultaneously shifting the burden of service onto the customer.

The exorbitant price attached to this experience is a stark reminder of how the elites exploit the economy, charging more while delivering less, all under the guise of self-service. The filth that permeated the tables was a physical manifestation of this self-serve ideology‚Äîa sign that cleanliness, like the quality of the meal, has been outsourced back onto the consumer. It‚Äôs as though the basic expectation of a clean dining area has been abandoned, leaving us to manage it ourselves, further eroding any sense of collective responsibility or communal care.

When I turned back to the cashier after struggling to find a clean table, she asked if I wanted a bag. I replied with a simple "okay," to which she retorted with a baffling, "okay yes or okay no, what does that even mean?" This absurd exchange perfectly encapsulates how communication, like every other aspect of service, has been degraded in this commodified, self-serve environment. My straightforward request should have been clear, yet it became mired in confusion, a byproduct of an interaction stripped of genuine connection, where even the most basic tasks are passed back to the customer.

Despite my growing discontent, I anticipate another visit, driven by my husband‚Äôs unrelenting craving for this overpriced, commodified gruel. This divergence in taste underscores a broader reality in modern relationships: the ongoing negotiation of disparate desires within the artificial confines of a society that insists on self-service in every sense‚Äîdemanding that we not only tolerate poor service but also take on the responsibilities that were once theirs. In the end, this isn‚Äôt just about a disappointing meal‚Äîit‚Äôs a reflection of the broader struggle for authenticity, meaning, and even basic service, in a world increasingly dominated by forces that strip us of all three, leaving us to clean up the mess ourselves.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNHn2iDb_SNFlh1k9nIcSqlGKLgA7mPhFsGD4AB&fid=0x0:0xf3432ba79c0904ac"],"When":"2024-8-24"},{"Name":"Jenine Walker","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJGrHsn8_KdzQGSzRRSYGrI0XfJWk03ad0jIBDV1PIF735Zpw=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Got a burrito bowl and they barely added any protein. The place was a complete mess, all the tables were dirty no napkins or utensils available. The garbage was completely overflowing and a staff member came by to add more garbage to the pile. It wasn‚Äôt that busy so I don‚Äôt know why they didn‚Äôt have someone come clean the place.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOWJpsC0ybqml2Ap8GTbXoVobDMNdF9Tn7wZ1j3&fid=0x0:0xf3432ba79c0904ac"],"When":"2024-11-11"},{"Name":"Reza Sadr","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXru4LpcAn18Jn35NoQwKQxXpHmvDgbhZNgOPAAlkkAAcdzNKI=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"Food quality is declining. It‚Äôs not a busy day, yet as it‚Äôs depicted in the picture below, the grill is overly carbonated and burnt meats (hopefully not mixed burnt chickens) taxing the food quality.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMt9SMOM8j6wXDaQH_B0LaVT-EptJ5DGLEsWA4H&fid=0x0:0xf3432ba79c0904ac"],"When":"2024-9-2"},{"Name":"Tara Turnbull","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLjaKmazlOug0ZvU1jKS2u0zRvdSuyqJKZevbR28ljSfSlq0A=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"jasha the cashier was rude, i asked her for a little more sour cream please, she didn‚Äôt care to look, she didn‚Äôt care to ask, she didn‚Äôt even make eye contact with me, she rolled her eyes and said ‚Äúextra charge‚Äù and huffed and puffed. she made a rude comment to her co worker in front of me, i walked away and won‚Äôt be back.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOeVPgV_IeC4sQ_g0CUzDE6HJjwfhudnr_THOW-&fid=0x0:0xf3432ba79c0904ac"],"When":"2024-10-10"},{"Name":"Hitesh Bhatia","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLO-fwU1qaUIiQ4Q0r7ZR9vXXks5nm5VSSBB0chJ1jHXrTsIA=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"I ordered a veggie bowl from Chipotle, but was given a burrito filled with beef. When they finally provided the bowl, it was missing the veggies and sauces. This careless and reckless service is unacceptable. As a lifelong vegetarian, this experience was not just a mistake but a severe violation of my dietary and religious principles. I am appalled by this disregard and am considering legal action for the distress and harm caused by this incident. Chipotle has given me the most horrible experience of my life, breaking my religious beliefs and trust.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNyZcGx-Tgp3Sk9ZPfg3Dq1eEJWD6sGDvtMwvSV&fid=0x0:0xf3432ba79c0904ac"],"When":"2024-6-29"}]

I mentioned it to one person here who told me ‚Äúit‚Äôs the area‚Äù which, as a restaurant general manager I can tell is is an epically weak response. Dining room was spacious and included with bar stools and tables.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOiBV1w-qO7w81gZyDpRzmX_UsvrrvjDATGsNbr&fid=0x0:0xffa2b11cfdcfa1ef"],"When":"2023-11-1"},{"Name":"wook","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIqp0gMFvE4skPeneUBcTd-N67VCK6a9iR3cSFETH6BY0iXhcE=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Do people in Canada make hamburgers without wearing gloves? It's remarkable to see them confidently handling hamburgers with bare hands, even while customers are watching.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Simranjeet Kaur","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX5rzNy0ATmHFu4TZgYSvribnfdcj7xaKs3hjwDrOqdA-VACXU=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"It was my first time to visit here at this location and for sure the last time. The timing is 6.18 pm and it‚Äôs 1 November, 2024. The cashier girl had zero customer service. Even though I work in A&W and ordered the masala veggie burger. She seemed to be working like as she is forced to. No smile no thankyou at all. The staff should have good gestures.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Ads","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVwDyuvQtXP_VygmU1rNXhUJ0mc48E4h1QtDkdEfrlXmuS-mYhL=s120-c-rp-mo-ba8-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Convenient location when waiting for a late night bus from Broadway City Hall and is a 24 hour location which is super handy.
Staff are friendly, joint is kept in good upkeep and the coffee from A&W has definitely upped it's game since they merged with Pret.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipP-IVlmYCzMY2df5pVUywayMa4R_wACs_IOVqah&fid=0x0:0xffa2b11cfdcfa1ef"],"When":"2023-10-29"},{"Name":"C Ad","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJZpyuvX7NU_PTHMQlvXDNyq5jM3OWSpruXo8eoIzAWI6j52w=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"I have been a long-time patron of AW and have fond memories of its vibrant delicious food. Unfortunately, in recent visits, I‚Äôve noticed a significant decline in both quality and service. It seems that some of the company‚Äôs recent decisions have not been for the better. The once-crowded dining room now feels empty, and the dishes lack the flavor and freshness they used to have.

Moreover, the prices have increased dramatically, far exceeding the rate of inflation. While I understand that costs rise over time, the steep price hikes are hard to justify given the decline in quality. It‚Äôs disappointing to see a place that was once a favorite lose its charm and become less accessible to loyal customers. I truly hope management takes steps to bring back the excellence and value that made this restaurant stand out.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Luke Alberts (RCDRIVER)","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjW-R1GPxwO-xUNzlkqtDxlvDcs-SZ_ol6_9yVcpvuIz022nqhs=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Went here to grab some burgers for me and my son. Was served two absolutely disgusting raw chubby chicken burgers.

Got home 10min drive away, I took a bite of one and didn't notice until after I swallowed. Cut the second one in half to check and guess what? Nearly raw as well! Good thing my son didn't touch his yet!

Drove back and they cooked me new ones, and gave me free fries. That's it. The lady didn't even seem surprised about it, probably happened before maybe new staff? Either way she didn't seem very sincere when she apologized. While I was waiting for my new burgers to cook, two more customers returned with issues with their orders as well.. What a nightmare.

I was in a huge rush and already running late so I didn't have time to argue with them about it I just wanted to eat at that point. I should have demanded some free coupons or something, but I don't know if I even want to return there anymore or any a&w for that matter.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPHrPns0yIa1497hkt4VZFm_hOip1JwxA4VOYv1&fid=0x0:0xffa2b11cfdcfa1ef"],"When":"2018-12-30"},{"Name":"Emilianna Peters","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVQplCH73gaFnpEJ8EHkJQUp6Add876Ypnn4snVV-5O_-JjDTk=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Order missing items. Gurjeet was incredibly rude when we went to ask to have them replaced. The order came with no sauce, no dips, the coffee had to creams or sugars, and she said that it was our fault. When we showed the recipet and explained that we didnt get things, she saod it wasn't their problem and that they would replace the items. Honestly just incredibly rude, and surprising sonsidering that replacing a small order of fries would cost almost nothing.","Images":null,"When":""}]

Now back to this joint the place was clean, staff was friendly and service was good.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOLKLuT8fVUbRG5ugaMF6ZQsA8FoxqaXZIK5j26&fid=0x0:0x319f332ed8fa8bf1"],"When":"2018-11-18"},{"Name":"john helcher","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocItINmI3Um_uVNk2oxm0yTtj5KdVOMoDEBbY3EJmxA7NXl-5g=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Great burger, great location, super friendly service. But I can't believe I can't get an A&W root beer float here. Wait.. What... ? Isn't that part of the whole A&W experience. And I wasn't the only one who was surprised by this. When the group behind me heard me ask for one and here they couldn't get one they also left. I happened to come back later and get a burger because I was staying at a hotel a few buildings down. And that ood and experience warrants the review I left. Ut I know after talking to the other group who left earlier when I did...they walked a LONG way to get a float. A lot of people visit here before departing on cruises after walking around the city. I am not a market research specialists...but I suspect a lot of those people from the U.S. who know A&W would love to come in and get a root beer float.","Images":null,"When":""}]

Then we went for olives and the exact same thing, I asked if I could have a lot of olives and I got like 3 of them for the whole sub. I had to repeat twice and I ended up with the amount in the photo. It seemed some kind of unfunny sketch.

I have no idea why but this is the first time i see it in a subway, and this is the third time in this place. Most of the workers are absolutely delightful but I swear that depending of who I find working I know I will end up eating slightly seasoned bread.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPsiFADAzglTbuHU-W-ZkFDHQK72fGDc7YE-4rH&fid=0x0:0xb050ac25aee49c5c"],"When":"2024-5-15"},{"Name":"Ed Vonhouzel","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocL6aspwEKSWiWIyIG-hfU-CmsfVSQ-mjxJFoAo_hZl3C11jBA=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"I really like the staff and it‚Äôs great food, but last week I just found out ALL tips go to the Manager only‚Ä¶ This is disgraceful as they are not the ones front line and centre doing the hard work.

I got the chicken wrap most days, and sometimes the new flatbread pizza and some timbits, along with a drink. The food is pretty good, the service is incredibly slow. I had to wait for 5 minutes for a cashier to show up on time, and usually it takes up to 15 minutes to receive food.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipN53IEpO1FwewhRjoN90Bs9iPryX5wKfx159x6K&fid=0x0:0x5130b6950efc878e"],"When":"2024-8-25"},{"Name":"parin saemiyan","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVO8dUTsSB-_7XCZPmDVp_5YCUEVR6ikfwlgHE3u8L1At-SafU=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"This Tim Hortons is pretty nice, and the staff are super friendly and helpful.

That said, it‚Äôs usually really busy, so you‚Äôll probably end up waiting in line for a while to order and get your food since they handle a lot of in-person and online orders.

If you‚Äôre planning to study here or grab something before class, get there early as there aren‚Äôt many outlets, seats fill up fast and lines can get pretty long.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Kenneth Lai","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVaxVGYXfpPoTmAfNhLJtbs31BGbuX8DK_7Hj5GOcCBNwv8VjrvXA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba7-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Tim Hortons at UBC is a fantastic spot for students and staff. Conveniently located on campus, it offers quick access to delicious meals and snacks. Their sweet chili chicken wrap is a standout, boasting a perfect blend of flavors that's both satisfying and affordable. The prices are budget-friendly, making it an ideal choice for those seeking quality without breaking the bank. The friendly staff and speedy service add to the overall positive experience. It's a go-to place for a tasty, convenient meal at a great price.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPyrwR9GNsOQg_gsR_-n15z4E3ZtxW48I_AfgIh&fid=0x0:0x5130b6950efc878e"],"When":"2024-5-18"},{"Name":"FARZAM ameri","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUC2df7lOXeiqMsnPi2htms2568VuOUkmExj9MZ8kkh6j2hvhus=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Defenately one of the slowest Tim Hortons you can ever meet in your life, No matter what time of the day U go there, there is always a huge line up for ordering and a double huge line waiting for their orders. Always short on staff and those few staff are old or middle aged and they are super slow.
If U are in rush dont go there.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPq4QoqtfWzvVv79fDVLkZyqnKEokF26M7-gNZG&fid=0x0:0x5130b6950efc878e"],"When":"2024-7-25"},{"Name":"brian120417","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWFywK3t8crg6bMuPhKjGg8TrQT7JzMjKfOhk3rtkVVK1ErjhGs=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Ordered a coffee and bagel and waited about 15-18 minutes but had to leave and never got my order.  The reason; there were about 50 customers waiting for their orders.  Mostly UBC students.  Most of them crowding around the pick up counter like a pack of hyenas around a kill.

Woefully understaffed and the order status boards are a joke.  They are never close to accurate.  Thus people feel the need to crowd the counter in case their order suddenly pops up.

Such a sorry operation.  I will not go to this location again.

Brian R","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Connie Steel","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKJId2k6PeYRKGvAp4KO6Z_RTe-7KPujKgztldYHe0zAh_tZg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I don't normally give a chain store all 5's, however, this place saved us when we realized breakfast wasn't included at our residence.  I liked the London Fog, which is an Earl Grey latte with a shot of vanilla syrup. Business travelers:  they do boxed coffee and boxed tea for meetings.  American tourists: Tim Hortons is like an upscale Dunkin Donuts.  Good price point, gorgeous donuts, and tempting pastries.  It seemed like they also have some hot food options, but I was distracted by the pretty donuts (how do they get the icing so shiny?)  You should visit one at least once while in Canada.  This one is super convenient if you are staying at Gage Residences at UBC.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNIQBfwgA9OhTLKoOGpP5KNLOJp6hNYWl3VN9Wl&fid=0x0:0x5130b6950efc878e"],"When":"2024-7-6"},{"Name":"Kabir Salgani","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXJHUQCifn7pU8ubekBkzk1ZO2TtQgjyLi40AmKO3Y6t4tI1248tg=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Today i did a mobile order from this location and i ordered 9 chocolate tim bits but when i went for pick up they said they dont have chocolate tim bits which is fine it happens alot but instead of compensating me they said they can even give me a donut because the price is high for donut.. It doesnt matter whats the price is.. its not my fault that you guys dont have the thing which i ordered and when i came back home after driving ten minutes i found i am missing 2 times bits for which i have paid ‚Ä¶ Its worst customer service ever i encountered","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipP1Ux-C8xU58dJNEX3C1WLsRnKsppd7JviPPbuu&fid=0x0:0x5130b6950efc878e"],"When":"2024-11-10"},{"Name":"Mehran bakhtiari","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX52_I8QBEvpbwP2DsvccLDQ1hUjTB0qEjwNL_660Q7Wjozcaqk=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"This branch has every bad attribute that a Tim Horton needs to have as the worst branch in all of Canada.
