[{"Name":"David Durango","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjV_2PesKmt-cFSjzAWF8ZpvzKFIQfYWeYB7sfNc7YronxWjhwaDKw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"Pros: very nice atmosphere, nicely decorated, welcoming and cool. You can tell the food is freshly cooked. The receptionist is nice and provides good service. Price is not abusive, but not a good deal either.

Cons: I bought the bacon cheese burger. It was OK, but not great as far as burgers go. The patty is very thin and it was burnt at the edges. That burnt taste disrupted all the other flavours unfortunately. Burger was also rather thin, and medium/small sized for $12. The cost of that with a can of Pepsi was almost $15. Can't tell if it was worth it. Overall the burger was alright, but nothing special. I wouldn't come here regularly, but I might return and try other food.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPC_WSVm2R1iWnu3CrO7emblqKzKIatkUEdN5uV&fid=0x0:0xeda594cb6ca6920d"],"When":"2024-11-8"},{"Name":"AJ Brown","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUsu0-zLfdBIi0BMvFkmCrQ7LvpDpcqpsmyMO44b1viyR7y0ygy=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Great vibes. Love the wall art and neon signs.

Absolutely smashing smash burger. Got the bacon cheeseburger and it delivers on all fronts. Flavour! Texture! Toppings!

Didn‚Äôt try anything else but you better believe I‚Äôll be back. Outstanding!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPMq0ttU_bQMDF3XRWkQVIT4ns8WiFz2MCvNkrH&fid=0x0:0xeda594cb6ca6920d"],"When":"2024-12-7"},{"Name":"Shelby McLean","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXGrJIxT_w5hI3sCYlNvQIRBmY0nhG0Y1Wwz7fnYiH39NwxA_WG=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Very cool place with good food. Our order was a bacon cheeseburger with crinkle fries, a vegan crispy chicken burger with yam fries, and two milkshakes: Oreo and Reese‚Äôs peanut butter cup. I recommend trying the vegan chicken burger if that‚Äôs your thing, definitely with the yam fries!! Fast and friendly service at the counter. Compliments to the chef who came out to see us and check in ‚Äî it‚Äôs a new place so they‚Äôre open and receptive to hearing what people want. No washrooms inside but affiliated with The Cambie around the corner. Added seating in the restaurant and a small patio out front. Will definitely be back (:","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMdvrZ_7bO0zYB-y566GFF3Cc9bPZf4fkm4oT6j&fid=0x0:0xeda594cb6ca6920d"],"When":"2024-5-7"},{"Name":"em ladou","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJp3bi7taDvf1OUi1p06pu7kgDizbNv37YGZ7wxE7ujoS6rOg=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"We ordered from skip the dishes - I got the beyond veggie burger... asked for 1 patty and received 2, there was 1 piece of tomato, 1 flimsy leaf of lettuce and 3 pickles all smooched in the middle of the burger and smashed patties are very wide, also no option to add cheese... it just seemed like no effort was put into it. My partner enjoyed his double bacon cheese burger, just that there was not many toppings in it. Fries were a good portion but arrived cold (might not be restaurants fault)

In the picture I added my own cheese ( I didn't have much at home) pickles are on the other side.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOZRBiYjpxAO-QUcJz2r7ZKrtVfdAaQoXGn4-MS&fid=0x0:0xeda594cb6ca6920d"],"When":"2024-7-27"},{"Name":"Olivia Levesque","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUb4zZbV0YXKhHkU2F_3dwx03KNXKQqTHdsRQyeSWJ9SjDYl5kv3A=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"The single patty bacon cheese burger was absolutely delicious, ordered as a combo with the crinkle cut fries & brisk iced. Would definitely order the burger again, but the fries ill pass on next time as they were more on the mushy side.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPNWGu7jj0plNj9ZXWnfHWYCySZb1ilYzJZSY4H&fid=0x0:0xeda594cb6ca6920d"],"When":"2024-10-4"},{"Name":"Emmanuel Mor√∫a","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXVgDDr7Bq5maIJYTC_on0x6OlVE8ViM6rt1o7JGzQMU2HdiVQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I ordered a Bacon Cheeseburger with crinkled cut fries and a brisk tea, very tasty burger with flattened meat which is unsual but definitely good as hell, service is super fast, courteous and attentive. Place is always clean, might need to add a washroom for customers tho, but overall very nice experience and a hell of a meal.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOJy0Y21-kOiIRcC21u4vqQnUEKGH7fThlshY-h&fid=0x0:0xeda594cb6ca6920d"],"When":"2024-8-4"},{"Name":"cgmc70","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVzXD32DfRqqvnrxut0qW4Xp1dRXi1jGQ41udzAPASAQpd5iacc=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"My cousin & I just came across this place & decided to try it .. Exterior vibe just called us in ü•∞ .. Ordered 2 shakes & fries to share, picked the window to enjoy our snack. 1st impressions inside was that it was SO clean!!! Table tops were nice & smooth, and our window view was great!
Friendly & quick service .. Owner gave us a couple of stamp cards towards our next purchase.. We‚Äôll definitely be back !!!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipP2UdZuJKWqbBaqRrtYIJ1akNRJnztBZQHXxv-3&fid=0x0:0xeda594cb6ca6920d"],"When":"2024-6-18"},{"Name":"Keenan Nuttall","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX-45u8DUs7KPX3Ki1k-P7NTWYoNYOccWZLNsOVIRFCYOzhvSQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Arriving at 5:32 and promptly receiving my order by 5:39, the efficiency of service at this establishment is commendable. The carefully curated music and inviting atmosphere, complete with the addition of a comfortable couch, contribute to a warm and welcoming dining experience.

Manager Thomas exemplifies hospitality by not only providing attentive service but also directing attention to complimentary amenities such as the free lemon water. Additionally, his evident kindness towards his employees enhances the overall positive atmosphere.

The ordered burger, priced at $8, while featuring authentic burger meat, falls slightly short of expectations compared to competitors like A&W. However, it offers a refreshing departure from typical fast-food fare, providing a pleasant change of pace.

On a integer scale (with 0 representing fast food), I rate this establishment a 0.2, acknowledging its efforts to elevate the dining experience beyond typical fast-food standards.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipM6V8cLCtXNdS19c57hY1mbofnILEdduN65i4lj&fid=0x0:0xeda594cb6ca6920d"],"When":"2024-4-15"}]

His name was ankit and the girl was simran, they gave us very good service while we were in the store, great communication skills and best service provided. It was a nice visit because the service was good. We would love to visit the store again.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Kat Ruston","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUK6qkOolyqmWjrGsFU8pVzuAEXnECAUDmEp9ZoNWqeUKKCpxEqXw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I appreciate how this location is managed. It goes far beyond my expectation for fast food. A&W is always my go to for quick but QUALITY convenient food. I never feel gross with their food.

Thank you, A&W for making cheat meals always satisfying!! (My go to is Papa burger, sub lettuce wrap + no mayo and fries... Sometimes double fries!)","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNOc_gY5tKoCwfVMwFISDZPRwXxIaoGdf0zb2dO&fid=0x0:0xb92249ac468832cc"],"When":"2021-4-28"},{"Name":"Peter Au","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUwBxrbZVtlTM1OV2SDGm3NwMn7yUHEw1MaS3fh_B2utP_W4kON=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"I used to come to this A&W while I was working around the area a few years back. While I had an appointment earlier with the hospital, I decided to come again.

Ordered a mama burger combo with onion rings, and root beer. The root beer was using the frost chilled mug which was a good idea to keep the drink cold without ice melting to water down the drink. However, this location spilled the root beer outside the mug without wiping it clean. The root beer got frozen on the outside. It then melted while I put it on my table, creating a mess.

When I was picking up my food, I saw no napkins nor they were provided anywhere I could pick up. I asked for some. The lady pointed to the tray on the oil-stained single piece of napkin unfolded lining under my onion rings. I was surprised not to be given any extra napkins when asked in any branded food chain store.

The lady who took orders had no smile all through. I seldom cared much about this kind of thing, but together with the above issue, I could not help but taking note of it.

The food was good though. The burger was well made and onion rings were freshly prepared. This earned them back one star more than I would initially like to give.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipP1FnhStgDj_9Zj3xi2_W6QBZyT-B6PbOzwJU41&fid=0x0:0xb92249ac468832cc"],"When":"2023-8-3"},{"Name":"Zac A","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUKH0x18-boXvRQW3CKdXmlcw9Ga4TtlIUfrKNoZCIhPCuaptVz=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"The regular place. Nothing stand out","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipM00W4QP7VL0yuwjSH-GrO0nBYSaqV6idEWqwAx&fid=0x0:0xb92249ac468832cc"],"When":"2024-12-10"}]

user_reviews:
[{"Name":"Chris Charles","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVrISq9W73HrjlGADtJWok_5lo7jNqrkaquC2lVl_FVv-ialwI=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"What a wonderful local Italian restaurant!   Nestled intimately in the Dunbar neighbourhood, I passed this resto for years without ever trying it until tonight.   And what a decision!   Food was delicious, excellent, wonderful.   I stuck to the evening specials ‚Äî veal with seasonal veggies and homemade pasta, that the waiter said has been on the menu for 34 years (incredible).  It was excellent, flavourful, everything was delicious and wonderful.  Throw in a few glasses of white wine and you‚Äôre totally good to go! Service impeccable and friendly, like a great neighbourhood restaurant should be!   Will definitely be back for sure !    Excellent experience!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOYssGks_7wTAx_N8jv0tVQ8uVfVY8aoqTlI-0V&fid=0x0:0xa009c83facfa02b2"],"When":"2024-4-14"},{"Name":"Benjamin O","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX0AEZ4nN0g3LRlrKmy826B4mTNNVNjrTxwcXXXBDK3e_y-xXVOew=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"The piano was great and very lovely vibe.
Service was abrupt, functional, and cold.
Food presentation and plating were excellent.
Flavors were a bit off. I love butter and garlic, but somehow, there was too much of those things. Veal was tender. Muscles had an odd smell.
We had a large group of 4 kids and 5 adults, which triggered an 18% tip. I'm not sure if I would have even tipped 10%. The prices were good.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOgxy4Ghmiu1dq3gRgKypZJZs7pCVxCsOhrsidF&fid=0x0:0xa009c83facfa02b2"],"When":"2024-6-10"},{"Name":"Josephine Ma","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjW4ctBP8R2rm9S8Aa5NyuULMapTvyTQYakS6AvI9Cd025oSy86H=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Situated at a quiet corner of Dunbar St. is a charming, family owned restaurant called La Notte that serves up some incredibly delicious Italian eats.

Featured here:
Carpaccio
Mussels
Eggplant Parmigiana
Linguine Alla Vongole
Marguerita Pizza
Tiramisu

Mussels were plump, moist, tender, juicy, and flavorful. These were some of the best mussels I've had in a very long time.

Marguerita Pizza was tasty but more cheese would have been preferred.

Eggplant Parmigiano far exceeded my expectations. To be honest, I was a bit skeptical about ordering this dish. The last time I ordered eggplant in an Italian restaurant, I found that the eggplant was not as soft as I had hoped it would be, and was very much lacking in flavor. Not the case with this eggplant dish. My husband tried my Eggplant Parmigiana and he was blown away by it as well.

Linguine Alla Vongole and the Fettucine that came with my Eggplant Parmigiana had both been cooked al dente and were accompanied with very flavorful sauces.

It's been awhile since I've had a good Tiramisu, and this was definitely a good one!

In most respects the service was decent; however, we were a bit turned off by response our server gave when one person in our group inquired about the chocolate cake they were serving for dessert. He asked the server if she could describe the chocolate cake. Her response seemed to imply that it was a stupid question to ask. As though we should already know from the name of the dessert, that it's a cake and it's chocolatey. The question was asked though in the hopes of receiving information that might describe whether it was moist, or dense, or filled with chocolate ganache, or whether it had a crunchy wafer in the middle, or whether it was covered in chocolate buttercream frosting. Our server's response was quite a turn off. Aside from this though...service was good throughout the rest of the evening.

Service: Could have been better
Parking: Free parking on the side street
Location: 3307 Dunbar St., Vancouver, BC","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMEUZxfHtSBIpk0XdHybesPfNmYwEGSQfH9hnfk&fid=0x0:0xa009c83facfa02b2"],"When":"2023-12-1"},{"Name":"Timothy Chan (TimTim)","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjURIoSl-5oBZzcRd91bCuWm5mXoW-rsGa8ZawpNSjddYI4bCo-k=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Cozy little place suitable for intimate dates or gatherings. The place can get a little noisy. Has live piano music too. The food is excellent and prices are reasonable. Also excellent customer service. We will be back.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOL-A_SXZTq4BIvfeavzJKxrbPgVJ4t2t6ehoK4&fid=0x0:0xa009c83facfa02b2"],"When":"2023-12-18"},{"Name":"Noa Damiani","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKUCwWOXuNJeEPDlRyYKWRNcmB4oD9tS7rSX8xSTt26mNi7gQ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"Don‚Äôt really know how to describe this place other than mid. Everything (including soup, salad, ESPECIALLY carpaccio) was doused in cheap tasting olive oil. They try to hide the low quality of the ingredients by over-dressing/saucing everything. I‚Äôm pretty sure the tomato sauce for the gnocchi was bought in from Sysco. Vegetables in the minestrone soup were undercooked and the carpaccio felt like taking a shot of Walmart olive oil. I literally could not taste the meat - pretty sure all the protein (and likely also the pasta) is precooked and frozen, resulting in a lack of flavour and an overall disappointing experience.

(Giving the atmosphere 3 stars for the phenomenal live piano player! Yes, this is the best milkshake in town. Red Robin and White Spot do not stand a chance. Maybe Fatburger could stand up to them, but I haven't tried theirs before.

Review:
Someone on Reddit said that this is where you go to get the best milkshake in town. I was rather skeptical that some little corner store in the heart of the Downtown Eastside could hold that title, so I decided to try it for myself.

The milkshake costs $6 (compared to Red Robin milkshakes which go for $7). It consists of 3 scoops of ice cream, an unknown white liquid that is probably cream, and maybe other ingredients that I didn't notice. There are about 16-20 ice cream flavours and you can pick up to 3 of them. They make the milkshakes in front of you for your viewing pleasure.

I personally had the Strawberry + Vanilla + Mango milkshake and it was simply DIVINE. The thickness was perfect and it was very smooth and creamy. I would 100% recommend this if you're in the area and looking for a milkshake, however I don't think it is worth going on a journey to visit unless you're some sort of adventurer.

The location and ambience is certainly not the best, but you'd likely be a fool to think that a place in the DTES smackdab on Hastings is a place that you'd go to for a comfy atmosphere. However, the owner and the employees are pleasant and friendly folk. I walked into a "Hi, how are you, my friend?" once I entered. Great attitude! I overheard some chatter and apparently they've been around for about 20 years now.

Definitely worth a visit if you're a curious milkshake connoisseur.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipM6UbvsG1FDkaHOdDhgmm2Ka7xxXc9HRrsx0zyj&fid=0x0:0x641e3eb6d33ef898"],"When":"2022-4-27"},{"Name":"Kelly Hrelja","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUVWh8qmVdPEfqahFaQ6ox93SOukCBaQIQqwS9jEApuOOnHfC4ZzQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I honestly love this place and have been going semi-regularly for about a year and a half. It's the only place I'll get milkshakes now! They have a TON of different ice cream flavours (including some cool ones like root beer float), so the milkshake combos are endless. Also LOVE their cheese pizza which has white sauce and sesame seeds on the crust. Grilled cheese is a good deal at $5 for two. The night staff are super kind but worth mentioning that most of their clientele are DTES residents","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Misha Sample","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVSdo1w83leysMEkxM5fjMksNBkDuxJgMVVK1LliiKcT_ZNTSi9Sg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"The cheese cake is awesome! The service is very fast too as they always have at least 3-4 people serving and when it's busy 5-6 servers. The burgers are good too and the milkshakes are worth the 5$ you pay as they are literally made with only icecream and a bit of milk. I would have given 5 stars but the location and over-all ambiance are lacking. In general I will say that the location is great if you live or work somewhere near by and want to eat out without breaking the bank and since it is a takeout only place with super quick service the ambiance is not all that important.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"L ‚ÄúP3N‚Äù B","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUh-UGBUNem5TJ2P_14rcdbt1vUCwAuu7aPgOLjSr3rgXvNHK3A=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Love their milkshakes and pizza - other foods are high quality in deliciousness as well. Each time I bring someone here, they comment how delicious it is and how much of a hidden gem they are.

Hidden gem indeed, I recommend giving New Brandiz a try regardless of how you feel about the neighborhood.

The only con I can think of is how inconsistent they can be with their hours. Even the listed hours on here seem to be wrong & not updated in a while. It sucks but to be expected due to how few workers they have hired. In all, a very small price to pay for their fabulous foods & drinks. :)","Images":null,"When":""}]

user_reviews: [{"Name":"Minyoung Park","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocI6UiB4ukByUssouP7rxYxjakeP_U2cD50PcO6YInibSKEuLg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"I visited the store with my family last Saturday afternoon. I ordered two sandwiches, and when I mentioned that there was an offer, she told me to place the order online. I did as instructed and sat down to eat. While eating, my child spat out part of the sandwich, saying there was a foreign object in it. Upon checking, it turned out to be a piece of steel wool. When my child informed the staff, she responded that it likely came from the bread. I was shocked to overhear this. There was no apology, and the attitude was as if it wasn‚Äôt their problem since it came from the bread.\nBoth my wife and I went back to speak to her, and even then, we received the same response. My wife, feeling upset, asked if an apology should come first. Only then did she offer a brief apology, and that was the end of it.\nNot only was I upset about finding a foreign object that should never have been there in the first place, but the staff's attitude was also shocking and extremely unpleasant. We went to try their chicken today for the first time. The menu made it sound like it was Korean fried chicken. We ordered the yangyeom (sweet and spicy). When we got it we were surprised how they came in these huge balls but upon first bite we learned that half of it was just batter (sticky doughy texture). The rest were also just as doughy.

While the chicken itself was tender and tasty, this is NOT Korean style fried chicken.  It‚Äôs more like a heavy battered chicken meatball. It still tasted good but definitely not worth the price and not what we expected.

Edit: ok I‚Äôm changing this to 1 star. I got home and took apart the remaining chicken balls. It was half yellow ‚Äòbatter‚Äô and chicken skin and half actual chicken. In fact, it was so ‚Ä¶ unexpected‚Ä¶ that I decided to make a video review of these ‚Äòmeatballs‚Äô being taken apart.

Definitely will not go back and wondering if this is unique to this store or to others as it is a franchised chain.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMyHsAZ2-SdDlgOfLKI0ncd0scj-lJOm2J0Dafh&fid=0x0:0xdedb520ffee85475"],"When":"2021-10-23"},{"Name":"Ryan Wang","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUnJ8DwJvwkDxj1059vEktYj3QQ4Venz8sBldx-ql-dLXJc8D8=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Ordered full size for original taste. [{"Name":"Justin Lui","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjW-FdRiGfo2e9hT3F0_cCnq49mtFvfr5P2Kj_MWoiXLHpbkMBi_=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Hm, growing up in New Orleans with a strong Vietnamese population, the food here is on par with I grew up with.

Food is a strong 4 star (or a low end 5 star).

Ordered the beef ball pho for the nephew. Solid pho. Brown tinge, semi oily, all good signs.

Also the spring rolls, 4 star. They don‚Äôt put mint inside which is a good thing.

The vermicelli lemon grass beef with spring roll? Very nice. $17.50CAD, it‚Äôs semi pricey but it‚Äôs Vancouver. Large portion so it could make a meal and a half.

Fried spring roll? Nice. The other 3 dishes very solid. Overall, enjoy.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNVbcepGbE8DK7gGEaT4s5njpHpbJugJrKrVNqi&fid=0x0:0x70e8369905c747ed"],"When":"2024-7-11"},{"Name":"Joanna Wang","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXVKywkcSQSTgK9g7RgoZY0axGSK_FaSWEp99fbQnc0Tq28WlTy=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"üëçüèªgreen papaya salad: Very refreshing and the fish sauce was sweetü•∞ plenty of roasted peanuts on top which added crunchiness, the portion was quite big given the price!
ü´∏üèªcrab spring roll: so so
üëåüèªBeef rib combo:  spring roll tastes p good but beef ribs were quite fatty to my taste and the sugarcane shrimp tasted like lots of starch, but in general good value because it‚Äôs really filling
üëçüèªLemongrass salad roll: my goto dish all the time, the best salad roll ever! Not stuffed with vermicelli like everywhere else, the herbs and picked veggies filling goes well with the sweet and smoky chicken. Tried the pork one once but not as good. Their satay sauce made the rolls a solid 1000/10!!!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNmv0_uxRsXC78zlZpVGiJEDyiA43H9OILV-NJE&fid=0x0:0x70e8369905c747ed"],"When":"2023-8-24"},{"Name":"Mahdad Nour","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLq5GqpFajc0Znw8mo90PS6wome53kTdEKYoi-WehAkn2r7VA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"Food was good specially the chicken (not the pork) but I didn‚Äôt understand the rudeness of a boy working there, he was impolite and aggressive with no reason and acted weird. Wish him find a satisfying job.
Unfortunately, I have to say one of the worst restaurants I‚Äôve ever been in Vancouver because of staff and service!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNuDWzSqZ9OrSQ7_dw-V1f5U8eMKaEKyB8Eafwy&fid=0x0:0x70e8369905c747ed"],"When":"2024-7-2"},{"Name":"Rachel Wong","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXomH1lZlI7mhtYlp01FAnTARB7FsittB8nZfAF_A5Jz0GL70U=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Great lil spot for pho and banh mi! Everything you‚Äôd need for a quick lunch. Banh mi was delicious!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipN5GNs3C0RTL69HqzJUNc_0oisdZ8k6lUXK7qxV&fid=0x0:0x70e8369905c747ed"],"When":"2024-12-21"},{"Name":"William Lau","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVmQdctlbM12t5Occdf84xI_X4OatAdUnoO7Mf5nuujaBWYasmgPA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Food was ok. My #46 dish ($17.50) was a tad underwhelming as far as flavour is concerned. Meat and pickled radish didn't have much flavour. Fish sauce dip for spring roll was a compensation for that at least. Next time I'll try their namesake, a baoguette (banh mi)!

Parking is metered street parking unless you go more than a couple blocks away for residential parking.

Service was ok. Taking orders was good but no follow up after bringing food with refills of drinks.

Dining room was not too busy but we were there kind of late in the evening.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNJ1Ix5NdkS0jWHz0KyQyZLiskeB2UoR7tgKy3A&fid=0x0:0x70e8369905c747ed"],"When":"2023-6-8"},{"Name":"Patrick Cheng","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLF-zGQ83z5pjjXkV0kf822DW9RQtMHgVs8ODXBiG0gHzpnaw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"A  Vietnamese restaurant that deserves a solid 4. Pork & crab meat noodle soup is awesome. The soup base looks thin but tastes really rich. The food in the bowl is plentiful and delicious - pork & crab meat ball and fish cake are house-made, well textured and tasty. The bean curb is not fresh enough or washed well though. Rare beef & beef ball noodle soup is another delight to the taste buds. The soup is very hot when served which is a nice thing to me. Love the taste and texture of the beef balls. The last dishes ordered is house special rolls. It‚Äôs a mix of traditional deep fried spring rolls and paper rich rolls. Truly amazing. Overall very happy with the food in this restaurant. Looking forward to the next visit.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPOjgxIj2yka-rdXufGZN3-_IKXHN0RyJOJgtca&fid=0x0:0x70e8369905c747ed"],"When":"2023-1-13"},{"Name":"w","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVECjtzjKwGGU2yagM5sH2sMNpUPFv0VdGQBZqvehtzvpFlyVDi=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"sooo yummy and had a great time. reasonable prices","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPe6zFV-RXG60VYiU5Xt1XfEFmNTpUfVwoZxbVz&fid=0x0:0x70e8369905c747ed"],"When":"2024-8-9"},{"Name":"Michelle Hillock","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJrzRoOQIhVr_Azv33mg4FgqnXjS5clP8SiddvR3MVEWC9e9w=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"What is going on. The bread is so stale and dry. This is the worst banh mi in my entire life. The tasteless meat. The dense dry stale bread is now the correct type of bread for banh mi. Price $8.50 in store and $10 on door dash.  Totally unacceptable. Please do better. The soup spilled all over in the bag they used. It was cling wrapped but the lid came off and pho soup spilled on everything. The salad rolls are pictured too.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOJ3QJGn7mpRKg7eKm-GD8CH2x4eakjAN5hB2d0&fid=0x0:0x70e8369905c747ed"],"When":"2024-6-9"}]

user_reviews:
[{"Name":"Lost in Flax Blog","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWnuEdz0exGAqoaKWuU3YZ60m50P5j2VjB_aqaZVW3VnTtNws28=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"What can I say? My family have been dining at White Spot Kerrisdale for nearly 30 years! I used to come when I was very little and now my daughter (who is 3) experienced her rite of passage with the pirate pack recently! I was blown away by the sheer portions of every dish including her pirate pack and the cute menu/colouring page she received. They have many options for the pirate pack now! The vanilla bean ice cream was also of exceptional quality, which surprised me.

I usually order the Legendary burger with extra Triple-O Sauce and subbed sweet potato fries but this time I threw good sense to the wind (my weight watching sense, that is) and ordered a 6oz bacon cheeseburger with subbed poutine and an extra side of tartar sauce as a dip! My family ordered the Spot‚Äôs fish and chips (so crispy, so fresh), and the Monty Mushroom burger. No complaints from any of us, particularly from my little one. We will definitely be back. Thank you White Spot for always staying consistent! Will probably order the milkshake, cheesy bacon pierogies, crispy haddock burger next time around! Or stop by for breakfast. You can‚Äôt go wrong!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipO6aHj-dEL92ssnBKD7tf_kKtXe42jPnot8PZEo&fid=0x0:0xc1287e6cfbaf4bc5"],"When":"2024-10-22"},{"Name":"Marcus Xiong","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWNKHkNu0r9L6u_s13vBOcHGIOl_tisn1xjH9tQbojiCd_NkDw-YQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"The best option in Kerrisdale for western food. The service is usually quite slow, but the food makes up for it. I come here about once every 1-2 months, and on my latest visit, I got chicken strips and a BBQ chicken flatbread. Their burgers, fries and milkshakes are some of the best on the menu, but they also have lots of other options from other cuisines.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMrcohLErP9t8Fy9iRT4zqwtFYX65SCg1tMqg8t&fid=0x0:0xc1287e6cfbaf4bc5"],"When":"2024-7-1"},{"Name":"May Pantaleon","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXNbv66HOBn65rTAVh2W7iNvWBPgyTNl-D5o6mnSaULlkltF-gt6A=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"It's okay. Our server was attentive and helpful. Food was good; however, the fries we were served was inedible (burnt in places, dried out, and chewy, didn't taste fresh) and shouldn't have been served in the first place but we paid for it anyway.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOii6c3k1u6L34rOtZFx7G0_ae1V26sKkzOW2g2&fid=0x0:0xc1287e6cfbaf4bc5"],"When":"2024-10-1"},{"Name":"Wei x","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX_gqktxpcwm5-Ae9lvoeXAyfIgSzBgJfFmiGs2nilpJU5Zx6z7jw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"The place has been in the neighborhood for decades. One of oldest white spot that we have been to. Food is average for white spot. Service is not bad.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOt-i4cXCUS9mJFShOt_4612Swg2hCOoa-0p7zQ&fid=0x0:0xc1287e6cfbaf4bc5"],"When":"2024-12-16"},{"Name":"Seonjae Im","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIt1GgA1qP_NjMCQxVFgkQjulbXGtYGtfVP5U0gEJ-yvUVuQw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"We went to this place on Saturday morning for brunch, and it was quite packed.
Kerrisdale doesn't have tons of options for brunch, but this was one of them.
For some reason, as we walked in, servers were gathered at the host stand, and it took a while to get us seats even though many tables were available.
Food orders came quickly, and they were delicious.
However, it was impossible to get our server's attention and took a while to get our water and drinks refilled and the bill.
Maybe they would be better on the weekdays as fewer people come.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMp1wBDmLuiwj-EtopUtsT8xrq0vpReThLt43r8&fid=0x0:0xc1287e6cfbaf4bc5"],"When":"2023-6-15"},{"Name":"James Lee","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKNNi1MwDRcxrUNhqhTb_OBEAXs_3ZOmePDMv1OP1syMUsu1g=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"If I can give 0 on this review I would as I didnt even get to sit down to order anything. Servers busy running away albeit the guest at the front clearly told them she was only picking up the food so they could attend us. Never knew it would take two servers to take turns in order to take a payment. Good job on exploiting tips.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Anmol Ratan Singh","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVpbS1tkljKBfJB4b-0p2H0otsImRDVKU0w3EKQEutGlo-eaoLNuA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"This is my go to place for comfort food and drinks, must try their Thai coconut prawns and strawberry milkshake","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNu2aNv_FQd17JgGqNFAMThXjA9G0_WYvy8HngD&fid=0x0:0xc1287e6cfbaf4bc5"],"When":"2024-12-3"},{"Name":"Dianne Turner","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLBAgLZWug1OhFGaxmTDdh4Xn6nGobIfnhLtWOTsO2_UIYTcA=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Worst service we have ever had at a Whitespot.
Waited 45 minutes for our food - long after others, who came in after us, were served - and actually left the restaurant just after we got our food!
The servers forgot about us - we had to ask several times for the parts of our meals to be brought to the table. No one asked how the food was - no refills were offered on water, tea ( had to ask for milk for my tea - and the tea was cold by the time the milk was brought), no condiments brought to the table even after asking twice,-  had to finally ask for our food to be brought to our table after a 45 minute wait.  Two out of our four orders were partially wrong and we had to ask for the additional items - but had to wait for those so long that our meals were already cold!
This is not the first time we have had bad service there- but it will absolutely be the last!","Images":null,"When":""}]

[{"Name":"Cindy Pau","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVoPTXcD0se4Xivuf7NkSP5gs4tyMdl3dj2UUvcKcUFHAnauC-IMw=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I  recently organized a private dinner at Jess‚Äô Cafe, and I cannot say enough good things about this incredible restaurant. From the planning stages to the actual event, the manager, Don, went above and beyond to ensure everything was perfect. The attention to detail was remarkable‚Äîgood food, excellent wine, and service that was truly exceptional.

The restaurant itself is beautifully decorated, with stunning crystal chandeliers that create a warm and welcoming atmosphere. The ambience was elegant yet cozy, making it the perfect setting for a memorable evening.

All my guests thoroughly enjoyed the dinner, and I couldn‚Äôt have asked for a better experience. Don and his team made the night so special for everyone. If you‚Äôre looking for a place that combines excellent food, great service, and a beautiful atmosphere, I highly recommend Jess‚Äô Cafe.

Thank you to Don and the team for an unforgettable night!!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOSMIrFtJozSqSkSeXH3E_ojyB_nWDXH87P7XrR&fid=0x0:0x84d2a175c35e3d9a"],"When":"2024-12-8"},{"Name":"PristineVIImages Photography","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWGCgLiXlOaLAaKvqMsvgvGbp_5MSFtnUtOpoV6XZkTapQsj6oV=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Breakfast and brunch spot that you simply can't miss. Chef Jay is the mastermind behind this amazing place, and he's not only a talented chef but also a friendly and approachable guy.
The food is out of this world, and I've been to a lot of places, but this one truly stands out. Not only is the food top-notch, but the washroom is the prettiest in Vancouver. It's a must-visit spot for anyone looking for a delicious and memorable meal.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipP38Qk9qH2ctneMgvkwwN9XGwoSWbyJZVK6Wq-F&fid=0x0:0x84d2a175c35e3d9a"],"When":"2024-11-13"},{"Name":"Magdalena Nakahara","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLaY9r4HiAQabJ5jPi3rAbqhu1TCH2jjjoC7_NVC42NpVefVw=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Really cool brunch place. We tried the avocado croffle and cinnamon croffle and both were delicious! It‚Äôs casual enough to eat in with your child but nice enough to feel like you‚Äôre eating at a fancy place. üòÅ
The staff is super friendly and the taste and look of the food is top. We‚Äôll definitely come again to try more menu items.

(They also sell gift cards, which we took advantage of this Christmas. üòâ)","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipORlwbE0Or8vzFm_4AdvFqJtpa_enBXbqrWDZaa&fid=0x0:0x84d2a175c35e3d9a"],"When":"2024-12-20"},{"Name":"Winnie W","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXBoIPjRuUZOsdiO0wVzMCvy81ggQ1VJgwF61I1dnSDn5bs60Yg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"My first time to Jess Cafe, 4 of us ordered food to share, I especially enjoyed the chicken and croffle, chicken was juicy and flavourful. I heard that they opened for dinner before, I really wish that they would serve dinner again so I could try more of their food! It‚Äôs a great place to hang out with friends.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNlTLKUYR7rXn3nZzMvqijBcs_8vDC7GpqmGwSY&fid=0x0:0x84d2a175c35e3d9a"],"When":"2024-11-19"},{"Name":"Snoopy Kitchen","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjU3h-I-trbYva-Tzrs-UNhkQe4Nn1jgsblAcoQ0hPrnUWvugM3Y=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Food is creative Korean fusion.  A bit pricey but taste good.  Vibe is like fine dining but service is not so a bit pricey.  I like beef tartare not like traditional only mix with Korean pear but also on top of rice crispy and carviar.  Too bad that they don‚Äôt serve afternoon tea anymore.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMYVJkuCv8dgP6p1LHxViffDMPPay-Y5qGLwfzc&fid=0x0:0x84d2a175c35e3d9a"],"When":"2024-9-8"},{"Name":"Stella Oh","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWvqyQ2KS_YIN6XYOMkDtQZO2ezjEJLWRODsOzNFIWuIhCYtAL-=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"We made a reservation for the Mother‚Äôs Day special combos. Amazing pork jowl appetizer and beef hot stone bowl rice! Just as hot and tasty as what I had growing up in a Korean household. It was refreshing to see a restaurant incorporating modern European techniques into Korean cuisine.

The service was good but not as good as I hoped for a fine dining restaurant. For the most part, the food came out quickly and the staff were friendly. However, after I said yes to their offer to mix the ingredients in my hot stone bowl, they forgot about coming back and doing it (and she even said she would come back). I noticed that one waitress had a gloomy face the entire time we were there, which gave off an awkward vibe, but I didn‚Äôt let it affect our time there. We had a great meal overall and would consider coming back to Jess‚Äô Restaurant for another special occasion in the future.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMLolxORTvtHYS8hCbxMOePjJ0b1BtMwVEefZ0g&fid=0x0:0x84d2a175c35e3d9a"],"When":"2024-5-21"},{"Name":"Melinda W","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUqFa91nGQX9-WVxFZ-rAUul10GF70bhWZFQZe97ymoPVUZrvFxnA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Surprise! Jess' looks like a high end restaurant but is serving egg bennies and croffles. Most important, their pricing is very affordable.

We tried the smoked salmon benny, shrimp benny and spicy chicken sandwich. All of them taste delicious and came in good portion. $19 for an egg benny with salmon / shrimp in a nicely decorated cafe really worths every penny. No wonder it is always full house as I was told.

Their food offering is quite limited though. Besides egg bennies, croffles and sandwiches, they serve a few other like spaghetti. Well... More variety is not always the best in my opinion. It is better with just a few dishes but with the bear quality, like what Jess' does.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMqU6JSyu20hfBGlr1tZcfFxUdg36pI_ULFYTGL&fid=0x0:0x84d2a175c35e3d9a"],"When":"2024-11-17"},{"Name":"Lorenzo Pasello","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJ6hbnvxnMILdsBmV0t46Ba3AxzeLwqn8uJIRKL2Z6HOa5iig=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"A fantastic lunch experience at an amazing price point
I was walking in the neighbourhood devating where to eat and my eye was drawn to this restaurant. The chique blue tinted interior and interesting choise of chandeliers definetly catch the eye and for once style is not used to simply replace substance but rather to elevate a delicious lunch spot serving Korean fancy lunch fare at a cheap price.
I chose to simply follow the preset 3 course lunch menu (45 dollars) and got 2 excellent dishes and a solid dessert.
The Fried Cauliflower was delicious, well portioned and nicely presented but the true standout was the Albacore and Scallops Sotbab served with Kimchi, Anchovy Paste and a selection of home made sauces. I am by no means a Korean food expert but ive been to a few Korean restaurants before and this was one of the best. The Sweet Soy Sauce especially was delicious, though I wish there was a bit more anchovy paste available.
For dessert I opted for the Yakgwa, which was pretty good, nicely presented and served with some gelato to cut trough the honey which was a really nice touch. On the other hand the coffee was not particularly good and I suggest diners to stick to the iced variety rather than the hot one.
Overall it was a really good meal at a fantastic price in a nice central location which on its own should earn 4 to 5 stars but what really pushed it over the edge was the fantastic work of Yeaji, the host, who was kind, knowledgeable, polite and super efficient while remaining really respectful. Dishes came out fast but she always had time and attention to give a little explanation and guide me trough the menu despite the lunch rush. Never had to wait for drink refills or the bill and had overall a great experience. I hope he goes to big places in her food service carreer. I'll be the first to admit im not the biggest tipper due to financial reasons but i just tipped 11 dollars on a 40 dollar lunch and would do it again in a heartbeat.
Overall a great experience! Check it out if you are in the area and even if you are in Marpole, Kits or UBC it might be worth the detour on a lazy afternoon. They are switching over the the Fall Tasting Menus for dinner service (various options between 40 and 120 dollars from my understanding) and I cant wait to be back","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPgzrxPZdUBI9cWp4xLdl7UkYWoTZvf3i164RvV&fid=0x0:0x84d2a175c35e3d9a"],"When":"2024-9-4"}]

The crust was airy and crisp, flavour oils are a nice addition and the burrata was so good!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPNuDpM09FfMm9z4J-At2XkpOjWxkeN7GtGOEk6&fid=0x0:0x11d8438d85c62ca5"],"When":"2024-11-2"},{"Name":"Rachel Black","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocL-HkYOavdooWAnfkQL2O6cYpA0X1NgB6v0B8cQ-nIvPRvgsg=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Warning: bring your trust fund! This joint charges $18 for a potato salad serving size that's smaller than a toddler's appetite. And when we complained, they shrugged it off with a 'yeah, portions are small here' - code for 'we're fleecing you and don't care'. If you want overpriced, mediocre snacks and a side of disdain, this is your spot!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPxGb8rTuToIM6HxA3ZPj5RMeE2UciFkguOo6yp&fid=0x0:0x11d8438d85c62ca5"],"When":"2024-11-20"},{"Name":"Zhaleh Esmaeili","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXRYncnU_9beu1lSnUnibBbNozK95HCGeB-1D1yMIItLgiixvhG=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We went to Bufala for our first day last year and had the best of times, so we decided to recreate the memory by going there on our anniversary this year. We made the right choice. I love the outside seating and the waiters are always cordial and kind and very attentive. They were extra nice when we told them we are there for our anniversary. This place has the only Pesto Pizza in Vancouver that I like and reminds me of real good pizza back home. They also have great drinks. We ordered the garlic pizza which was both delicious and great to look at. We finished the night with the tiramisu dessert which was just heavenly. We will definitely go there more in the future. Highly recommended.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMuYiYjwER-3H0FtRxqzaLlSiX93ToSw290SQS8&fid=0x0:0x11d8438d85c62ca5"],"When":"2021-8-22"},{"Name":"Gemma P","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjW0oYduMa3EEwAyuXKHwhSSt3CaAXnJElv-JuhT0yxWkxkxd5G1jw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"My favorite place to eat pizza in Kerrisdale.
So, I came here to celebrate my friend‚Äôs Bday. It was happy hour so I ordered a Cocktail in 9$ which is normally 12$. Kale salad was little different than other reviews photo (before it had an egg and bacon on top. But now it‚Äôs gone üòÖ) But still, taste so nice. Fungi Pizza, some said too many arugula but I love it so it doesn‚Äôt bothered me at all. It was fresh and white sauce with mushrooms was perfect matching. Service was over the top. Thank you for a tiramisu üòò Overall, I loved it! I will definitely visit again and again ~","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPm-xAPCb9U9YS74mfNYfsO7qBw2M1Hn2bAuaUX&fid=0x0:0x11d8438d85c62ca5"],"When":"2022-7-15"},{"Name":"Sasha K","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIq1oC1G6LFLmsQ_k8bhT6FX_zK88STGyLXgIiOK8XUXeVv_X0=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Great lunch spot! Authentic wood fired pizzas that are served with a trio of dipping oils (my favourite part about dining at Bufala!) The restaurant isn‚Äôt cheap but is on par with what‚Äôs around! I really like the kale Caesar salad and usually get the artichoke and olive pizza! They also have great happy hour and daily specials!","Images":null,"When":""}]

[{"Name":"Sue H.","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIvBtkDy7sChQrgUSbaQbtqqCrAf2D0SisH1FaTP8ES9Tr74g=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"I had ordered from this restaurant many times for take out order, but this time was the worst. I ordered the chicken nuggets this time to try, but once I open the small box, the chicken nuggets portion was so little. It's only half size in a box for $12.95. Completely speechless for this small portion  and that cost. With such portion I could have got from somewhere else for cheaper price too. I feel very disappointed and deceived as a customer","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNF8798hvkU_zahAWU4XB4qeChniusFrQ3HXbEh&fid=0x0:0x6db46bf4030a7238"],"When":"2024-8-16"},{"Name":"Deb M","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXPrATP9E08bOlyd-Dd5lrVgbexx--OhGR-WZHHVn-fl3mHFca1NQ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"Met my daughter for a quick late lunch, neither of us had eaten here before. Staff is friendly, atmosphere is quaint, but the food - worse spicy hot pot soup I have ever had. I have travelled extensively and can appreciate good flavouring - this was bland, zero seasoning, and lacked spice. Sadly I will not return or recommend $60 for two bowls of hot water with a few noodles and spring rolls. Oh well perhaps it was an off day but too pricey to give another try.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"kandis wong","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLqRhBa2Up1c5kTR3_4Xyp4X-usl87anlLy3zvB0Lv9fePorg=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"A very friendly restaurant from the front to the kitchen, I have been going there for almost a year. I feel like going home with super good food without regret of keep going for my first choice in Kerrisdale.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNiu2Z3xPLu3hqJsoG2qWNMLmD7fKj4SlMpJJXq&fid=0x0:0x6db46bf4030a7238"],"When":"2023-12-17"},{"Name":"Luke Weng","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXn1tdfwXfRnZVszKV8bZBNwooyRqfHv0VT8T0EAQWyUrqTrrO6aQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba7-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"When I first came across this restaurant I thought many things. "This looks like a cafe," I thought. "It must be a good place for coffee and Bubble tea".

The reviews said that some Taiwanese lady (possibly the owner?) was very nice and was super accommodating.

When I actually came in to eat, I was completely out off guard. This place was in fact indeed a Taiwanese restaurant! An actual authentic and traditional one too!!

And the lady that the reviews spoke of actually waited our table. She really was nice and took the time to explain the menu. When we needed extra utensils she grabbed them without hesitation.

The only thing I didn't like was how small and pricey of the menu. Even the appetizers menu was more expensive than some restaurants I've been to. The cheapest item was $9!! That's almost 10 bucks for a few pieces of vegetable.

Asides the price and quantity, everything else seemed pretty good.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMQzJAsuVV-l7aTrYfV3korh6j_L420aima1o_l&fid=0x0:0x6db46bf4030a7238"],"When":"2019-12-4"},{"Name":"s.m. kindersley","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjV47VumTpOhpzvxhFz-c_hGo06rqHrL9wuzc1BLqx--ayr95g_E=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"my friend and i came in with dietary restrictions, one vegetarian and one gluten intolerant.  with help from the friendly staff we had a delicious meal.  crunchy tasty green beans and Hai lan, back eggplant, stir fried tofu, vermicelli with veggies. pleasant light background music was playing,  the servers were attentive with tea and water and condiments. i would be happy to go back with family and friends.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOo-lWy0Bmxb74cQMZAywBc3tjORhcT_kwWf8VT&fid=0x0:0x6db46bf4030a7238"],"When":"2024-5-7"},{"Name":"Kulisara","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXgRkeyi8SVcJb38h_m9cRjdJp-L43vcMpmhQcIExnujS5plEU=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"My top 5 restaurant around Kerrisdale. Flying squid tentacles and lemon chicken are the best!!! They also toddler friendly. Very thoughtful they gave me cute utensils for my toddler. Customize menu to fit my toddler needs. This shop is amazing!!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"C K","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKzpv-PyqqKemfUW68qED6-0vJQn8fAFvFcrRLPf7-q5kdHow=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I had a great experience here. Amazing service and good foods. My Taiwanese friend recommended. Not sure why such a low review. I will try again then see if I change the mind.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipP05aIn7uvcfl3xOYLdRbPFZBYhDl263UFkhn94&fid=0x0:0x6db46bf4030a7238"],"When":"2023-8-29"},{"Name":"bill l","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUADAxax50DlUz5DZ920mDMlqZoQdcFwmLe637VZbXiqzWiDOMw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"We were disappointed with the portions here. Definitely not good value for your money.

Ordered a chicken with black bean sauce and vegetarian tofu which cost me $10.95 and $12.45 respectively. I'd be fine paying that if they were regular sized plates -- but these were the size of appetizers! See the attached photos. I placed a bowl beside the chicken dish for scale. And it didn't even come with rice.

We also ordered a Fish & Vegetable Noodle. That was a normal portion and cost $11.95 so that's better but still on the high side in my opinion but that's probably understandable being located in Kerrisdale.  In the end we paid over $40 (incl tax and tip) for lunch and we were still hungry.

The service was good. The food tasted ok though the tofu dish was a bit too salty. *If* I were to come back (but I don't intend to) I would stick to the noodle soup menu items. It has better value compared to the dishes.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMaHzhs-AvMgTsKsyAuzTt77zq7DsA9TYh_ggcZ&fid=0x0:0x6db46bf4030a7238"],"When":"2018-8-27"}]

[{"Name":"Lizzie S","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX5qIG1VmBASZQRSYXsIMifm6rtLhZA6xcKTGDs0bvXyJT2pXkmsA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"My Tteogbokki came with cold fried items and a little bit dry. The steamed egg was great, hot and soft only a little bit overpriced for 11.99. The half and half fried chicken was only acceptable, chicken not juicy and hot but sauce was good. The whole services were very slow and we didn't get banchan because didn't order main dishes even if we two people ordered around 70 CAD food. Just a disappointed experience, I'll drive to Burnaby or Coquitlam to have Korean food.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMsPzUSEp_IhruWdlsCOWP5X-uOXffPNgtl3SLd&fid=0x0:0xb5fcca1c039dcc4f"],"When":"2024-12-15"},{"Name":"Andrew Chin","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLjJ5B2L5Dt4E8YWZkDm0kUr4V6HGv2CX6lHWiA5TE8KD_TXQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"First time there based on reviews and it wasn't wrong. From the moment you stepped in and left the restaurant, service and attentiveness from the staff were friendly, welcoming and top-notch.  Any company out there should take notes on how to make your customers feel welcomed by learning from these guys.
The food was fresh, tasty, prepared professionally and unforgettable in a good way. We ordered the Kimchi tofu soup (spicy but addictive), Bossam (so good and fun to eat) and added the
spicy fried chicken and kimch fried rice as a take out.  All in all, we were very happy with our meal.
I would certainly return back again... This is probably one of Vancouver's hidden neighbourhood gems.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMrYYnnLCxLvxl3TUVisZqQ_Y0Jv9rArkaUrnDU&fid=0x0:0xb5fcca1c039dcc4f"],"When":"2024-9-23"},{"Name":"Tina Pim","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJcFYQ2Z7LuFLahFP7CVS-FUtLGpOifZvQYu_Ed3r3ElgLyLA=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"This hidden gem in the heart of Kerrisdale stands as the pinnacle of Korean cuisine in town. The warmth and friendliness of the staff enhance the intimate, spotless setting, which hums with the lively energy of satisfied diners‚Äîmany of whom are Korean, underscoring the authenticity of the experience. Given the restaurant‚Äôs popularity, reservations are a must, as the wait can extend up to 45 minutes. However, patience is richly rewarded. Each meal typically includes a comforting bowl of Miso soup, steamed rice, and an assortment of traditional Korean dipping sauces.

As a frequent visitor, I can confidently say that their Bulgogi is unrivaled, and their variety of fried chicken is nothing short of perfection. This evening, we ventured into new territory with their Bone Broth, which was accompanied by crispy rice crackers and tender gyoza dumplings‚Äîan absolute triumph. The potato croquettes, with their delicate, golden crust and perfectly fluffy interior, were bursting with flavor. And let us not forget the corn cheese, a decadent delight that never fails to impress.  This place is a must visit always.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNHKDM1PLbDfRmzBS136TmK-MpnPt1QGTok5syQ&fid=0x0:0xb5fcca1c039dcc4f"],"When":"2024-9-3"},{"Name":"minnie li","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKRoQOlIxvrw__7xun_s22_XplGfNg8u2NALefXOOF5MWkjHg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"The food was fantastic. However, there‚Äôs a big issue with the service. They only had two servers working during the weekend rush, and it really showed. The place was packed, and with so few staff, it was hard to get water refilled, and the wait for food felt way too long.

I get that it was busy, but I really think they need to hire more servers, especially on weekends. It‚Äôs a shame because the food was so good, but the long wait times and lack of service were frustrating. If you‚Äôre going on the weekend, be prepared to wait, but the food is definitely worth it if you‚Äôre patient.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMAj-xMZFPl1t1mY-Rush0sPQ7aCYx8NtCJoih3&fid=0x0:0xb5fcca1c039dcc4f"],"When":"2024-9-10"},{"Name":"Jordan Ho","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjW11-xeEA0Ih57ocfphXt0C50QwI614ll6t2qknklEqHoDt3aVy=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Good quality Korean food in Kerrisdale. Kimbap was good but maybe slightly dry; still solid quality though. [{"Name":"Kelsey Jay","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWuNS-SGBHi_pUA46Wj3qi4MNXNZ6mjGjwWV5sTSKtUK1CEq3QH=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"Thai fried rice with chicken was good. Hot spice level was accurate. Also had the pad sew with beef which was hot spice level, was pretty good. Green curry with chicken was great. They were missing the spring roll in the Thai fried rice combo though :( was looking forward to trying that as everyone loves it as per reviews","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOlRoiu3IpKNSTSQcJ69luANC9rsmTZvXPyQOEH&fid=0x0:0xe2a9207bf5e23816"],"When":"2024-8-19"},{"Name":"Jim ST","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXUiuSF5HfAepfnO5grGc3WGFcI3PLjOFi0BLNhgwfeHeG6qpEo=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"oh god this is awful‚Ä¶ the place looks and smells like an 100 year old abandoned house. Dark and damp, filled with a musty smell. The tables, chairs, and floors are all old and dirty. And not surprisingly, food is awful, rock hard no flavor beef. üò£ only good thing about this place is that the staffs are friendly.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOuOa3D2l2H4mmE6phj2irOT-tpiCJlgGQ0NUYD&fid=0x0:0xe2a9207bf5e23816"],"When":"2024-7-30"},{"Name":"Evelyn W","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWKN7puiWTfhN7citaJYEm02_jDInbGSRCV0vjW-pu2Y5eOb6CgTw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"HIDDEN GEM in Vancouverüëç

I found this place on delivery apps and decided to give it a try. My orders: 1 Green Curry Lunch Combo 2 Pad Thai.  The lunch combo comes with a green salad and a spring roll. I absolutely love their spring rolls. Thin skin and rice vermicelli fillings. The green curry my favouriteüòç. Rich coconut cream, very milky and just a hint of the spice. Chicken strips and veggies are nicely cooked and soaked in the sauce. Goes so well with üçö rice, I finished all of them easilyüòÅ Pad Thai tastes also good! They are sweeter than I expected, I can tell there are some tomato flavour in it. But I would not recommend to order beef in it, their beef is a bit dry. Overall, full-filling lunch with cheap priceüëå

üìçKhao Thai by Legato Cafe
W 41st Ave, Vancouver","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMazsy-Q5noyMf2KOpG16FjLc_Vgx0Kv6xOTQ5D&fid=0x0:0xe2a9207bf5e23816"],"When":"2021-9-2"},{"Name":"Elton Chung","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjU_SVkVqkNe3SvSFwaZ1xrBYHObNVkTiTTXXYykf58guqGIk3qy=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Recently I have been to Legato Cafe for brekkie and lunch several times. From outside I thought it was just a cafe serving coffee, tea and cafe foods. In fact they serve Thai cuisine for their lunch menu and the quality really impressed me.

The customers in the cafe are generally the people who have been living in Kerrisdale for decades. Many of them are now over 75 years old and they are the loyal customers who visit the cafe every morning. As a new face to the people, I was warmly welcomed. The customers know each other like family members. The vibes made me feel like home there. In particular they don't play any background music - I really like it!

Regarding the foods, the super breakfast and a cup of latte are definitely the good choices for a chilly morning. In my last visit at lunch I ordered their Yellow Curry Chicken with rice. The curry was very tasty and I love it from my first bite. The taste is authentic and I must say it is better than authentic. I should have a larger portion of rice as the curry sauce went well with the jasmine rice.

This is a cafe full of nice people with stories and good foods where you can slow down and enjoy the moment.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMFv8oH_FTrdyS4SQHN8qhNb14WHlcb7eniXYI&fid=0x0:0xe2a9207bf5e23816"],"When":"2022-12-12"},{"Name":"kawaii hatchiko","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWLtom4JJghW2UnkOsI7GKr-J96yxZfSX4SBdkTaAQaNBfKVBVT=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"Ordered here for the first time. The pad Thai was super dry and lacked flavour. The sauce to noodles ratio was way off. The soup was terrible. I do not recommend the soup at all. The curry was good. But I‚Äôm not sure if I would reorder.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOFZ7y225aN7c1kxCmqxMSsnz4g4klrU8cFUSWq&fid=0x0:0xe2a9207bf5e23816"],"When":"2023-4-9"},{"Name":"Penny Rusty Sophie","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUkGfXMIDqwS_yD1axTk6tkHoLsnybE2ErvKrHMoMIElMJWekI_=s120-c-rp-mo-ba7-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"We don‚Äôt make it out to Kerrisdale much so, whenever we‚Äôre in the neighbourhood, it‚Äôs always a chore to figure out where to eat. I noticed that there was a Thai place nearby and made a mental note to try this place out. When I finally got here, I was a bit confused because the place looked like a coffee shop (not a Thai restaurant).

As it turns out, however, they do have a full Thai menu inside the shop and we wound up ordering the Sampler Platter ($15.99) as well as Green Curry Chicken ($13.99) and Pad Thai ($12.99). This appetizer platter was really good and had all of the items that we enjoy‚Ä¶ spring rolls, chicken satay, fish cakes, shrimp cakes, and deep-fried prawns.

The green curry chicken is exactly what you‚Äôd expect from a full Thai restaurant and had tender eggplant, bamboo shoots, red and green peppers, and Thai basil leaves. As expected, the curry sauce goes very well with a bowl of white rice.

They use tamarind sauce in their pad thai (instead of ketchup) and this version turned out pretty good.

Overall, I was pleasantly surprised at the quality of the food in this little coffee shop. Service, while adequate, was a little bit more in line with what you‚Äôd expect at a coffee shop than at a sit-down restaurant (we had to seat ourselves and also flag them down to order and get take-out containers and then pay up front at the cashier). Still, I wouldn‚Äôt hesitate coming here for Thai food if I was in the area.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOciZuMvp6lMWxtRvXN968xbSxy1vDrbgdDpVn-&fid=0x0:0xe2a9207bf5e23816"],"When":"2021-4-25"},{"Name":"Ads","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVwDyuvQtXP_VygmU1rNXhUJ0mc48E4h1QtDkdEfrlXmuS-mYhL=s120-c-rp-mo-ba8-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"This joint is a cool, quirky and alternative spin on a dining experience!
I have to admit, I was a bit skeptical when ordering a Pad See Ew ‡∏ú‡∏±‡∏î‡∏ã‡∏µ‡∏≠‡∏¥‡πä‡∏ß and I could smell a grilled cheese being made at the same time. However, the grub was dope, real tasty with great seasoning and fantastic portion sizes including good helpings of tofu with no greasy or oily texture. This place tastes like good home-style Thai cooking and made me think of my awesome days back in Thailand. The kitchen is shared but completely separate, and they are able to offer a classic authentic Thai menu with awesome veggie selections as well as a quirky and upbeat cafe offering some pastries and cakes.
The dish also came with a small salad and one of the best deep-fried veggie spring rolls I have had in a while, an absolute gem and steal of a cheap tasty lunch. Lunch menu is from 11am-15:00pm and has a great selection of different thai cuisines.
Staff are super friendly, welcoming and accommodating.
Khob khun ka ‡∏Ç‡∏≠‡∏ö‡∏Ñ‡∏∏‡∏ì‡∏Ñ‡πà‡∏∞ !!
Support local business!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNhJQlIF7K1u_Hc-pqJJRaHt5mLTgvEjWMYamTs&fid=0x0:0xe2a9207bf5e23816"],"When":"2022-3-7"},{"Name":"Cheling Ling","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocI8tiyEVZVahH_y3WnzM4UtxHhZcWbpwbKfQUDWZZCQCiQxUA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"Ordered a so call chicken curry, over watery, only spicy but no curry taste, n I see no sight of chicken pieces. This should rename as potato curry.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNwMAfQViV0MiEjs4IIz3iDEoRJokpSOq1vwMYt&fid=0x0:0xe2a9207bf5e23816"],"When":"2024-6-5"}]

The service is always fast and polite, and I‚Äôve taken family members and friends here multiple times. The menu has something on it for everyone (including my friends who aren‚Äôt that into raw fish) and includes Japanese and Korean food. I‚Äôm a big fan of their set meals as they come with a variety of different dishes at an affordable price point, and I usually end up taking leftovers home. Definitely one of my easy button, staple restaurants in Vancouver.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNH9wbEhLGH5Kalrf2rslo9N4ZDypaWjxrCmE8i&fid=0x0:0xf3fc28a63e684202"],"When":"2024-10-22"},{"Name":"Nazli Ko√ß","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWUvsMH1bCXbFh2_25G52wtgIHogl0umoIdCZUV89dI-9MOztJa=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Ordered the Go Go Crunchy Roll, Caterpillar Roll, Real California Roll, Pizza Sushi Bite Roll, Rocky Mountain Roll, and Beef Yaki Soba. All were amazing. LOVE the tea. Super friendly staff and very clean atmosphere. Would come again for sure!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNYxgF-elwNimZBwkoaF6VdxK50EwWl5Ff2fNhS&fid=0x0:0xf3fc28a63e684202"],"When":"2024-5-25"},{"Name":"AJ R","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLo4tIvUrcwNXdNPm8MhPpZgzsQXb-_lGpW8MEceFXJ5buZ1dI=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Great sushi! Nice flavours and consistency. Chicken Karaage was pretty good as well, the dipping sauce was really good. The menu was very large, lots to choose from! Very clean establishment and friendly and attentive staff.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMjF-RQkp9LECHFkxtuFOAcFE7xnLZVW7emJmBg&fid=0x0:0xf3fc28a63e684202"],"When":"2024-8-6"},{"Name":"Harv Shen","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWOiS8VEPaWvjFgDKfbUg1C3dUpS2ohaV4E4FgRxRh65KAfi5ox=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"You can expect decent sushi and Korean food here. Cost is reasonable.  We ordered dinner box, octopus ball, spider roll, chicken karaage. Love it!
Been here 8 times already, never disappointed","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipO29OfqtWkCKBlqNxarMZ_4AqBLUYQrLS_x_wpa&fid=0x0:0xf3fc28a63e684202"],"When":"2024-3-17"},{"Name":"Jennifer","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKl00HXRgRORegvG_1u7KRKapKpF5-ZBiEaGLAzwBybNJk80A=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"This is our go-to sushi place in Vancouver. Food is tasty, the service is fast and efficient and the prices are reasonable.

We ordered a number of dishes including Sakura and Voltex special rolls, wild salmon, tuna, dynamite rolls. We also tried the assorted tempura and the beef yaki soba noodles. All very delicious!

Just one thing to keep in mind is that they do not take reservations however, we didn‚Äôt have any issues on a Tuesday evening.
I would recommend trying this restaurant.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOYKT2FcHlHt8TdJ-42nW4wruhMxgoZPi52cwHo&fid=0x0:0xf3fc28a63e684202"],"When":"2024-1-10"},{"Name":"JSSC","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocI7izrr8xG2f0SKMaI1NA24UJJRcVZj7GR7YXkHRJE0jVnKVw=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Food is always top class. Some of the best sushi I've ever had. Chirashi don has plenty of fish and tastes so fresh. Korean style chirashi don is also great and has just the right level of spiciness. Oshi will melt in your mouth! Good prices & fast efficient service","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPadovprMPi2b9dJTnzs1ge0yvXlxLjVadtCGEU&fid=0x0:0xf3fc28a63e684202"],"When":"2022-8-26"},{"Name":"P G","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX0fCU2Qc0a_c6EyAnrC9oWHMXOLKbAIpYaZPyN9xTdV9lbUoGm=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Korean-Japanese spot that‚Äôs usually busy and is better to eat in than take out from. Good for those not looking for especially authentic Japanese, and an easy option in the neighborhood","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOQCXa5sUgH2ILCVHPm1mUo_G_FfiGTuhX7Qiem&fid=0x0:0xf3fc28a63e684202"],"When":"2024-7-19"},{"Name":"Samantha Bacchus McLeod","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVYiRIvy_TuMch5JQY-yF_gsT_IZst0-J--PuSw8Il6loRANjyf=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I was very happy with my visit to Asa, the classic rolls were so delicious. Oh my gosh, the rice is perfect, slightly tangy, loose and sticky, which means it is perfectly cooked. The seafood were fresh and delicious,  the vegetables crisp.

I loved the salmon sashimi,  love it. It is BC farm raised salmon, so of course it is fresh, clean, melts like butter in each firm bite. I will always choose farmed food over wild, especially salmon, because it is a highly regulated industry we get the best of the best.

The new age deep fried rolls with cream cheese were so decadent that I would consider them a treat - if you are young enough to burn it all off:-) then go order them all because they are scrumptious.

The service was on point; pleasant,  helpful,  thoughtful, and an overall  pleasure for us, the guests.

The Sake warmed our tummies on a cold rainy night. Gorgeous.

The price was honest. Surprisingly affordable in these times.

The place is small and cosy, yet seems spacious once seated.

I am a definite return patron!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNQ3-Jz1Wxk3Dpaw0b-vTUbM3jnIojuOqG5jB-W&fid=0x0:0xf3fc28a63e684202"],"When":"2023-4-10"}]
