[{"Name":"Sandra Chan","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUS3d7aZA4lMhkB4lrjOTrDjB_p6PvngmeWQeM0VFHPfzqli2Uc=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"It was my first time here and I enjoyed the food. The Ebi Mayo was particularly delicious. My mazesoba or mixed noodles were very decent even though I prefer noodles in broth more. There were other more interesting items that I will return to try. This place is easily accessible. There‚Äôs free parking on East and West Boulevard as well as on side streets.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMDrwTiO2PqouDtQFtP_6cYtSXXr_Za0Qkvx2wR&fid=0x0:0x3abc60392c570033"],"When":"2024-11-14"},{"Name":"JOE CHEUNG","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocITcUa8udaZfgZECEKe5qn4g0G5mpOKc-aHAY-YGVBDA4qWLA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"Well
It‚Äôs a bit disappointed this time
To be fair, we don‚Äôt order their main dishes which is the Mazesoba
I ordered a Curry Pork Cutlet, some tofu, a bowl of std ramen.
Honestly the ramen is ok average
The curry is nowhere near.
Most disappointing is the rice. It‚Äôs hard and non Japanese grade rice. It‚Äôs like those u bought from supermarket and put it in microwave like convenient pack rice
The cutlet is very below average, hard and not juicy at all
Ramen, soup is ok, noodle is good, ingredients is fair. Pork slice is average.
Can‚Äôt compare with other nearby.

I should order their special and mazesoba to give a full review

Staff is nice
Atmosphere is cozy modern and clean.

End","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMSRyBt3ocBdmzW1E7wOYApZQYFkeR54uk3NUMS&fid=0x0:0x3abc60392c570033"],"When":"2024-9-9"},{"Name":"Kwong Tang","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVRNhrcdIOQyhkpCbdjoUSwC0OqkPEp5C09o-KZX9pyAsIQioX9=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"üçú Tasty Tokyo Vibes at Kokoro Tokyo Mazesoba - Kerrisdale! üç•

üåû Stopped by for a quick meal at Kokoro Tokyo Mazesoba and was delighted by the rich flavors! I ordered the Original Ramen with Tamago and a side of Gyoza, and both dishes hit the spot. The broth was savory and comforting, a perfect treat on a chilly day.

üç≤ This location offers more than just traditional ramen; they‚Äôre known for their mazesoba‚Äîbrothless ramen that‚Äôs packed with umami. While I didn't try it this time, it‚Äôs definitely on my list for my next visit. The restaurant's ambiance is cozy, with a modern Japanese feel that makes it a relaxing place to enjoy a meal.

ü•ü The staff were friendly and welcoming, providing excellent service and making me feel right at home. Whether you‚Äôre a ramen enthusiast or new to Japanese noodles, Kokoro Tokyo Mazesoba is a must-try in Kerrisdale!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipP2pebEC-K4cFHZa4NmO50jcLlHUQMlkpcGfdnI&fid=0x0:0x3abc60392c570033"],"When":"2024-10-11"},{"Name":"Greg Tam","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIztK7ST5k5VuzWkkg5vJ2qJTDlhYdWJW6idgaJUdMSylPPQdBg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"This bowl of Japanese noodles is not udon, nor soba, nor ramen. It is mazesoba and it means mixed noodles! Think of it as a brothless ramen. And Kokoro Tokyo Mazesoba, which comes straight from Tokyo, does it best. Containing a wide array of delicious umami toppings and the chewiest noodles, you'll want to scrape up every last bite of this dish. This is one of my favourite places to go to when I visit Vancouver.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipP4jrfSdbSQKxZniNx8_4QkTyYWUiSJTNpaNLgg&fid=0x0:0x3abc60392c570033"],"When":"2024-8-16"},{"Name":"Azuki","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXDO580thEC_aOqQ6Ey2F5p_tJwlNUQNurFMEvymExhrUJyiE5I=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"As our favorite Mazesoba restaurant, it'll be our "go-to" if we're around a neighborhood that has one, and this one is in Kerrisdale!

Everything is as consistently superb through every Kokoro Tokyo Mazesoba visit at any location - quality control is amazing.

The only downside of this particular location is its size. The restaurant can sit ~ 25 and there's only 1 (maybe 2) big table that can fit 5+ so if you have a family of 5+, there's usually a wait and it's first come first serve.

Tip: Niku Mazesoba has the most toppings (most meat!) at $16.50, which is cheaper than those with fewer toppings.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipO45hmAo3Oafs4Xd8B7vNbThx-TFE26T8U6boGV&fid=0x0:0x3abc60392c570033"],"When":"2023-11-18"},{"Name":"Kelly Wu","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUwXTwWPi0f0C76m9b7ohgdsL3CpuHkuvPE28inqJasz4aJoh9x=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Delicious food! I‚Äôve never had Mazesoba so this was an interesting experience. The egg was delicious and I love that they give you extra rice at the end to finish your sauce.

A really filling meal for lunch and probably perfect for dinner! Also like the meal combos they have as well, it makes it feel like a more well rounded meal.

The milk tea was too sweet for me (not adjustable, which makes sense), I would probably not get it again but was entranced by the packaging.

The cheesecake dessert was super cute and mild in flavour, which I enjoyed. It also had an Oreo cookie crumble at the bottom that added texture to the dessert.

Service was really good at the beginning but once it got busy it was hard to get the servers attention. However they were very polite and friendly and did come to check often in the beginning.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNv77Ag9vQqdIjvxOsQk1TONzXkNG4cUJVTEW_W&fid=0x0:0x3abc60392c570033"],"When":"2022-10-30"},{"Name":"8T8","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLaHAe29LTwj-kDB4Rxp2LPyCtNn-xUw5U4xwT2905ny-JNkA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Mazesoba, where have you been all my life?   üòÜ.   This is an edit to original review of the ramen,.which I gave a good review.  In my last visit, I noticed everyone eating mazesoba, but I had already re-ordered the usual original ramen.  So I came back the next evening and tried the Tokyo Mazesoba.  Omg, each bite is incredibly flavorful, and the texture of the noodles is making my mouth water as I write this review.  When your taste buds are overwhelmed, simply add the vinegar they serve on the table. , that or take a sip of water to cleanse your palette and you are good to go again.  What a delicious dish!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOYzRdBYC4cYlWH1Lb6atGPPp9qolx0dH0etO-k&fid=0x0:0x3abc60392c570033"],"When":"2023-10-7"},{"Name":"Kram S","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocK9ON9D1tWKSKWDjtVVsOMXBA3V721YkX50l2liWOTv3G9ZMg=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"My daughter placed an order for 5 spicy Mazesoba, chicken Karage, chowsu ball and dumplings, came to pick it up and there was only 1 mazesoba. No sorry or anything, Akane  just walk away after she fix the mistakes.

I wasn‚Äôt even mad or annoyed, mistake happens but at least acknowledge your mistake. I even left a $15 tip on a $127 bill.

Update:

I got back in the office and guess what? No napkins and no chopsticks! I have to order other food close by work so we could get chopsticks. I called the restaurant and spoke to Akane, I told her that it‚Äôs impossible to make too many mistakes with the same customer, specially the restaurant we‚Äôre just opened and only a few customers were inside.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipO8_ovNejOL8umM4NWgPcUFRqttG3I0u4bxdJ8y&fid=0x0:0x3abc60392c570033"],"When":"2024-8-30"}]

Fresh ingredients, not cheap with the cheese (like other places), perfect crust, delicious dip (1 free with pizza) & the staff are super nice.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Mary","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXWhbvwqlNCHopopIqo3mQOHyUhwt04UYqn3mFVwemMJY4ztyP4xA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Beautifully made pizzas! The crust is soft with a satisfying chew, which we really loved. The specialty pizzas we ordered had a nice balance of flavours. My kids liked it too. You won't ever want to go back to eating boring chain restaurant pizza!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMLm7kaXldZnny3JA1M8UdQKHcZvn9NYNMBmWma&fid=0x0:0x453f42919c87558f"],"When":"2020-10-2"},{"Name":"Joseph A.","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLWEo09Sk0DXz9nVdamenK8v8Kzy-wdu1RDGIlZgAdYqC9sBA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"I ordered the Sicilian pizza I think? Cappicola, Spicy sausage and a few other meats on it and the garlic cheese bread. Dough was good. NY style. A bit thicker than a Napoleon style and chewier.  The toppings were not very even. One piece had a lot of sausage and one had non. Not the end of the world. The garlic cheese bread was good, but it was severely lacking garlic. I would call it more if a cheese bread. I did NOT get any garlic flavour or taste whatsoever. Was very good, but maybe just call it cheese bread.

Overall I would give them 3.5/5. Not a 4 not a 3.
Value- 5/5

I don‚Äôt know if I would order again, but I‚Äôm also very picky about my pizza! Although for $20 it‚Äôs significantly cheaper than say pizza garden.

With that being said, I think for the price I would recommend this place.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNePDOgZ1ZQ_uSzqn3U5AV-qBNapRZyDIZldSxW&fid=0x0:0x453f42919c87558f"],"When":"2022-8-7"}]

[{"Name":"Rosa MD","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJdQP4sczaFc0tUIRWY3-9n-Ka30Hep9X0NHrOJ8caM7ajUywM=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Ordered the spanish latte, and it was good. I still think it's overpriced. Service was good, and coffee came out promptly.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPxXbdZgSQH2R9ieWkSHiZ4QhRiAdViJWLAfltK&fid=0x0:0x6907a11959b0b8ea"],"When":"2024-12-25"},{"Name":"Tammy Y","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWn0N2I5STxk6Dw-kQhoKTxOlHlPrvcouHiB9OgzjAG84pt3M0D_Q=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"TL;dr: expensive drinks & sweets, ok place to study. Would give another visit but not for studying.

‚òïÔ∏è Food Quality: 5/5
I got an oat latte and it was pretty good. Strong coffee flavour for those who don‚Äôt drink much coffee. I also got an almond crossaint which was a whopping 6$. It was good but not worth the price.

üìöAmbience: 4/5
It‚Äôs a bit loud but expected for coffee shops. It was also really crowded when I went. There was no where to plug in my charger unless you sit on the booths next to the wall. The tables are a bit too low to do note taking but at a perfect height for typing on a laptop.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNjF_7Y_QpdNB8tl7iYkGxR-exprYdpij4WjUQR&fid=0x0:0x6907a11959b0b8ea"],"When":"2024-9-25"},{"Name":"Lisa","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWcvrwRrMlU3mo5HAPYEpsQgZoTaiuiBo-vP4V2zXl0-qYclXI=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"I've been to this location over the years and loved it. However,  my last experience was far from pleasant. From the moment I walked in, my presence was being monitored and clocked, as the team, led by the manager in charge, prominently enforced their 60-minute stay limit right to the dot. I absolutely understand this is their policy but the way they went about it felt targeted as the table beside (who lined up to order before me) was not even approached. It felt personal and discriminatory, leaving me feeling unwelcome and singled out.

The coffee was good (as always), but the customer service overshadowed the quality. Policies are important, but so is treating customers with respect and fairness.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Philip Raymond Lim","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjV5EIBAgpBLsauhPMdjXym7mJ4fA8mtryDtWQIJCZfJxYXxupU8=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Caf√© Artigiano in Kerrisdale is a nice spot compared to other cafes in terms of lighting and ambiance.

The coffee is good, consistent with what you'd expect from their other locations.

As for the pastries, cookies, sandwiches, and other food, I'd give them a 3 out of 5‚Äîthey fill me up when I‚Äôm hungry and they‚Äôre okay to pair with coffee, but nothing stands out in terms of how special they are.

That said, I still come here from time to time for the convenience, and I appreciate that it‚Äôs clean, seats are ok, which is great since I‚Äôm often in the Kerrisdale area. So I always come here again and again.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNjcHicBw_TWBCNLBztqus5mkx8YgQUuBbMfWEE&fid=0x0:0x6907a11959b0b8ea"],"When":"2024-9-13"},{"Name":"Keira","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjV9Mym_WLLod0GsobtEG7Be0_t0q704qLZpId_34rYp9CRn4m_H=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"This place has a good ambiance but the workers up charged me for my drink by a whole dollar. My friend also was given the wrong drink. Secondly they didn‚Äôt tell us before paying for our beverage or coming in that there is a maximum 1 hour stay limit which is very inconvenient as a student going with the intention to study. My friend and I had great hopes but were very disappointed from the quality of our drinks and service. We will not be coming again which is a shame because otherwise seems like a great study spot.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Pradyumna Gujjar","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXVHYwZPoeWTWb_r-Pj3URXZmwvjMuE8IJLkPSR4xqAVv86CR0HjQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"The cafe itself is beautiful and host Apple
Seating space. Staff are friendly and attend to customers with a smile. I found the hot chocolate very plain and watery. Was defiantly a let down. The churros were soft and didn‚Äôt have above to it. I would give this cafe a try again and would revisit the review if I ave a different experience","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNw3_QtTQFOpfifphm2NVXGxUeoqml_U8Me2rpX&fid=0x0:0x6907a11959b0b8ea"],"When":"2024-2-5"},{"Name":"Azuki","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXDO580thEC_aOqQ6Ey2F5p_tJwlNUQNurFMEvymExhrUJyiE5I=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"#hotchocolatefest
Sweet, Elegant & Relaxing!

Different vibe than Honolulu Coffee just down the street. Very elegant, spacious, business casual for the older crowd.

Both hot chocolates were a tad on the sweet-er side to my liking. The extra gem of adding a cookie/churro was a bonus in value and presentation wise ...but the quality could have been fresher.

The Ham & Cheese Wrap was the spotlight!!! As you bite down on the crispness and flakiness of the wrap into the warm, soft, juiciest of the ham & egg.  It was the highlight!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPUFwVDlAZGIF1Pm8pOXScfa6jxbWXuO68R29pS&fid=0x0:0x6907a11959b0b8ea"],"When":"2024-1-21"},{"Name":"Cassandra Wong","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIEuiSYCANIXn_gPt7YBivEPd5wIj4Rpp--f0L6NarEUVHjFA=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"First time here, the atmosphere is good and I ordered a coffee but since they are closing in 30 mins, they gave me a take away cup of coffee tho I mentioned that it‚Äôs for here‚Ä¶ umm‚Ä¶ sorry, my 20 mins break destroyed a bit‚Ä¶","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNaVT9DTYQfoiVmWgeZgYrwxpf0xBdhTcT_ORPQ&fid=0x0:0x6907a11959b0b8ea"],"When":"2024-10-19"}]

user_reviews: [{"Name":"ISHAN CHHIBBER","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUuO4E4d5VUcgqamASgUx8ttxCgiKU7m_HIsQZzCuUOWZ31N_g=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I had a great experience at the KFC Broadway location in Vancouver! It's rare to find such great service, and Anmol truly made the experience memorable. Highly recommend this location for both the tasty food and outstanding customer care! Will visit soon.. .. ..","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Shikhar Dhall","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLaSoMPYI8XqOFbPOu0-Xa1k2oAmPvQDvA5KzBohlYlQKu3fw=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"I just had a six pieces meal and it‚Äôs floating in the oil. Dear owner/hiring manager please train your staff properly  otherwise they gonna kill someone with giving a huge amount of canola oil in the chicken bucket. A blind people can also see the oil in the bucket but the lady who was working in the kitchen can‚Äôt see the oil. Please don‚Äôt spend your money at this place cuz it doesn‚Äôt worth spending here.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile\u0026image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPCujwbmV9eo2Mm5ohsng3_8kUIN_amoMT9kaKx\u0026fid=0x0:0x9d9956ec9aa6a9a5"],"When":"2024-5-4"},{"Name":"Parthivrajsinh Parmar","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUssdY71zvGKBouPx2fZurWXH8OeG58IIiASPL2OkLAYHvny1uj=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I go for the veg options, I always look out if Anmol is on the shift. He always remembers my order, makes sure that proper standards are followed, segregating the veg food from the non veg  section. That is why I love this store and visit twice a week.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Christie Myers","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWcUzAlx9ucXwRLAz7q1oFpMYJq2VGI1_I0aCL3_cyIsRDgfnqZ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"I want to be clear that my review is no fault of the staff themselves‚Äîthey really do try their best, but they are insanely overworked and understaffed. I go here every so often because ironically I love their plant based burger, but every time I come here, despite ordering in advance, I have to wait at least half an hour for food.\n\nThe store is always full of at least ten people also waiting for their food. Again, this is absolutely not the fault of the staff, but when there are ten people waiting, more orders coming in with one person working the counter and one person working the cooking station, it‚Äôs never going to be run efficiently. I get they want to make money, but joisus, it‚Äôs not fast food if it‚Äôs taking over 30 minutes every single time.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Christopher Nguan","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKSvVJZ_4yLo8Tuvps-xeUDW8nyywBgkET2lwA6kBX6GJIiZg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"This is a KFC located in East Broadway. A small place but very busy in its own right. There is parking in the back for about six or seven cars. There‚Äôs no dine in element for this location. It seems to do a lot of good business. We ordered the Family bucket today Only had to wait about 10 minutes before Her was ready. Of course KFC is a standard so the chicken tasted fresh and tasty and well cooked. Gravy was excellent fries or what you expect. Coleslaw as a staple and I seem to remember being glow in the dark green when I was a kid and they seem to have tuned the colour down quite a bit, but still the same type of very finally chopped vegetables in a creamy sauce. Which the fries seem to have changed a bit since I was a child as well from whatever I remember and our no longer the larger thicker soggy fries, but rather than more shoestring style and cooked to perfection. Stable and will keep coming back. Value for money is good.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Will Ko","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjU8QFf0NZ_ejwgXpI23LqHN9QIf25zp2IpOVPEFVc7b7Xri5HpCEQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"Ordered door dash from this location. Got the order wrong (missing one item), the Door Dash seal sticker was not applied to the bag properly (the temper-proof part wasn't ripped, the whole sticker just wasn't correctly applied) and the gravy was incredibly watered down. Only giving this a 2 star and not a 1 because the chicken was still fine.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Rochelle Drager","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjV8nlEvjIcxFFKk359Px3QqGFjRhR5P6XVcjY52dsaS2aTP3ums=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"The service is always so slow, even if you're just ordering sides. The past few times I've went it took over 5 minutes just for someone to take my order with no line, it always takes at least 15-20 additional minutes and they always seem way under staff considering they are supposed to be a fast food chain, and this is at different parts of the day, without fail so it's not just during rush hour, and I haven't had this issue with other kfc.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Babak Aghanejad","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKeRAgLVwTmb9zdMVM-gPX-LZRLcQGKVXYI2CsVaWOIXg2cfA=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I‚Äôve always been satisfied with this KFC location, and today‚Äôs visit on September 25, 2024, was no exception. The staff were incredibly kind and professional, as always. Everything was served on time and with great quality. I really appreciate the friendly service and consistent excellence here. Thanks to the wonderful team!","Images":null,"When":""}]

Then to the straight garbage attitude, \"What's your order? [{"Name":"L S","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLI0488T05p1G4gaZi6bsHBmtW5yaCb2BxUD4imhHuJOiSiFQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"This is legit the worst Dairy Queen I have ever had. I ordered a peanut buster parfait and they 1) must have given me a smaller cup because there was not 3 layers of fudge, only 2. And 2) they used the bottom scrap of the peanuts container, that had all the broken bits and tons of salt.
The first taste was so salty I scraped off the peanuts. I didn't think of taking a photo of the entire thing, only the top. I, for some reason, thought the peanuts at the bottom would be ok but no, it had made the entire ice cream salty. Like super salty and inedible.
They were also sold out of Cupfection that I originally wanted. Holy this was really bad.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOaCp8E1fj-JB2e_xSeGum14BMY06_Wm-n-LBp2&fid=0x0:0x30ca72fea2229514"],"When":"2024-9-3"},{"Name":"Johnny C","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWMH8aFZIGB5a7CFStbNQ6JGT0sYgxOttD7xMtIebcz8N9tnSzq=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"DQ Dilly bars....yummy üòã Dilly bar is my favourite...what‚Äôs yours? The restaurant have a limited number of seat in tables. On a hot summer day patrons can sit outside to enjoy DQ ice cream or burger. Usually there‚Äôs only one cashier working so it may he slow when there‚Äôs a lineup. My gripe is that sometimes the tables are dirty and needs to be cleaned ever so often by staff.

Personally I find the grilled chicken burger to be bland.  Not enough sauce.  The chicken strips on the dry side.  Beef burgers are good‚Ä¶not too dry.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNmReDR4eqyqsRX4arMWkosk2bRrZU-LChnG6pF&fid=0x0:0x30ca72fea2229514"],"When":"2022-2-6"},{"Name":"Ryan Ross","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUxbDlhVenJX4nGQzNLn3JyLXDgKUYiH-a3lBo-VWu7_cthLUW_=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"Entered the restaurant at 9: 25 pm, unaware that this particular location closed @ 10pm  given the other dairy Queen on Kingsway is open to 5am. After ordering I sat facing the front counter opposite my partner and received multiple again "displeased" displays of body language, coupled with rolling eyes, shaking head, and  walking away type behaviors. At 9:55 p.m. we were told the store was closing in 4 minutes and they had to lock the door and we needed to leave. user_reviews:
[{"Name":"jess cho","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjW61jux6VeXb22wP_Q69cy-q8ajx-92HgzF2pNEmhrQlrDyUy7N=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"My best pick was the free peanuts. I didn‚Äôt like the fries that soaked in peanut oil and hamburger had not much good beef flavour. I am not sure if I want to come back for burgers here. However, I was impressed the servers were quick and keep the store clean.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNARyKU-Emzs2VdBRrjFSWf9ukBeulw0ZlOXmK1&fid=0x0:0xb4d0b76dd25af09"],"When":"2024-11-5"},{"Name":"Vince C","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjV7rdvicqg2cC0r2JZ88o-9VEbfffVsLfbQQoXym02s6iusLNT2DA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"I was craving a good beefy burger after a hike and figured 5 Guys would hit the spot. I ordered the bacon cheeseburger. I get that price of supplies and labour have gone up but I feel like the quality of the burger and flavours this time weren't worth the price tag of almost $15. (And this is without fries!)

It wasn't bad per se but it wasn't fantastic either. It was just okay. It seemed to lack fresh flavours and you can see from the photo there's no lettuce. The flavours of their mayo sauce and fried onions with the bacon and cheese all kind of blended together and lacked any contrast. The buns weren't anything special either. Even if they didn't add any fresh ingredients like shredded cabbage or carrot, what would've helped is if they charred the beef patties a bit and properly caramelize the onions to give the burger a more diverse flavour profile.

Previous visits, I don't think I was this disappointed. I think I'll go elsewhere the next time I crave a burger, you don't get a whole lot of value here for your money anymore.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPshOMb0vR0Y8UWWcns6OSPNfrPWGO2f8E4oe5g&fid=0x0:0xb4d0b76dd25af09"],"When":"2024-8-15"},{"Name":"Scott Wong","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWqszz3Ljse-x4B5fzMk5AEAHCU8CBTkRxMEZLJtD02fVmXsiwidA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"The fries are as good as the burgers! Simple, fresh, delious. Definitely hits the spot if you are craving for burgers. Nothing fancy, just plain goodness. Peanuts are always free, and remember the regular comes in 2 beef stack.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOn-7YaSok4J7zuARN5xocYyICjTw3rRQO4oyfr&fid=0x0:0xb4d0b76dd25af09"],"When":"2024-10-6"},{"Name":"Lynne","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUZCsf97y3t-Ppi4xqcVMVpZ9qy3abZg0k-7Vz9rSFc5K4h7Apj=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"I haven't had here in a while, and this time I found the beef was slightly overcooked compared to my previous visits. Washroom was only single stall so it took a while to wash hands.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipP08rhJrfoIYluJ1DFh3peQOEBlpyXQa0-0CRTL&fid=0x0:0xb4d0b76dd25af09"],"When":"2024-6-24"},{"Name":"Wun Tun","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJRX8y0CFiE6nMEK8WbNNliTbzoWixhnMbLndMuv6xykpVccF8=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"First time trying this place.  I wasn't expecting double patties on my bacon burger.   It was a mouthful of juicy goodness. The cajun fries were just the right amount of zesty heat.  Wished there was more seating for larger groups.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Norman Farrell","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWOKauCUm-k2P6JXZbVaCjI514xmAUd8cPqhMzakFQdELGnjKWj0g=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Typical fast food burgers and fries are variable in quality, depending on how much time has passed since cooking and assembly. Five guys solves that issue by cooking to order, a process that takes seven or eight minutes. Because their burgers and hot dogs are not prepared before a customer orders, you can add anything from a long list of toppings and condiments. Suit yourself. That's a key. My burger had two thin meat patties lightly crusted on the exterior but still juicy. One "small" order of fries was hot, crisp and well seasoned. My only complaint was the serving size. It went beyond generous to excessive. Of course, we wouldn't want to eat in a restaurant that is not well maintained and staffed by people who seem happy to be there. On my May 2022 visit to the Park Royal store, housekeeping was in perfect order and the staff was friendly and attentive.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPMXR6QLFj4X3VZv51FJM_zSw6fzzwoMbUcb6gg&fid=0x0:0xb4d0b76dd25af09"],"When":"2022-5-6"},{"Name":"Justin P","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXHylp2ZUwAe8GQzpXv3X57qq7fheRuk9vvTbhwgQPiEDR2zu0=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"There's a lot going right here. It could be a lot worse. The lettuce was crisp. The burger was yummy. We got two patties which was cool. The Cajun frys really had a good deep fried crunch to them. I felt like I was in rural America. You walk in and you think what type of food could this place possibly provide? Well it's exactly what you thought. Nice and greasy.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPlLCZ5nFxXs1vlYfbxo3G8UfOu87ZZj4iyfIVQ&fid=0x0:0xb4d0b76dd25af09"],"When":"2024-3-31"}]

We felt slightly uncomfortable without having wipes handy to clean the table.

We were here to try the cookie dough McFlurry. It was quite good, but I still liked the Skor one more.

The chicken wrap was not bad at all! You don't expect that at a fast food chain as it was quite refreshing compared with the burger options.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipP41_nieOdk_O3uL923z4MlOiRY3QtqQeI2Y4wL&fid=0x0:0x517076643a3cb240"],"When":"2024-5-22"},{"Name":"Zane Thind","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWUxC2FTp9d_DYXAC9wShHN50isRi7-tijSuiqIERExcbqolSk=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Food is always delicious. Atmosphere isn't super good it can be peaceful but it's usually busy and loud and there's a lot of hobos here too. But besides that the employees seem friendly and the food is good. So it's worth a sacrifice to me and the homeless aren't actually threatening. But, it really does appeal to children‚Ä¶ So, once in a while, I have to take them there so they can have a Happy Meal.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Gs bajwa","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKUCpCsd3BUR_OI8EhVh6MLeq-2eUTl2bk9t4Bhx0Cepql4hA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Good place to eat. My views have changed.

Incident Report: Discrimination at McDonald's

Location:- Victoria drive vancouver.
Date:- 2nd Nov 2024
Time:- around 11am.

As a loyal customer of 3-4 years, I faced discrimination at McDonald's.

Incident:

1. Purchased coffee from McDonald's and food from nearby Kent's Kitchen.
2. Staff member refused indoor seating, citing "strong smell" policy.
3. Agreed to eat outside, but couple with same food was allowed inside.
4. Forced to eat on wet patio benches due to rain.
5. Bystander unnecessarily intervened, suggesting I leave to avoid security/police.

Experience:

- Discrimination
- Harassment
- Humiliation
- Repeated heartbreak in this country

Action:

1. Never visiting this McDonald's again.
2. Sharing experience on social media.

Seeking Support:

- Community organizations
- Online forums
- Friends and family

Remember:

- Everyone deserve respect and equality.
- Everyone,s voice matters.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMzecxKUIOw4iRBRW27OBrEcqcbuO7ImOKWwlwp&fid=0x0:0x517076643a3cb240"],"When":"2024-11-3"},{"Name":"Farhid Ali","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjW1zuAO8x9a5ssIXOGhZ_7VTeqYkdXQd3jYy7BUKcVt1yVlf2A=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"The food was good and the staff are nice too. However, the music is bothering me. Two different songs play on different areas of the store and they‚Äôre both loud.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Jayce Nguyen","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX9HAau6UlezyQSPaIHmozfNrwnV_QPE-MBoaut39VdtQDU9nQ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Had a quick quarter pounder meal with a coke zero at this location at 11:00pm. Had to spent the rest of my Saturday laying in bed to rest up and inconveniently had to skip work.","Images":null,"When":""}]

[{"Name":"Stella Oh","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWvqyQ2KS_YIN6XYOMkDtQZO2ezjEJLWRODsOzNFIWuIhCYtAL-=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I kid you not. We came here three days in a row just to get their kebab platter. The kebab platter comes with a heap of rice, pita, green salad, a grilled tomato, and an extremely hot Serrano pepper. Warning: The Serrano
pepper can cause an upset stomach or diarrhea. If you want to go for the challenge of eating the whole pepper, I suggest you keep some milk nearby. They didn‚Äôt put any sauce but the rice was flavourful (it was buttery) and the meat was very tender.

The men working there are polite and professional. They sell produce with some good deals from time to time. They were selling onions at a lower price than T&T on one of the days we were there to pick up the kebab. You can find various Middle Eastern snacks, teapots and even a Quran stand.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNyAwCU7_gJcR3PnSmO3X22vCrQ1Hr2T95IWRQY&fid=0x0:0xd69dc290bfe6c0a2"],"When":"2024-9-8"},{"Name":"MAHSA SAEDI","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLaxchhog6Zp6V6tEwnDWOD1wSB44CSK7hzfi4X3luP1tXC9A=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"The best supermarket grills I‚Äôve ever visited in Vancouver! The food was incredibly delicious, with the ground beef portions being an absolute standout. The staff were friendly and provided excellent service. The prices were reasonable, and the promotions added great value. I highly recommend checking it out ‚Äì you won‚Äôt be disappointed!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Kamaran Mawlood","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXzxNUd83x41KBrHh1tKmoaE1e33xEfzQoAgQia-agLsPFPNdU=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I recently visited Sultan Market, and I am beyond impressed! The store is impeccably clean, which makes shopping a pleasant experience from the moment you walk in.

I purchased some meat and groceries, and the freshness of the meat was unmatched. It's rare to find such quality these days, and the prices were surprisingly affordable!

A highlight of my visit was the 12 Kababs with rice and salad I bought. They were absolutely delicious, well-seasoned, and cooked to perfection. It's a must-try for anyone visiting the market!

Overall, Sultan Market has exceeded my expectations with its excellent products and service. I highly recommend it to anyone looking for quality groceries and delicious meals. I will definitely be returning soon!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Morgan Wowk","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjU8XJeykp3UaIMXFIjGg3pGXdgVnOcXB7nWYwQm9D2jwstBev_f=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Lovely shop with unique and tasty food fresh off the grill! user_reviews:
[{"Name":"El Styles","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXrrii3J8F9-5asxwPQAFrEFqNgl8kKXITZ3zJga8KlqLQjMRtjbw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"Kind of weird. Was really in the mood for a classic Donair Dude donair. Used Google maps and found this location which I've never been to before. They had a lot of different dishes than other locations however the prices are pretty high. They know it as well because an employee saw me looking at the menu and unprovoked she began to explain that they use grass fed beef that is why the price is high. I ordered the $15 beef pita wrap anyway because I was very hungry and didn't want to bother going somewhere else. When they asked what veggies I wanted, I started with "lettuce" to which the employee corrected me by saying "cabbage". Huh? No lettuce at a donair place....ok give me the cabbage then ü§∑ when I started eating the donair I noticed that the beef was diced up even smaller than the veggies! It looked like cat food. I don't know how this place can be under the donair dude name when it's this different. Maybe some of their other food is good?? I don't know but personally I won't be back. Staff relatively friendly though.

Update: I think all Donair Dudes have switch to cabbage now.... What the heck! Ruins it for me. I won't be going to Donair Dude again until they get lettuce back!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOtlT_KicGHK5IhSyy-GuoR8k8yqnzlgO29qxbc&fid=0x0:0xda283e9b15939c57"],"When":"2023-2-13"},{"Name":"Kram S","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocK9ON9D1tWKSKWDjtVVsOMXBA3V721YkX50l2liWOTv3G9ZMg=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"I ordered a Large garlic Parmesan fries for $11.99 but was disappointed how small the portion was. They use the same box for their platter, the portion is the same size of buying triple o Fries. See the photo on how much fries and space for this $11.99?","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMq88VM4s8Skf169QW-pVItvPcoDNunucYpzGca&fid=0x0:0xda283e9b15939c57"],"When":"2024-1-27"},{"Name":"Sean Chao","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIMvyOh-nfqnGrQEpZi3RouTOxQjxS5ffJavINOFiqNZdU3XQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"What's the point of offering a two for one deal if you split the meat portion of 1 into 2??

You guys serve meat as if World War 3 is happening outside, are you okay??

Canada produces beef and chicken, you don't need to be so stingy on the meat, Jesus Christ, just don't offer the two for one deals if your food cost can't effing handle it and your employees can't keep up the consistency.

The order still came out at 60$ from doordash, 2 beef and 2 chicken, I'll just go to Mr Shawarma next time","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Velvet Painting","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUycpLF73XsT5wZusZ2qYHcBR09KnVXYlK90uooJJkIxORxweU=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I go there pretty often  as it is on my way to work. Highly recommend!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOcou4dqGroi_kelkRV0BqkiwvSNE9YJLWt23x-&fid=0x0:0x389182f9c3e3ae82"],"When":"2024-12-5"},{"Name":"Salina Siu","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWxpGx9PtwU6w3sKuOjsoqRRctoryZk5GPJZ0KpCJuDAxGw6fJT=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"I ordered two chicken value meals, which is their special deal currently. The price is about $10 and the quantity is OK. Not something I would go for all the time but in a pinch it does the job. The value meals come with rice, meat, sauce, with a few small potatoes on the side and one pita with a container of hummus. Food is tasty and comes with enough sauce but overall ok.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOoYaMEOeMKsONR0x-JQ-_nNIPqErHRBWYUqwYi&fid=0x0:0x389182f9c3e3ae82"],"When":"2023-2-7"},{"Name":"Sam Trueno","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVVL6r1heC-oSKsEQRFj95jyQwURoFe3hKqV3FFNLud24nn-EU=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"I recently had a Donair from Donair Dude and unfortunately, it was a huge letdown. The quality was shockingly low, leaving me unsatisfied and disappointed.

Firstly, the protein content was severely lacking. It felt more like a garnish than a substantial part of the meal. I expected a hearty portion of meat, but instead, it was just a teaspoon of grey, unappetizing substance that resembled cat food. This was a major letdown, especially considering the reputation Donairs typically have for their generous servings of flavorful meat.

The visual presentation was equally unappetizing. The dull grey color and unappetizing texture of the meat left much to be desired. It was far from the appetizing, succulent image one would associate with a Donair.

Overall, my experience with this Donair was extremely disappointing. I was left wanting for more in every aspect - from the protein content to the visual appeal. I would strongly advise against visiting this establishment for a Donair, as there are certainly much better options available elsewhere.

It's a shame when a beloved dish falls short of expectations. I hope that this restaurant can take steps to improve the quality of their Donairs in the future.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMRf0nENsj6AVm-Snx-pcEUqebUvZT7rhaBHtL4&fid=0x0:0x389182f9c3e3ae82"],"When":"2023-10-14"},{"Name":"Lawal Faikat","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJN00XA841by2Nh6cm9ww6w_Ljjq9BsRhevmdth_hHcxwbDZQ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"The worst place to get food. As a person of the black community and a female,  I have never been so disgusted by someone‚Äôs behaviour. I wish I could give no star. I was openly being rude to for no valid reason(I have worked in food industry and I understand the frustration), even though I was very understanding and easy. The woman (no name needed) with a piercing was very very rude to me. I‚Äôm sure she does that with other clients as I have seen it myself. Not trying to make anyone lose their job or anything but the employees should be trained to understand that not everyone that enters the store is uneducated or ill-mannered.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPUNl6t34KwsZrO1V8tFeo2bgYLEFM3UIm0DmYC&fid=0x0:0x389182f9c3e3ae82"],"When":"2023-8-8"},{"Name":"Sarah Kosari","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWRKJF1Yntnp-zRLmumvc9e-i3Wwazxmkif9r_MkSiD9JZJ8ngfpA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Delicious food, beautiful ambiance with healthy options! I definitely go back again ! The chicken & waffles were great! We ordered it with the sweet & spicy sauce. We were also given some syrup and spicy mayo for the chicken & waffles. We also ordered a medium size Original Black boneless chicken, but we both preferred the sweet and spicy sauce. The onion rings were also super crispy and flavourful!
There is only 4 seats on the window side, so you should definitely consider doing take out if you have a big group.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNOQa3Yk1hSkyB3PG1e51HB_F4bO4zFz8lcLLQU&fid=0x0:0x9745cd9466a1cf98"],"When":"2024-6-16"},{"Name":"Mia L","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUq642CDPVZTSH8j21c0TphXuT4YKuFtCxeaLXz7q1CKF5Ej-Lg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Came across this place today and wow !!!

Time .

Everything was great, definitely wasn‚Äôt expecting to find this place today but I‚Äôm so glad I did .","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMfjbnHy2SyD_4E5_IYp-igffK2X3ZINwrXQQdT&fid=0x0:0x9745cd9466a1cf98"],"When":"2024-10-17"},{"Name":"Fuzzy Nemo","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWMhjGNDhI-RZYgIiVRXnRDEQCiyyP-dsVjb7EhBkcymNr9MvYi0A=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"This place was pretty outstanding. But overall the service and the ambience is good.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPB-AOS6R-6mKqQqENBRCOZoGmM_w0UqJbIe44&fid=0x0:0x43e657669f8110be"],"When":"2024-10-19"},{"Name":"Elise","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjW8VzNw2Tx5_BjbfDePWcglR8ou3DS5pLuf9I_qJ859XvOdO5ljnA=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Very good restaurant! Staff are very friendly and attentive. Food was delicious! Most plates are available in small or large sizes, with the picture of beef rendang curry attached showing the small size. [{"Name":"23Ìù¨Îèô","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocL1kXSjZzrG9rqzpINVPJM281Qvj-Z_UpNbjiuu7_UW3AXF-w=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I've been there twice and it was great both times. We ordered different dishes and they were all delicious.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOfDyiDliTVAlUjTIt8X_Z2s35mwcdMNAPo9IGn&fid=0x0:0x1c0135c6be7f3dcb"],"When":"2024-8-1"},{"Name":"Joshua Lamb","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWpxxroB9wWkDP81-bzqi9m3qKH73kXPdF1qlay8Miqx3mQiFLjRg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"Okay, so first time here and my friends said it's awesome. We luckily got here for happy hour. So, we got a bunch of different dishes, so let me review.
(I did not try the impossible burger and Cobb Salad, but from my friends, it wasn't anything special.)

Pros on food:
The Fish Haddock Burger with ceasar
Mediocre and honestly the coleslaw flavor neutralized whatever fish flavor there was. The crispiness was on point, but having jo flavor really shine through this burger, I was left sad and feeling like I had a fish filler at McDonalds. The ceasar was the most disappointing salad I've had. So I started nibbling on my friends dishes.

Prawn Spinach and Mushroom Fettuccine:
Dry. More like a dry pasta salad with some shrimp. The prawn was decently cooked, but once you're done with them and left with the rest, it's exhaustivdly dry. She's didn't even finish her dish, just a few nibbles that's it and left the bowl full.

Fries:
Average

Okay so let's be real, I just ate at a burger style Denny's. Price was moderately higher for this quality of a meal. I'd rather stick to my more trusted restaurants.

Worth it, if you're hungry it's a fun place and service was spectacular. Our waiter deserves a raise and the speed of food to table was nice. But quality of dishes, 3 stars. Sorry supporters of White Spot.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOViFw_zrYBGKJiIUte6eN0RiZchwawd-vvaoYS&fid=0x0:0x1c0135c6be7f3dcb"],"When":"2024-7-2"},{"Name":"Julien Salomoni","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjViaO6gVJkm-aDsrcz_NkNmy8tx1NR_WPh1jW1IEU3WF2qJs0Sk=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"My first time trying white spot, believe it or not!
My friend and I had a great time, we‚Äôve been welcome with smiles and warmth then we choose our spot, decided to get outside and it was lovely. Our server was literally the nicest ever and helped me kindly but surely to enjoy as much as I could my dishes. He was a real professional, and if you read this lines I personally thank you again, I should have ask your name. I got myself the sweet potatoes fries, I was craving for those since a while, they were delicious then I got the tomatoes and spinach benny because Benny are a must to get, I added an extra bacon with it. It was really good. And to harmonized my lunch, I finished with the salted caramel milkshake‚Ä¶ I was full and my heart soothed. Thank you üôèüèª","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPduon6HgpNo6c1PELLUzGNWUGUhfkkR_3qHEix&fid=0x0:0x1c0135c6be7f3dcb"],"When":"2024-4-23"},{"Name":"Nancy Wang","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjU_94zzTXxyiloKEVIGEZMIl3YYDzeOKg_OlxLIktGWc93WB4B6-A=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"This quaint eatery nestled in the bustling Westside of Vancouver is a breakfast haven with a myriad of delectable options that are both satisfying and beautifully presented. The portions are generous, ensuring you start your day fully energized. What stands out is the freshness of the ingredients; each dish bursts with flavor, indicative of their commitment to quality.

Parking is a breeze, which is a pleasant surprise for the area, eliminating any hassle before your meal. The restaurant‚Äôs layout includes a charming outdoor section, perfect for those who appreciate dining al fresco. It‚Äôs a serene spot that offers a slice of privacy in the open air.

The winters here are made comfortable with the thoughtful addition of heating lamps, creating a warm oasis amidst the chilly weather. Natural light floods the area, making it an inviting place to linger over a meal.

An added perk is the unlimited coffee refills, a gesture that coffee aficionados will certainly value. This isn't just a meal; it's an experience‚Äîa place where the food, atmosphere, and friendly service intertwine to create a memorable dining adventure. It‚Äôs no wonder this spot is a local gem for brunch enthusiasts.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipN4bq1ycOOyy6cblJlCUbWRuI7uCD6JHXvycJak&fid=0x0:0x1c0135c6be7f3dcb"],"When":"2024-3-12"},{"Name":"Cooki Lumsden","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVtcYuaSju9uQoB-dVKkUC51ry_tzg4h-XCUCGhTJVUJjJgBNZU=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I‚Äôve not been to White Castle since 1965 when it was a drive in only burgers and fries joint. The dining room and expanded menu are a very pleasant surprise.
The legendary burger was just a burger then, but it has since become legendary and is still as delicious as I remember. The fries are very good and the coleslaw is wonderfully sublime.  I‚Äôm told that the perogies are quite tasty.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOvlNUB3MIxs3xuzaY74GAq0pi1T0L7XtgTDI7j&fid=0x0:0x1c0135c6be7f3dcb"],"When":"2024-2-11"},{"Name":"Chloe Rachel","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWgExGuK1W-XgQc1tPnrQlqQkWxCTaNhdz977uVTTY3zjpsAzs-=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Dined during happy hour and had the Humboldt squid appetizer (savings of $4) and Caesar salad. It was a satisfying portion for lunch. The squid batter was crispy and came with lots of Tzatziki presented on the plate versus in a side container. At a regular price of $16, I would have expected more squid but it was reasonable for $12. Service was adequate and friendly! White Spot continues to be a favourite spot for comfort food. We are disappointed that they no longer have a seniors menu, although our server did say a couple of items like the fish and chips can be made in a smaller portion.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMIBx3ALJjnH355V8Z-ItLu7ybatm72uuTy2VBr&fid=0x0:0x1c0135c6be7f3dcb"],"When":"2023-10-26"},{"Name":"Jon Pool","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJgB4Ixcm3coGrtFxgy8d_jXc_y7csLbAvrSGKW0bRwFuxqgA=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"Come here often (2-3X week) for dinner.  Came for breakfast on Sunday morning at 9:00AM.  Waited for 2 min at the front for a host to notice and offer seating.  Our server Paige was slow and seemed disinterested.  The food is usually very good although my wife‚Äôs pancakes were the same size as my daughter‚Äôs pirate pack pancakes.  Mornings seem to really lack atmosphere or any sense of fun.  If we come back it will be dinner only I think.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"GOZDE Kilic","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUywfFev2T_aNUd3Hhof86yAL56zOfCSebLsolBAv89xxXYh-lE=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We stopped by to get ourselves a milkshake after ice skating. We chose chocolate and vanilla which tasted really great. Fast service,","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNs90j0T-_wBrFE1bCuJ6rjhr5XzW2P3CoCTtmN&fid=0x0:0x1c0135c6be7f3dcb"],"When":"2024-12-16"}]

[{"Name":"Shay Saville","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX4VJKZi-fOdCK8EP7o1EJBQkK7QC6nD-skoidaFJCPBo5NfnrTQA=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Sorry but what the **** did I just buy? Got a bowl and burrito for dinner tonight, smelt great. Opened it up and it was literally cabbage and cartilage with some sauce. In the bowl: Barely any rice, super greasy, a bunch of cartilage parts of chicken.  The burrito: super greasy, one large chunk of cartilage and fat which you can see in the photo. I took a bite into my burrito and that‚Äôs what I bit and pulled out. I couldn‚Äôt bite into it to break it apart. Upon further inspection the cheese was also just a large clump at the bottom of my burrito. So if I had gotten through all that cartilage, I would have bit into a straight ball of cheese.
We are so grossed out. Will definitely not be eating from tacofino again. I never make reviews, but like I said‚Ä¶ what the **** did I just buy?? Such a waste of $53 dollars. If you‚Äôre going to eat here, order some tater tots. Those were good!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipP-4GwPN9cMGey92ZkqqUrQ7Lh_fi_WZLnDtlnF&fid=0x0:0x6525f225bc45571b"],"When":"2024-12-2"},{"Name":"Daria Liukin","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVkJyqUukJ1Tp32CT1Y60hgwO8TEu98t8UrHjC4vSHU3XhtZR-hfA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"My first time visiting here was amazing! I highly recommend the cheeseburger burrito, I wasn‚Äôt expecting it to be so good!

My friend had a bit of an issue with the service, as they didn‚Äôt allow lettuce to be added to her burrito but did offer it on the side. It was a bit odd since she had to open the burrito to add it herself.
Despite this, we had a good experience overall.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNHrrMRtoQJblTpjKW57KgYR3yNq3UqD3YtedJL&fid=0x0:0x6525f225bc45571b"],"When":"2024-9-5"},{"Name":"Clare Wang","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXk8vaI8odicOm4apSk77_C5_lBI2gd1LxngMFranmQFokEsPvD-w=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"Got the crispy chicken bowl and it was good‚Ä¶ albeit on the small size. Their nevertheless non alcoholic beer was good!
Service is pay and order at the counter, though they bring your food to you.
Atmosphere is okay! Nothing special but spacious thankfully.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipP1JuAka89jkyb1iloywOH2OrxFlvdBH-eXfy_I&fid=0x0:0x6525f225bc45571b"],"When":"2024-9-7"},{"Name":"K","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJ3p0B0lElhzgRwIPkYbb0yJbYMEI0-XJUCpyVZaXsmo-4i6w=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Had a great experience having lunch here! I've never had anything like the vegggie chick'n before, and it was satisfying and filling in the delicious burrito bowl! Bonus that it was meatless Monday üòÉ

The crispy tofu wasn't crispy, and somehow that burrito bowl seemed a smaller, less substantial portion.

Wanted to shout out the super service from the lovely Alana! She made it a wonderfully pleasant and memorable visit, with her friendly, kind, helpful, smiley, sweet service! So appreciated, and a valuable asset! Thanks Alana (and chefs & team!) & all the best to you! üòä","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOZmgXx8LeYK87yC4pYZo5bl96VoVD7Odu_HFiB&fid=0x0:0x6525f225bc45571b"],"When":"2024-10-9"},{"Name":"P","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLJfI7Jv5AdroY1kV5bfM4zh0h9da438LBsla_KJiY9uJPJdg=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I love this place!  The burritos are my favourite. At this location, I love the crispy tofu, and corn fritter burritos. The flavour combinations are amazing, and the crispy bits in these burritos make for such great texture. I am hoping this location might get the super veg burrito at some point, as I‚Äôve had that in Squamish and it is another favourite. The burritos are not only delicious, they are very filling.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Kayla Powell","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJb65Mvndjv_oKz95NJR7hawyPOjSna1MBnvKfolazTaj5iDQ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"I used to love this location for their bake it yourself nachos which are so convenient! But I've noticed in the passed few years their containers for the ingredients have reduced in size twice and the quality is a toss-up at times. The chips used to come in a big to-go box, then they changed it to a small paper tote, and now it's in a bag they use for their cookies, stapled together. As well, I used to get the guac in a brown container and it has since changed to a smaller white one with much less. The salsa I got today for the nachos was not fresh, it was dry and old and the tomatoes look pale.
I was disappointed as it was $30 and was not the usual standard.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipM3bbJYYGe18_GzKGkYlfkBfLaNydEpGkAThr7L&fid=0x0:0x6525f225bc45571b"],"When":"2024-6-24"},{"Name":"Natalia Rosas","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWqj5-V2_ESmcV6u0FGYK4tYaIveDzvE7GElTRUxOoirdh3usP5gA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"So good! We also had the Maui Pork Burrito and chicken wings, we‚Äôll definitely come back ‚ù§Ô∏è","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOJXFKym7ROHi0cfZ4PkaGXjoPia4YA9K0kVh07&fid=0x0:0x6525f225bc45571b"],"When":"2024-11-4"},{"Name":"Kwong Tang","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVRNhrcdIOQyhkpCbdjoUSwC0OqkPEp5C09o-KZX9pyAsIQioX9=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"üï∫ Dance with Flavors at Tacofino's Taco Fiesta üíÉ

Ah, Tacofino, where the flavors of the sea meet the zest of the coast! I swung by to snag an Albacore Tuna Taco and a Pacific Cod Taco, and let me tell you, they were nothing short of delighful. The tuna was a flavorful wave, while the cod felt like a friendly oceanic high-five. üåäüêü

The chill vibe at Tacofino adds to the experience, making it feel like a beach hangout minus the sand. It's perfect for a quick bite or a leisurely meal. Sure, there might be a wait, but the scrumptious bites are worth every minute. üèñÔ∏èüç¥

If you're on the hunt for some top-notch tacos, make your way to Tacofino. Your tastebuds will be dancing with gratitude! üåü","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOfURRudkBrKWUTV8r2zqoVowYjxsN3CSwfCnc3&fid=0x0:0x6525f225bc45571b"],"When":"2024-3-23"}]

[{"Name":"Jason Brawn","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXGJaU20iM-ZTxKU88Eh8aQ0G6FeQUBkbo4O84nuTWj3KUf3yIR=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I've lived just a couple blocks away from Tractor for years, but for some reason haven't stopped in before recently. That was a terrible mistake, as this place is awesome.

We've had lunch here a few times now, and it's always delicious whatever we have. The salads are the picture of freshness, and the soup/sandwich combo always impresses. Especially when enjoyed while sitting on their nice little patio.

Our last visit we had the meatball sandwich, and I'm tempted to have it again for lunch today. Paired with the lentil soup, it's about as tasty and healthy as a casual lunch can get.

As a bonus, the place is kept very clean, the staff is super friendly, and they have proper water glasses instead of plastic ‚Äì an environmentally mindful touch we don't overlook. We're regulars now, and definitely recommend the place to anyone looking for some great food in Kits.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNwErSjqF1fU_8xRnT3LCrZ94OZr7TWi0NBpzhH&fid=0x0:0x100298d06c4ad54f"],"When":"2024-9-3"},{"Name":"Arthur Sapounas","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKEZyp4x5vfcuXqazupP-qAYYDcl7n5BPWhlC_L7ZR_YkzicQ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"Normally this place is ok. I've seen them behind our building with your bins and asked if that‚Äôs their plan. Those bins are paid for and already heavily used by residents.

If you‚Äôre going to do this, at least make sure the lids are shut properly to prevent animals from getting in and causing the alley to smell or attract rodents. [{"Name":"Irene","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVWEsa7NYWic6K7ZWmmF5xDmMSH_xept3dal3ExovWoByBZJ0Mb=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I wish I found out about this place sooner! We had a great experience. The owner and staff are very friendly and service-oriented. They really take time to chat with their customers. Food is great: fresh, high quality ingredients and really delicious. The fried chicken is ü§å Portions are just enough and reasonably priced. Came here with our toddler and I would say that this place is very kid friendly. Ordered a mac and cheese for the little one and they made sure there were no spices in it for her. She really enjoyed it while sitting comfortably in her high chair. Adding this to our fave brunch spots!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNy_x1uQpoUyfXjIHjFvrD_cIAEh-zB57IL36VP&fid=0x0:0x68caafcff71e5e19"],"When":"2024-9-22"},{"Name":"Spring Jiang","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKCOcDF5iD93ntHy_A3C3_x1khcRP6ebt7-uX7XGT15seNvCg=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"hardly believe that such a generous and delicious restaurant is right on the bustling commercial street! The fried chicken is crispy on the outside and juicy inside, and the fries are perfectly crispy with a rich potato flavor! The portion sizes are surprisingly large for the price! The chef and staff are so warm and friendly‚ÄîI definitely have to bring more friends here!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNhCOgzQN9cASv6auURp6RUfYzG6EEArnawsg0z&fid=0x0:0x68caafcff71e5e19"],"When":"2024-9-10"},{"Name":"Jasper Koolen","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWYJcdW5-YH2IcWujxRwyhDwyPsh4E0vTFuvcrGen3PDIWgYw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Highly recommend! Some of the best fried chicken I‚Äôve ever had. The home made lemonade is delicious, and the portion sizes are generous. Chewie (the owner) is an absolute legend and takes very good care of his patrons. You can tell he cares about his customers and the experience they have. We will be back!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOArk8YAT41GaldV0jIfhKLEJhLMCtHaywZqgI&fid=0x0:0x68caafcff71e5e19"],"When":"2024-9-23"},{"Name":"Felix Rankin","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUpJ-yYQaqhIHkPOZ9xWbxX8zbVOuthsh7rV-GMj2_ucOkUKJU=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Undoubtedly top 3 restaurant in Vancouver for me. This place doesn‚Äôt try to be something it isn‚Äôt. Always nice service and super good food. I mean DELICIOUS. Competitively priced too. Always have to go with the white gravy and make sure you try the fries and the crispy chicken skins. Dipped in this sauce I forget what it was but it was very tart and almost sour. Paired perfectly with the chicken skins. I get intense cravings for this place about once a month","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOvvKNDBTZvKMQltj-CqPEBnRtK9MgTN1pvoXMR&fid=0x0:0x68caafcff71e5e19"],"When":"2024-10-10"},{"Name":"Hiep Nguyen","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWMRHHZ7t798igHqhwEObqqiXXBYRe7_vTRRS3-gXG7fOgZlXSH=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"My wife and I were at our elder daughter's volleyball tournament and needed to get some dinner before the next game starts so we googled the closest place to Lord Byng Highschool. Got take out and ate it on the bleachers while all the other parents were drooling üòÑ ü§£.  The 4 piece combo with fries and a can of pop for $22 was enough to feed us. We don't eat that much. I don't know what seasoning they put on the chicken skin, but it was delicious. And the meat inside was juicy and soft. The fries were really good too! I definitely recommend it here, much better that church's chicken (which is my fave fried chicken place for the past 30 yrs).","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipP5WjsEmiREkH775A3ABkmWvJl2LLFWrPeM7G1_&fid=0x0:0x68caafcff71e5e19"],"When":"2024-9-14"},{"Name":"Kathy Ly","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJn_eKY7tfjGINk8NgIe8tDjbdiIjqqkiBokkv6RkHq8at-jg=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I recently visited Chewie with my family, and we had an incredible experience! The fried chicken was absolutely amazing‚Äîcrispy on the outside and juicy on the inside, with a perfect balance of seasoning. The service was equally impressive. The staff were very helpful, especially in giving recommendations for first-time visitors like us. Their friendly and attentive nature made our dining experience even better. We will definitely be back for brunch to try more of their delicious offerings. Highly recommend!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPxzI1BCqK8POT3ikEU0bZx3siJ9pD_udkOJnb6&fid=0x0:0x68caafcff71e5e19"],"When":"2024-7-30"},{"Name":"Aim√©e Barrie","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWPe-12u9egPainL2VWWovAX8Cl0pc-qkoJsLKvriMFKeGt2GiY=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"This place is AWESOME!

The food is phenomenal, but what makes Chewies so special is the service. Shay (‚ÄúButter‚Äù) was warm and welcoming, while balancing out helping all the tables around her.

The chef (Chewie himself!) came out of the kitchen and spread warmth and care, truly connecting with everyone in the restaurant as if they were dear friends in his home.

If you haven‚Äôt been to Chewies before - what are you waiting for?
Come now, and come often. Trust me. It‚Äôs worth it.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipM2CNHGKkmpnce7Y8EJypYn-xkqNSnFiokN1KzV&fid=0x0:0x68caafcff71e5e19"],"When":"2024-11-10"},{"Name":"Christopher Neufeld","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjV5e6kqCASmiD1m7NndbDVevchKBrvgcmqG--c57OPk2gk6IzdS=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"A great little place with amazing food! We had a mix of meals, all of which were delicious. The biscuits are phenomenal! Their flaky, melt-in-your-mouth goodness was a perfect pairing for the crispy fried chicken. The eggs were delicious, with lots of flavour, and there‚Äôs a slight bit of heat on everything with a little cayenne (I think). But not spicy. Just a little warmth.
Overall, amazing. I‚Äôd highly recommend it. Also, the woman helping us was super friendly and helpful and rounded out a great meal experience.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNiRD3C9mn5IBXlh36p4gcg3CCb7aIqNhbqoJlN&fid=0x0:0x68caafcff71e5e19"],"When":"2024-4-28"}]

[{"Name":"Cole Davis","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVAOU6XCX3s_R0vWndse-P-J59JZDVGZbi6kfyG2pJARhX4qsYzZw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"Not a great experience, tightly packed seating and decent food. Prices are normal.
Parking is difficult to find here.

I have not eaten enough dishes here to recommend anything. Judging by the look on everyone's face, it's not visible which dish is this restaurant's special either.

I like their assortment of mugs. It's something special about this place.

Something else which caused problems for customers was the ridiculous amount of giant mosquitoes. We were sat down, not by a waiter but a mosquito. It was the size of my hand. The waiter/resses don't seem to mind them at all, which is hilarious.

Overall, if you're in the area looking for HK style food this could be your spot.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNwJoVFwxrAjML6PEnsPKA2gItLAjmE59zogEXr&fid=0x0:0xb9bc5d41b49f68e4"],"When":"2024-6-30"},{"Name":"Tracy S","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUPi18u3JsyAOz_Y6rVUxhHrmGj9FkTJ1e3zp3M68c8ShuDg6wc=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Really delicious food and good prices. Fish congee was amazing and large - enough for 2 people. We also ordered the fried tofu but it was a little disappointing. I thought it was the salty peppery tofu (ordered it in Chinese), but it had no garlic/chili so I would not order it again. Good crispiness though and amazingly friendly staff. ü§ó They also speak English really fluently","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Mark Liu","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVK013A6TM5Le2iVdQPHPEdhpJekGRPFgo9Lg1TAIeu9E3XRGNG=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Minced beef congee - it was tasty but I was hoping more crispy rice vermicelli mixed with beef.

Lamb stew - gamey but flavor is good.

Rice vermicelli with pork liver - Those who doesn't like pork liver is one thing but this is very well done.  They use Chinese herb to make the soup, it's very healthy, the pork liver was just done perfectly, not too cook and not too raw.  There chicken that used to make the soup is very tender and flavorful (chicken flavor means they use high quality free range yellow feather chickenÈªÉÊØõÈõû)

Broken rice congee with clams - The soup is so flavorful, I was delightedly and surprisingly impressed. Clams were big, it's not really broken rice they just add cook rice into the soup.  But it tastes really good.

I actually not thrilled with there lamb stew nor the minced beef congee but that's just me.  The other dishes I was very impressed.

This place certainly from HK with unique cooking skills.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPWprGNhTps3ajBR_Z3eQRqSc23bnaTJ1_dPdzQ&fid=0x0:0xb9bc5d41b49f68e4"],"When":"2022-3-26"},{"Name":"Sarah W","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXT0nZvuCCWtxE7tCmKwkdtK9DgTxxgPN_H5tcLUmMEgLxeACiU=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"It is a hole in the wall place with large portions and good food. If you order the special ‚ÄòWor‚Äô, you can‚Äôt go wrong. The price is very reasonable with what you are given. Lunch is busy but turn around is fast. There are only two ladies working there, they will get to you when they can.  There is no decor, you are there for a quick meal. Lots of takeout also.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipND_1D5VOL8reajpIXeluELOyq3nRVdsCJye3UJ&fid=0x0:0xb9bc5d41b49f68e4"],"When":"2018-12-20"},{"Name":"Rongting Luo","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUoUuPmBkCCZ4u--x14TLCOW3fVhRv0PFZZ3T-BSlj2I0mcMQMi=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I ordered my favourite black beans fish, beef soup rice noodles, large portion and delicious. Definitely will go back for other noodles soup.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Arielle Lok","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWtizUZyTvP27ebSmpanVv0Z9tQujmr--1qEE7rOUgWFj5vvv5i=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"good + authentic. u know it‚Äôs bussin when they have the sugar containers with the single circular hole and the dark see-through plastic water cups.

specials come with free hot drink. would return","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPYkDOJPsR_ByFZ_wujaAkBBK-hEWnh6_4CSekp&fid=0x0:0xb9bc5d41b49f68e4"],"When":"2022-9-25"},{"Name":"rageguy","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUEGMZ9NyPl3ohSB3CMTrGvf2DAtNlQdOkqk_IWac7PjoqFOYyU=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"It‚Äôs a no frills quick to go Hong Kong style cafe operated by what seems to be a mom and dad. Super affordable food and taste decent for the price point. Their baked pork chop rice is good and large. The minced beef congee is like HK, with fried vermicelli bits, better than Double Double. Bought the Friends and family bucket.  Online it‚Äôs advertised for $49.99 but if you go to the store it‚Äôs advertised as $46.99 so you save yourself $3.

They said they don‚Äôt offer the 2L torpedo of pop and you get four cans of pop instead.  I don‚Äôt see that as a fair replacement but the drink part wasn‚Äôt important to me.  The bucket has a sample of deepfried fish, popcorn chicken, fried bone in chicken, fries, and fried bone in wings.  It doesn‚Äôt come with chicken tenders so I can‚Äôt comment on those but they DO SELL chicken tenders.

Fish was really good and the four pieces were decent sized.  They looked like chicken tenders if you weren‚Äôt paying attention.  Fried chicken and wings were also good - nice amount of crunch and flavor and good sized pieces.  My least favorite was the popcorn chicken - the meat was dense and the breading not as crunchy but similar to your generic popcorn chicken like you‚Äôd get at KFC.

The fries are breaded like the fries you get at Costco.  Flavor wise my husband thought there was some sweetness to the breading on the chicken and the fish - similar to Taiwanese fried chicken.  Personally I didn‚Äôt get the sweetness but I thought it was just plain tasty and crunchy.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMDEc-Cx12VjYYOS_32_Mmev7ypFob2uZkabQml&fid=0x0:0x5bf2cdc7a058cc4c"],"When":"2024-5-23"},{"Name":"nicole","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUGCLqI3OvGBhvseSeeKQh4HSu6r2268xeNIemRHA9t2v6RKSfjrg=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Portions are HUGE! best chicken sandwich I've ever had.

Overall, if you're craving delicious chicken burgers, Hi Five Chicken is a must-visit spot! I can‚Äôt wait to go back!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipN6H5US-r9DuP2aelqXvJ1VnciV27qrPH4CyRi_&fid=0x0:0x261ab7b21373fa19"],"When":"2024-9-10"},{"Name":"dan roxas","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX9Jx1R3xmxZDUxzfyTjLL1LGbeewFEwWBaNs-uwgS_zYD2DheenQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"its alright, i guess, i ordered the korean sandwich and its not what it looks like on the menu. it looks like a regular chicken sandwich with a little sauce on top. my son ordered the classic chicken sandwich and they literally look and taste the same, except for the sauce part. bun was cold out and the chicken was dry. not juicy at all. we also ordered the 3 piece and the chicken for my taste buds seems bland. missing some umami flavour and also lacks saltyness. the gravy was too runny and seems like it was a watered down version of the costco gravy. which leaves me to the fries, the fries is actually good and crunchy, then it hit us up, the fries looks like from costco. over all, the food is still ok, it wasnt what we expected it to be. service is actuslly good, the crew was friendly and even took time to bring our food to our table. its good for immidiate fried chicken cravings if you're around the area.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMeB0YLQ99ShcpBOnJfv-Ho-oPOmTLBf01uADy5&fid=0x0:0x261ab7b21373fa19"],"When":"2024-6-15"},{"Name":"Adam Hermes","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJRF5DJob0OpJbAGckMllJLCTJOmcSQ0CoY4fWtV5ZEmqB6QS_p=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I recently visited Five Chicken and was blown away by the quality of the food and the overall dining experience. The sides were equally impressive, with generous portions of crispy fries and fresh salads. The service was fast and friendly, making the overall experience enjoyable and hassle-free. The casual atmosphere is perfect for a quick bite or a relaxed meal with friends and family.

I highly recommend Five Chicken for anyone craving delicious, high-quality chicken dishes. It‚Äôs definitely a spot I‚Äôll be visiting again!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"jd dgl","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJykWlX0RvcAipvxAj_PzSgczSg1vFdNZNjrb4wyDNA8FuBjQ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Would you pay $20.56 for this burgers? I am a bus driver which I was supposed to get a 10% complimentary discount when I came with my uniform on but I didn‚Äôt. I don‚Äôt mind about the discount as long as I get a decent sandwich.
