user_reviews:
[{"Name":"Colin Chau","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXKsZm0dxkoaNVpT_U5MSz6Hu71-aJgYtlTkTneFejPbF30OZkbOg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"Edit: WRT the owner‚Äôs response I found it to be pretty defensive.  There is an ego at play here saying ‚Äúif you don‚Äôt like don‚Äôt buy‚Äù is a pretty rhetorical point to make since already indicated I likely won‚Äôt be back the next time I‚Äôm craving the familiar taste of Donair.  I also did not say the basmati rice was bad, I was simply just saying that it wasn‚Äôt what the palate was anticipating.  An appropriate response would have been ‚Äúthanks for your feedback, and we will take it into consideration as we continue to receive feedback on our service offerings‚Äù without the need to commit to anything since I‚Äôm just one customer and not the owner who gets to exercise their own prerogative.  Some more growth and maturity is required on the part of the ownership.
‚Äî-

The visit (original post):
Service was polite.  Food was a bit disappointing. The rice used was basmati and it had the fragrance of indian food, which while nice was a departure from what this food should taste like.   All platters are $17.95 and most other places charging this price would follow your container to the brim. I found the portions here quite stingyyz would also help to have feta on the salad and turnips available.

I enjoyed my food well enough.  The sauce was also great (‚Äúas expected‚Äù) but something about it just felt really underwhelming for the money I am parting with. Probably won‚Äôt be back the next time I‚Äôm craving donair.

They also have violated the single use plastics ban that has been around for over a year (since December 2023), in terms of the cutlery.  The take out containers are made from compostable corn starch, however, these were also banned starting July 2024. A quick chat with the BC OPI on this file confirmed that indeed these packagings and cutlery are no longer permitted in BC as of the dates stated.  The owner‚Äôs response is that they are approved all over Canada.  Apparently, owner you don‚Äôt understand that while federal laws supersede, more specific provincial laws can also apply if they carry more nuance.  The federal statutes set a baseline.  Ownership Needs a lesson in Canada‚Äôs constitutional fabric and history.

All violations can be reported any time to plastics@gov.bc.ca with the name and address of the business and photos to substantiate the claim.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMCJ4YsAbfJ24vYwCOg6-EZ2Lo9WmneYc0Fr2eV&fid=0x0:0x1eb5beeadc5f6d94"],"When":"2024-12-6"},{"Name":"Haranmol Sidhu","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKYMAAWNVb-SA_Vn5-etruI0jR0fgujcpmUFXkhPuAV59_Sig=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"This is the worst donair ever had . Girl behind the counter does have no clue about  even how to say hello to a customer . I have ordererd a lamb and chicken donair . Lamb could be sitting in a container over 3-4 hours . It was so hard to chew , i couldnt not taste chicken in it . Paid $19 for a donair and pop .i could not eat it this picture is from next day .","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPw2eN5Ue00JETgO7vhlFBn1mH4KZHA5VusxVYv&fid=0x0:0x1eb5beeadc5f6d94"],"When":"2024-9-11"},{"Name":"Anisha W","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIqbmz6zzhfqCQOs58USL4ko_5KmB6oxtGvrM59_uBGyLTnzw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"I have been going to this spot for the past 6 years and have slowly been getting disappointed. Once in a while we get plates and they employees are always accomdating to any requests. Over the years the service has been decling with not even a hello or welcome. I ordered a plate last week and was so impressed the employee was such a happy bubbly women and she made sure the plate was worth the money. Tonight I asked my husband to go grab me a plate and oh boy not the same at all. New recipe for rice doesn't taste like anything just yellow rice. The chicken was dry and hard and the employee really did the bare minimum in portions. Half of what I got last week and usually this meal is filling but that was not the case this time. For 40 dollars absolutely not worth it, I feel robbed.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Steven McGuire","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVwk4yL8ADxf1nn8jtTMY0Wbicd3mmQ1BUZChNu9aNkqMmz8P0h=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"My hopes were crushed. I used to come to this place everyday on my way home from work and then I moved to the island so I have not been back in 5 years. It was awful, the chicken was so dry with lots of hard bits it it. Hard bits I showed the employee Incould break it with my fingers, it was barely eatable,  the Tzatziti sauce was flavourless. I didn‚Äôt even finish it, I showed the employee (who was lovely) and threw the uneaten half in the trash where it belonged. Very disappointing.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Naomi Buell","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUotaVk5VePwJw6IFKgqgBs_7nhWGabqBeoMhbLeq1jV8h0xRI6=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I'm surprised the ratings are not higher. [{"Name":"Danial Emamhosseini","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjW5yG-bMHoqbxyxcViS4vlLPGdzC7_8fQszfYP-souswf40xgFM=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I'm completely satisfied with this restaurant. The food is amazing, the staff is respectful and caring, and the LCD on the tables provides privacy. I highly recommend it. Parking is limited, but there's usually space in the alley at night.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMs2nmtwyZwdxKpWIrIGtxOyZun_XliAxLf6pqn&fid=0x0:0x1432aadab69bcbfe"],"When":"2024-10-23"},{"Name":"Leonardo Rivera (lleoz)","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWe7CkIlkhoBQ5QGgf4HV7MqdboSxIKdvaoSX9xANHBEMj9IGUsvw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"This restaurant is a culinary experience that you simply can't miss. If you're a meat lover, you'll find the most delicious pork you've ever tasted here. The flavor and texture are exceptional, and the presentation is elegant and carefully detailed. But that's not all, the Korean chicken is spectacular, with its seasoning and use of fresh ingredients making it truly unique. If you're into trying different flavors, this dish will definitely surprise you.

The service at this restaurant is friendly and quick, with staff willing to offer recommendations and guidance in selecting dishes. The decor is elegant and cozy, with a welcoming and relaxed atmosphere.

In summary, this restaurant is an excellent choice for enjoying a unique gastronomic experience. The quality of the food, friendly and efficient service, elegant decor, and welcoming ambiance make it a special place you simply can't miss. Without a doubt, a visit to this restaurant will be an unforgettable experience.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMlCQnsJqUyt6gVnyz9CIsu936qGo8eIezA8XpG&fid=0x0:0x1432aadab69bcbfe"],"When":"2023-3-5"},{"Name":"Lalita Junggee","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWk9lM-eyOFL7Io5cwjXYNTHhoykUm-jYn9BIt4NLw9jE_B0bUS=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"The best Korean food in the Marpole region, or even in Vancouver! It's so good that we'll never get enough of it. üåüüçú","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOdJV8SMSmrfLnKszeR76QqXfRHE7NgsminkrTf&fid=0x0:0x1432aadab69bcbfe"],"When":"2024-3-20"},{"Name":"Brittney Yoo","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKYmjiLDNAQSWLBLMlhCVbZAtgPXq1rS2Tob6gPAhqChDnUpMg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I give 4.5 stars because the pork rib with cheese is not the best, I have never had the grilled cheese with meat before and I thought I would like it but the cheese was just too much and too oily.

I love the chicken!! So juicy and large pieces too. Medium/thin crispy outside and even the fully coated flavour ones is still crispy.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNBY1_Us8Vgng3fpBDmsoBJdKRhTvzYyEJih_vk&fid=0x0:0x1432aadab69bcbfe"],"When":"2021-8-14"},{"Name":"Teguh Sam","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVWuoS0hMBC0Udj0ShJj2PokwQNls9sshW5Y6g9R9lBMKzDSm0=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"The portion of the chicken were good and the inside were very juicy.

Good portions fast service. Not too busy a location. One of the better choices in the neighbourhood.
The fried chicken has a very light crispy texture very tasty.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOAW0mY4C1CVtIL7WyUfDZA_uZV6JSbpDPzUb6G&fid=0x0:0x1432aadab69bcbfe"],"When":"2022-8-17"},{"Name":"Chris Chien","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKhGZrwc0b0pYZO9yUdtOubsx6Ni9bbVGoqEaDB-QRtcKr3SQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Delicious meal, will come back again for more different dishes.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPzevmsEb8wSNvfVaTRMj5wu-ZI4_Nk8zNq14hw&fid=0x0:0x1432aadab69bcbfe"],"When":"2024-9-8"}]

Every time I visit, it never fails to impress me with its exceptional taste and outstanding quality. One of the highlights of this place is that they serve food until midnight, making it a convenient choice for late-night cravings. The variety of options available is incredible, allowing you to customize your pasta with your preferred type, ingredients, and sauce. The portion sizes are generous, and the price is definitely worth it because you can enjoy it over two meals. Personally, I usually have half for dinner and save the rest for lunch the next day. The aroma of the pasta always catches the attention of my coworkers, who are curious about my delicious lunch. I highly recommend giving this place a try; you won't be disappointed!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNvZs3gjR6kvXVNhPW6hGELU7OyzWfJ2D93Rmu8&fid=0x0:0xff014f30ac2d834a"],"When":"2024-3-22"},{"Name":"Iman Sh","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWY_It5dFbhJ3ahD3y8wnnvsyYECBdVwU0ipYiueTLf-0IgvGbE=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"[First Try, 2024, Aug 16]
I ordered Rosa with shell pasta without any protein. It was delicious. They added a shot of Parmesan, which made the pasta nice, and it was a nice touch that they gave it separately. The portion was enough for one person. The sauce-to-pasta ratio was good. I enjoyed the whole dish and how they presented it‚Äîthe packaging, etc. Comparing the price, it‚Äôs 5/5. My next target is their Alfredo. üçù üòã","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMFuQ9cqLHny7L6mTt6dn2-2u-3ZVVqTwDYO6OD&fid=0x0:0xff014f30ac2d834a"],"When":"2024-8-17"},{"Name":"Sofia","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjU3DifFwDMTB58GBwUcG7HSGccjUCVlplE2gzWFv3JhMyR4mjDT=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"It‚Äôs rare to find a place that‚Äôs so generous with their sauce, which is one of the reasons I keep coming back. The flavors were ok, and the lady who was cooking did an excellent job.

However, there's significant room for improvement in customer service and professionalism. While the food was great, the staff seemed too focused on their own conversations and were being playful instead of attentive. The gentleman working seemed particularly distracted with personal matters, and he didn‚Äôt seem to take his job as seriously as he should. I also noticed a weird smell from the staff, which was off-putting. I understand that the kitchen gets hot and people get sweaty, but cleanliness is crucial in a professional setting. Unfortunately, I didn‚Äôt feel welcome at all.

If they can enhance their professionalism, maintain better hygiene, and make customers feel more valued, Solo Pasta would be an even better place to enjoy a meal.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipORHcmMX9YVWdrrB68PuzK6-jyyfTW967ThJxOr&fid=0x0:0xff014f30ac2d834a"],"When":"2024-8-28"},{"Name":"Gholamreza Mohammady","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjU4ImBFJEQhOHqcyCvSVQNwpgPmNHjkex-ldiPIFt2Xmamj_KeqGA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Solo Pasta: A Hidden Gem Serving Up Fresh, Homemade Pasta Delights

‚òÖ‚òÖ‚òÖ‚òÖ‚òÖ

Stumbling upon Solo Pasta on Granville Street was a delightful surprise.  The first thing that caught my attention was the sight of their pasta being made fresh in-store.  This meant that I was in for a truly authentic and homemade pasta experience, and I wasn't disappointed.

I opted for their fettuccine with their special tomato sauce, and it was an absolute masterpiece. The pasta was cooked to perfection, tender yet with a slight bite, and the sauce was rich, flavorful, and bursting with fresh ingredients. The portion size was incredibly generous ‚Äì I was full after finishing my meal, but it could easily have satisfied two people.

Their menu boasts a variety of other tempting sauces, and I'm already planning my next visit to sample them. In a neighborhood filled with the usual pizza and fast food options, Solo Pasta is a true gem.

In terms of the pasta itself, I can confidently say that it's the best I've had in the city. The taste was exquisite, the freshness was undeniable, and the aroma of Parmesan was simply irresistible.

The prices were surprisingly reasonable, considering the quality and quantity of food.  The service was also friendly and attentive, adding to the overall enjoyable experience.

If you're looking for an authentic Italian dining experience with fresh, homemade pasta, look no further than Solo Pasta. It's a hidden gem that deserves to be discovered and savored.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipP5DZ93yIHIyO1ahx8ke1sq3L9pedQ32fZMqsJ0&fid=0x0:0xff014f30ac2d834a"],"When":"2024-6-14"},{"Name":"Danny Yang","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWxoZeEyCdafS7zyhvbA9dUEwTC3QHyZf_zDQ51ZGivW3OY-m0bPw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"I'm actually a bit bewildered at the ratings of this place. We gave this place not 1, but 3 tries just to rule out any potential one-offs, but unfortunately, the food was consistently bland. Most recently, we ordered the pesto pasta and the only thing I could taste is perhaps the cheese. The texture of the pasta is decent, but despite seeing the pesto sauce, it had 0 taste to it. I really wanted to like this place as I normally enjoy small Italian takeout places, but unfortunately, this one simply does not meet the bar, at all.","Images":null,"When":""}]

user_reviews:
[{"Name":"Falguni P","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUQZ6ZBOjhcVWy-h1DxPlyLnjH8S-JVEnkqsZKXOVa_-wFjLST_=s120-c-rp-mo-ba7-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Visited her to try their Iconic Blizzard ice cream!
I ordered a strawberry cheesecake which was loaded with cheesecake pieces and delicious berry compote, the sweetness was perfect.
I also tried their choco brownie extreme, it was the best! Very rich and decadent chocolate flavour with loads of brownie pieces.

The place had amazing and cute options of ice cream cakes with different cartoons as well as simple design and custom ice cream cakes looked great as well.

They have good seating area but the place need a little maintenance.
The staff is polite and quick.

The place is wheelchair friendly ‚ôø‚úÖ
Prices are reasonable for the quality and quantity of ice cream they offer.

I also loved the part that they featured artwork auction to help gather funds for BC children's hospital.

They also offered take-away deals of ice cream treats box, where we can donate for local children's hospital and receive a free box of treats.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMV5Ib_ZUgATRFTTlxRQ1MRIUwqF01E21JsZe8Y&fid=0x0:0xb4046c5efc434763"],"When":"2024-8-30"},{"Name":"Khaled Saif","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXT9kwxHTC0uHGB4Gpgsy3rp29zqxoXLVvJksOs8Ce9O4_Hq8M0=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Honestly this was my first time in this location and will be my last. The closing team was extremely rude to us while we were in the middle of eating. I understand they close at 9.30 on a sunday (they locked the front gate at 9.20pm) but you can politely ask us to wrap up soon or a kind warning before we started eating (so that we would take away the food). My wife was just in the middle of biting her food and the indian girl came up to her and said ‚Äúsorry guys we‚Äôre closed‚Äù with a very odd face. My wife and I felt really embarrassed. There were other people dining as well and she addressed us all to take the rear exit and leave. What kind of service is this ? Every one of us inside the place felt really awkward and felt like being kicked out.

Honestly this was not expected at all and I am recommending every one I know not to visit this location. The restaurant was not clean at all, nor the employees were friendly. The cashier/server even forgot about my drinks.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOYYykS64ZmpNcMpvpVF3RTUj_kNovmYN7bfzCY&fid=0x0:0xb4046c5efc434763"],"When":"2024-12-9"},{"Name":"Dusty Engels","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocL9yM7geXKnH9WtrbWXZjEjdfa5--QLTeUoh1mMTl_DhpIfDQ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"The service was good friendly and all, but my burger was super gross to the point I‚Äôm writing about it I returned it got another one and it was greasy and just gelatinous cheese. Bottom line I go to a lot of locations and this one is lacking maybe a webinar with your franchise host to go over how to prepare burgers and how much ketchup and mustard.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Harran Shi","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVposYwd6J2dlDeYCSGnh3ME_dZtFZ9u3SjpUExJkrlqu62h0dh=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Very gloomy and old inside. Building is worn down. Staff are cold, tired and look overworked. So impressed and grateful","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Candice Hilliker","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjV5B-lcDZCmzkh9z2yn_sszqoeiFXAZFBqdyVDWrRLAqvASMB48jA=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"Did not complete requested instructions for removed items on food. Despite living closest to the Kitsilano Dairy Queen,    if my mom  (or myself)   want to get a box of buster bars   or  a  frozen  DQ cake.....I almost always make the trek to this location,   as I think the owner is doing a great job and appreciate that  he's looking after this customers and restaurant","Images":null,"When":""}]

The chicken was half raw, really poor quality","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPgfW3u8KMnFUsKLtiu2NjrwVobngzEzPJP7x9o&fid=0x0:0xdccfb8ae670e0c60"],"When":"2024-12-21"},{"Name":"Joey Lam","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIncJBLfbVzRO24PRdfxE4-hovZn6C_s4RV_vqsGslULP8YEA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"We were here to try the long cheese burger. It was not bad. However, I felt a bit disturbed during my time dining in that evening.

I saw a middle-aged Chinese man came in and bought something. Then he checked the order and showed something in the bag to the server. Apparently, his ability to communicate in English was limited to convey exactly what he wanted to say. No one worked that evening was Chinese, so it made the communication challenging.

If I had to make an educational guess, the man was given something not what he wanted to order. It was because one of the worker kept yelling at him something like this was what you ordered, no, you had to go.

I did not understand why it was such a big deal to make a scene. When I started to think i should go forward and help, the man left with frustration.

All food we ordered was okay, I would come back if I did not witness this experience.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNb6O9u8s-DJSCdvD75H7OT0FZ42VSnqddM3HX0&fid=0x0:0xdccfb8ae670e0c60"],"When":"2024-6-12"},{"Name":"MIGUEL MARTINEZ CEJA","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUztjwBaMsNtjBzVBFRcaUJ7t1cbUF1T1cS_N4MiFB5Ow65fUsX=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Are you tired of paying so much for your small size McDonald's meals. Absolutely disgusting. The entire thing was just swimming in oil.
You‚Äôre only as good as your employees, in which case you are garbage
What is the main problem with training? Are you afraid that they will spit in the food if you start holding them accountable when it comes to quality presentation?
Threw then out behind the nearby Costco for the raccoons to binge on","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Saffiyah K","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIoJFPB3UElzfFzgmtLAW8kHDStnnUR5JsiUwXk66DnEy17UnYN=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Disappointed. user_reviews:
[{"Name":"rwpow","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIMZHZZy8yLkw6tffki855GmumW3XF5y9VuOp9bQBP0R4GbNg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"I recently ordered food online and requested delivery. When the food arrived, it was delivered by a cyclist. Unfortunately, everything was stone cold when we got it, and the bag was not wet but felt damp. I would like to have the option to choose that my food is delivered by car or at least have the option to chose. If I wasn't feeling so lazy and just wanted to stay home on Christmas day, I would have just picked it up myself. I could have driven there and picked it up in half the time that it took to have it delivered on a bicycle. I ordered two regular Cokes, but both of them were Diet Coke, which is disgusting. Also, why does the app divert the order to a McDonald's that is further away? There are two McDonald's within a half a kilometer of my location, but the app chose to deliver from one that is 5 km away???

The burger looked like it had been sat on, the Mcnuggets were stone cold, and the fries were not fresh. I was surprised because I have driven to this McDonald's many times and always gotten home with hot fries.

Deliver fee $3.99
Service Fee $2.66
Courier Tip $ 4.79

Payed a premium for this type of service, $11.44 in fees ????","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNxSJF868qTX-S6EQxBmrBtmfEQfw15KpFEA8FK&fid=0x0:0xbd71c75a4354d4eb"],"When":"2024-12-26"},{"Name":"Miss Mouse","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWB97BLtSpQNZucNiBH6GaIGB8dF8nLk6uxajImUVEd_fpSgyAU=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I haven't had McDonald's for 5 years.  Stopped in today on a whim to eat inside.  The Big Mac combo was hot, fresh, and loaded.  Fries hot and salty.  Coke fizzy and cold.  The restaurant was immaculately clean.  Security a constant presence.  It was worthy of making a good Google review!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNpPNwOBn_xuzEKhzGOWpBU3mTJdVbAX7fPOMWh&fid=0x0:0xbd71c75a4354d4eb"],"When":"2024-11-19"},{"Name":"Thomas","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUI2GSqvzKBZrX86jhtU8WjOUfxMIP7NMYhzhHKU7b9i8Vnl3COxw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba8-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"Same food as at other Mc Donald's.
Poor attention: we ordered to have the food delivered at our table.
After aprox 15 min of waiting we went to the front counter to find out that th order still hasn't been completed.
The fries and the burger were already cold; the coffee hot.
The staff didn't really care or did something to speed attention up. Too relaxed - not customer driven.
But the coffee was good - also the Mc Sundae.
Wooden/ecological spoons - but still lots of plastics.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOI2Q8Fo2jmdXwbAKdvviJVcfU1W4om4a4F98fr&fid=0x0:0xbd71c75a4354d4eb"],"When":"2024-7-18"},{"Name":"Cassidy Benson","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWOWk7Z_BvZUKzFKgu1xQSX3SzfkvqX_klyMwLB3tOBqEMkGHbL_w=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Attended a besties party after party here and was blessed to see DJ Grimace spin some tunes! Great event hosted by McDonald's. They had a photo booth, lots of bracelets and merch, and opportunities to take a photo with Grimace and Birdie.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPNQ_v_OtVf3AnINiQm2m7oahMTfuCP7H6s4tgS&fid=0x0:0xbd71c75a4354d4eb"],"When":"2024-12-7"},{"Name":"Capili Mia Carryl","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVVpTKvFe7zslLVuMQRMZ1z1IXMXQ4nr-mc-Ll0bUGtowQHZEzJ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I always appreciate McDonald‚Äôs for their variety. Whether I‚Äôm craving a burger, nuggets, or breakfast food, they‚Äôve got something for every mood. The McFlurry is also a sweet treat that never disappoints, and the fact that they introduce seasonal items keeps things interesting. Their drive-thru service is efficient, which is perfect when I‚Äôm in a hurry. I also like their app because it offers discounts and deals that help save money. For a quick bite with familiar flavors, McDonald‚Äôs is a solid option that delivers quality fast food in no time.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOvsqmeOZ-plH2ID3-_B_Y7yUf8kU_yWxHm9BoE&fid=0x0:0xbd71c75a4354d4eb"],"When":"2024-9-30"},{"Name":"Shinn Inagaki","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIpF1gPQ6II9FjL7HoACMWpgmrVznxivHZdomkvTJ9wRIkWHw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"Oldest McDonald‚Äôs in DT Vancouver is going away sometimes in December 2024.
This place has a security officer who has hand cuffs and not really safe.  üò≠üò≠üò≠","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPHPGhqyzqtrkEVMp6B6nF40zjRE5FZJ4jBGak&fid=0x0:0xbd71c75a4354d4eb"],"When":"2024-9-28"},{"Name":"Simranjit singh","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJcdOBXxAQPNgHVb61nnpVIE1pcdaHSBGWFqBPkP1neW-9j3w=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"The burger is all messy. This is the 3rd time i got the sandwich like this. This is so frustrating that i order food and got in this condition.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipP6ROuow2RBAClEYxRhvCCWpCulOoEIKoV37HUv&fid=0x0:0xbd71c75a4354d4eb"],"When":"2024-12-22"},{"Name":"Tomasz Jura","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWraPO0j7TKFl4u5Bq62BMPa2eK4GmZIpHY9vm10PB1b_siB9qx9g=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"General recommendation - try to avoid this place.

This is the worst McDonald's I have ever visited, and I have probably been to more than 100 all around the world.
- It is always dirty; I have never seen it clean.

- The food is average, but they often get your order wrong.

- Even if you choose the option to eat in, they give you a to-go bag.

- The waiting time is around 15 minutes, but on several occasions, I have waited for more than 20. This is unacceptable for fast food.

- The staff almost always marks your order as ready very quickly, but when you follow the information on the screen and approach them, they tell you to wait and that they will call your number when it‚Äôs ready.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipO6wIEoIvfi4425qi0DhnQPAGNMp_bxSrTCPxqU&fid=0x0:0xbd71c75a4354d4eb"],"When":"2024-4-8"}]

[{"Name":"Annie Isaak","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXVTCvx41kGYcH72iCQpkHbZFwDH754CPLMluwrDJaO3ZfWn5Y=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"I found this place online and was so excited to come here to eat, but when we walked in the place was crowed with no waiting area. We had to wait about 15 minutes to be seated which was fine however, we then had to wait a full hour for our food. The food was very disappointing. The ‚Äúafter school special‚Äù grilled cheese was flavourless with only mozzarella cheese inside. The lobster Mac and cheese had very few pieces of lobster and portions were very small. Don‚Äôt let the food appearance trick you. It‚Äôs not worth it. Our server was impolite and rushed. We all left here feeling sick from the food and very disappointed. Not worth the money or the wait.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMDeZaDethcvoex3L1A5FderlFEUPwJL9y_ipcX&fid=0x0:0x88666f921cdaba55"],"When":"2024-11-4"},{"Name":"Igor Tasic","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVVDGBnB1WFh39DClYcxlfqJWlD7Rs-J70CZIwxySY9GWxt_SYjZA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"I do think that they really deliver on the cozy vibes and comfort food idea that they market themselves as. The food is good and comforting, the decor is really on point and the service is great. The only criticism I have for this place is that the prices are a bit expensive compared to the food they make. If it were a bit cheaper (particularly the drinks and soups) it would've been 5 instead of four.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNcSJLZApWX02i03n2NuGI3ckTrMqkpVLFb1z9t&fid=0x0:0x88666f921cdaba55"],"When":"2024-11-4"},{"Name":"Lydia X.","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjViT0kOTUfe-14sI-XZzuSAMJ11zLMz2yRFRP-Y15rc4maS4qQo=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Very cozy vibes, perfect for a catchup with friends on a cold winter day. There's limited seating and it can be a long wait during oeak hours. We appreciated the coat hooks by our table since it wasn't very spacious.

The gooey cheese grillers with dos diablos was delicious. Generous amount of cheese and the chorizo added a wonderful flavour. Sunset corn + chicken was alright, but definitely not standout. The mini mac + cheese was decadent and the perfect comfort food. I would definitely come back again just for that.

The service was decent, she took a little long to get to us at times, but it didn't affect our experience.

Limited paid street parking.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipP7uz9kmcIwDPr4qWnSlwgT6Sz1sKug2kU4MNQq&fid=0x0:0x88666f921cdaba55"],"When":"2024-12-26"},{"Name":"Dee","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXHNcNOPaNMwoQhd4a3MaNl6j5NagLUmPpfBNlw3ukI7k88v9FP=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"I‚Äôm torn because I genuinely wanted to love this place, but sadly the server was the shining star here. He was great but the food was just horrifying in my most honest opinion. The karrage was not very crispy and almost gelatinous on the inside. I ate it because I felt maybe the main dish would be delicious and worth the wait.

But the butter chicken tasted like watery tomato soup, the rice did not have any kind of seasoning (including salt,) and the pita was dry. I didn‚Äôt expect it to be super authentic, but I also didn‚Äôt expect the food to be flavorless‚Ä¶ I picked this place out because of the reviews. And it really disappointed me that it was kind of a fa√ßade. And like I said, I really wanted to love this place. The waiter is so genuinely kind and the restaurant is very cozy and ideal. However, I strongly believe that if you‚Äôre going to have an ethnic dish like butter chicken on the menu‚Ä¶it should be made with some respect.

I won‚Äôt lie, the food presentation was lovely. That flavor though‚Ä¶","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipO-LRwU-KGZ3Oj121nXbw6vzvYxfZ3OE3El61MD&fid=0x0:0x88666f921cdaba55"],"When":"2024-8-27"},{"Name":"Jhk 727","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXRlpzpCG0lmTiswrjxl92nKs9mapw2VnKHEXcy00upiXVnodNCJA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Had the beef bourguigon and bistro salad with a few sides. Stingy on beef to be honest - mushrooms were the main here. Tasted a little light (not enough reduction). Salad was mid, nothing special and head scratching value at 16 dollars. Excellent service along with pleasant atmosphere did the job though. Would come again for a date, where eating would be secondary.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipP9J7I82ceWDiNYjtXfJZyx01rt28m0eO7l8AO7&fid=0x0:0x88666f921cdaba55"],"When":"2024-7-12"},{"Name":"Khasha Shariati","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjW9BRwWPJBkIcOPMqU92TxMjsbdN__O-S3D_jQsct6oG5_sIP8Z=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"The atmosphere is awesome and goes well with the type of comfort food. The food quality is great and worth the wait time, previous reservation is highly recommended","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOYyOLzBnl8sULbxYBx7TGNGrqhcEjHYBSJiNiC&fid=0x0:0x88666f921cdaba55"],"When":"2024-11-3"},{"Name":"Ka Tsun Wan","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXOatRF2LA4thVdUPna9_1ek2utrcSSMqAz-MY7eZLaBTHk7_wS=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"I usually eat in the other burgoo branch, like the one in point grey. Today I was craving their butter chicken but then point grey‚Äôs ubereat shop closes earlier, so I had to order from mount pleasant. I had to say I was so disappointed with this butter chicken I got. It tastes much more bland than the one I usually eat in point grey. The size of takeout is not even the same as the dine in plate but it‚Äôs more expensive by 2 dollars, excluding ubereat charges and tip. I only had a spoon in the photo, you can see there‚Äôs not much. The quality variance is out of my expectation.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNNHcGac6E1pLsfdY7EFhQL07eoJ3_QbcVdr5Dz&fid=0x0:0x88666f921cdaba55"],"When":"2024-11-19"},{"Name":"Tanvir Biki","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjV-dheStmXZJ4Tti0jxdMC4cCoQscxwxtzKNNKNS5xRCTWOMKgN=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Went to try to Beef bourguignon, love the taste. Great size for value. Good for one person. If you are more foody than go with the onion soup and this plate. You won‚Äôt get disappointed, the food was tasty and had a happy hour wine. Taste good and the mashed potatoes were smooth and very tasty.
Although I don‚Äôt eat pork or bacon they were kind enough to make it without.
Thank you","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNtLmbw2gYV6Ej6wzWd-LjTFKoCbHMwfRTAKxlf&fid=0x0:0x88666f921cdaba55"],"When":"2024-7-14"}]

[{"Name":"Dana Sullivan","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWQIw-0oOUNgoyniYugTscGkgpKJS8tpx4V0tAajn3ZGkNIfqEk=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"This is a popular Mount Pleasant vegetarian burrito/taco restaurant, and a good alternative to the big brand name burrito joints for plant-inclined eaters. The staff are very cool as is the vibe.
I've tried a few things here: the Johnny O, Blair Stanley, Jo June, and Poser in either burrito or bowl form, and also the vegan chocolate chip cookie they offer. The Poser so far is the clear winner - the ground round was nicely seasoned. Jo June was alright but blander than expected given that it's made with stewed poblano peppers. I did really like the Johnny O, but the chipotle sour cream is what ties it together, so I‚Äôm not sure if the vegan version would hit the same. In general, the burritos/bowls lean toward the ‚Äústuff thrown in a bowl together" vibe rather than a cohesive dish to me. It's okay but not something I'd crave. Similarly, the cookie was fine but didn‚Äôt wow me. I probably wouldn‚Äôt get it again, but I just don‚Äôt care for chocolate chip that much unless it‚Äôs got something special about it. All that being said, I am willing to go back and keep exploring the menu to see if I find something that really speaks to me.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNkYsZGBSaxy2PiRBOMTnqmSivDeGrGKCbMlTZZ&fid=0x0:0xef86884cf35923d5"],"When":"2024-8-3"},{"Name":"Frank S.","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXszoVxoGs2VKeFIl31zJDEGnCub412s6iYyLf2VmABfS8AId1H=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"I have to admit upon going in I didn‚Äôt expect a whole lot but I had a good experience. Washrooms were pretty clean, they were friendly and the decor was urban stylish. I‚Äôm not a vegetarian so I ordered the Poser which tasted good and there was a lot of garlic in it which I enjoyed. They played neat 80‚Äôs rap music while I was there which wasn‚Äôt too loud and enjoyable. I‚Äôll be going back.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Chloe M","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXr8JKvX5uvV5LemrDd7roHWUvC8Oej6WDibmPj3O5qOcy5rD9c=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"This has been me and my husband's favorite place for about 9 years now. All vegetarian options can be made vegan and the most flavorful, fulfilling and satisfying flavors in a burrito you will ever get. I'm vegetarian leaning towards vegan but my husband is an absolute carnivore and he was the one who showed me this place and now it's our spot. Over the years they have also made the atmosphere more cozy and warm and it's just a cool vibe overall. It's honestly one of the best kept secrets and I really wanna keep it that way. I always get the Blaire Stanley made vegan and my husband gets the Johnny O (make sure to ask for a side of their sauces, the chili oil and Verde sauce are the best IMO üëå). I also love that they give you options of tortilla, beans, Lettuce and sauces. i cant say enough good things, I LOVE LOVE LOVE BUDGIES  and it will always be my favorite burrito place over all the places. Everyone we bring loves it too vegetarian and meat eaters alike!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNRW6do3YxtFQ5_TcySrZq6Oz5odIdH4KTz-GvJ&fid=0x0:0xef86884cf35923d5"],"When":"2024-3-31"},{"Name":"Chloe Rachel","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWgExGuK1W-XgQc1tPnrQlqQkWxCTaNhdz977uVTTY3zjpsAzs-=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"The Plant Curious book brought me here for the first time! Favourite was the Jamedog burrito bowl (GF option) for the garlic and lime roasted potatoes. The guacamole is a worthy $2 add on! They were able to exclude certain items due to ingredient sensitivities. The burritos are $13.50 regular price, and they're massive! Very filling and packed with ingredients between the rice, beans, and protein. 1 burrito could be split into 2 meals easily. The only critique I had was the cabbage is relatively dry by itself, and definitely needs a sauce or sour cream (or in my case, guacamole) to liven it. Hopefully they are able to offer vegan sour cream in the future!

There was a slight miscommunication on our order and the staff was kind enough to let us keep the item made in error. The interior was retro and colourful (we loved all the details in the seating area downstairs) and the 2 staff members were great and patient! Would definitely come back to this East Van gem!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPBL890lJErA-nOip7LoBjgR-GF6ECu2sMZDVMq&fid=0x0:0xef86884cf35923d5"],"When":"2023-7-6"},{"Name":"Mike Wnuk","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLaH6KqvVWYvMqRnD0Gl4xZTn68vgLAIfxOnW1PRVsT7rgKqw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"First impressions matter, and my inaugural visit to Budgies in Vancouver's Mount Pleasant left an indelible mark. Stepping into the cozy atmosphere, I was greeted by a charming woman behind the counter. Her warm demeanor extended beyond mere hospitality as she graciously offered recommendations, highlighting her personal favorites amidst the myriad of choices.

The allure of Budgies transcends mere sustenance; it's a sanctuary where culinary delights converge. From the tantalizing array of beers to the scrumptious burritos, each offering is a testament to culinary excellence. Yet, amidst the gastronomic symphony, I discovered something more profound ‚Äì a newfound favorite haunt in Mount Pleasant.

In essence, Budgies is not merely a place to dine; it's an experience‚Äîa nexus where simple delectable cuisine meets unparalleled hospitality.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipO-2HZmi4yHfsnkRXtB0vzMklFv9U-8aaep1-4s&fid=0x0:0xef86884cf35923d5"],"When":"2024-4-19"},{"Name":"Josephine Ma","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjW4ctBP8R2rm9S8Aa5NyuULMapTvyTQYakS6AvI9Cd025oSy86H=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"We were on our way to check out a shop on Broadway and since Budgie's Burritos was nearby, I finally got to use my plant based deals coupon for it. My daughter and I both ordered burrito bowls and took them to go. It looks like a cute place and they have seating downstairs as well. Hope that we can eat in the shop itself next time.

My daughter got The Mr. Jones burrito bowl and I got the Jamedog. The Mr. Jones was a pretty basic combination of ingredients. It had rice, beans, vegan cheese , sour cream, salsa, and green cabbage. Jamedog was similar but slightly more complex as it came with a chipotle sour cream, as well as garlic and lime roasted potatoes.

Wow, those potatoes were so good! If I find myself at Budgie's Burritos again I will definitely order the Jamedog again just so I can eat those wonderful garlic and lime roasted potatoes again.

Service: Good
Parking: Mostly paid parking but there is some limited free parking on the street
Location: 44 Kingsway, Vancouver, BC","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPuItwYA7Z99T4FTt01B0u0zmD5QqzorbY_vmA-&fid=0x0:0xef86884cf35923d5"],"When":"2024-4-13"},{"Name":"Justine Roo","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXAQoC1sFgPJ6yj73Syg75podVcnn8oGnLLnNvApy7zcibZmOV4vA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Really good and really affordable. If you're a van local you've driven by this spot a thousand times. It's here waiting for you to try it! Lots of choices and the bowls pack a bunch of flavor. A great spot for almost any dietary restriction or choice.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Alexis Evren Smith","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKZETuSekdlIucy8lsHJsBuCR7PrE5peW3DrJhbDgHfC-0C8A=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Tasty, well priced, no B.S. vegetarian food with mexican-inspired flavours.

I aim to be back here more to save money, eat healthy, be a more responsible eater, and enjoy more delicious food. üíó

I had an RIP taco and it was perfect. The mild salsa was actually mild and I loved it. The staff were lovely. The vibe is chill and there's more seating than I expected downstairs.

They offer everything in vegan, which is rad. As a Coca-Cola lover, I appreciated this small concession made to big corporate capitalism (not many others in this place, as far as I can tell).","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOkaBY48A1rn6kmCyF6BpMBHWOibclo5z1g6MCd&fid=0x0:0xef86884cf35923d5"],"When":"2023-7-7"}]

title: Subway

[{"Name":"Jo-An Okne","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUYTIHbBSb3yr68Yh_CsSKdAITmqtos_iwgeLsolBfP07TuIJRf=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"What a treat to find this place close by. Especially after a long flight/night, the previous day. This was needed and so glad I came in. The items I ordered were excellent. Since I had a hard time deciding, I ordered two items to try, Garden Skillet and a single French Toast on the side. I always have leftovers lol Service was great to boot üëåüèª","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPWozTFWpA9SyfjKErBOQELyMO0UJ9vtBJmsR0D&fid=0x0:0x89cb0cf8b3562f50"],"When":"2024-12-4"},{"Name":"Edward Cheng","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWJ5t1luJWZ0TXirubqGJZ41s6LG2QmSjyD9Fyi7Z2m-eTjmKw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"Clean, well-appointed establishment, with a varied and wide menu, friendly and efficient servers, and food that satisfies...the Hollandaise in my Eggs Benedict was a bit more fluid than expected, and was a touch heavy-handed with the lemon, but it did not overly detract from my enjoyment.

My cream anglaise served with the Waffles and fresh fruit was quite a bit sweeter than our preference.

However, despite the preceding, we would likely return to try some other offerings.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOkcW-_5uYeiDZqWZtnyxrj3Xd7vcAfP72fQpvW&fid=0x0:0x89cb0cf8b3562f50"],"When":"2024-11-3"},{"Name":"Tatyana Ayrapetova","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXhKy-98t6ZdKhPzAFPxODP0Ie3Uo94lXS45JQrA-ha8UeYbax-0w=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"The restaurant focused on breakfast and lunch with a motto of special experience. Unfortunately I have not experienced anything special. Apart from a great service, my breakfast was below average in terms of quality of food and presentation. Eggs had a strong vinegar taste and unattractive layer of fried onions under previously frozen mushy smoked salmon. Crepes were, unfortunately, average as well with a strong smell of eggs. Overall, it is not a bad place to eat, but the kitchen needs a lot of improvement as well as the interior needs some addition of character.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPybfKqudoaKeJwCmatoDQIKlX7xzhNO3EMHmd6&fid=0x0:0x89cb0cf8b3562f50"],"When":"2024-8-21"},{"Name":"Sinyo ganteng","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVK6DhObLW3StVcJ_e9Ph42mdmAq5cSoW-d536hao-jSu7WAn8I=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"Breakfast or brunch, taste okay, just its big portion,skillets is good, fans of morning breakfast, might enjoys varieties of omelet,  skillet, waffles and french toast. Customer services are awesome, great, and serve with a smile. The place is pretty clean, the atmosphere is okay, and it is a bit crowded,  but room design is nice and bright.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMN4qxawIOfLgiCAQD8h2mVHXNvSO3Jdoo9eGa9&fid=0x0:0x89cb0cf8b3562f50"],"When":"2024-10-28"},{"Name":"Anna Capetillo","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIGnUICJf8jIdM41Y125lgIvSbhvgR_65c6vqMbLKdtNxbyXA=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"This place was AMAZING!!   I ordered the veggie skillet and added a protein.  Awesome.  Husband had the Canadian and said his plate was awesome.  My sister in law had a beautifully plated waffle topped with fruit.  The food here is so delicious and the staff (Bir) was very attentive and patient with our large party.  I highly recommend eating here.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNI5onrbb-8iJ99FmIsRfe4Bg0Uf6-i5ckjl-RP&fid=0x0:0x89cb0cf8b3562f50"],"When":"2024-7-13"},{"Name":"Maria Anna De Guzman","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJzXV1Lxm1oG9rHxIoo5NB1wIe1GTYUo6gjo1zaXY8-6A9llw=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Food was really good. I had the Canadian with Oh la la crepe which was perfect and my partner had fruits and waffles. The crepe was not too sweet but enough to satisfy sweet tooth cravings, bacon and sauce was really yummy. Potatoes could be crunchier but still good. Shout out also to Gurjeet for the outstanding service! Will be back.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipP8_wugTYLlq85MDZBeEjYmFSp7aAf9gCeBkWXN&fid=0x0:0x89cb0cf8b3562f50"],"When":"2024-8-4"},{"Name":"A F","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWYDMu7IeDJChdBgePrvV70PPcEHKO5R1jLykC_1m8QqAsxTREL=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Never write a review but this place is awesome! The food come out identical to what the pictures show. This definitely doesn‚Äôt happen at every restaurant. Food came out hot and tasted amazing. Our server Asfa was very pleasant and tentative to our table. We will definitely return! Thank you! ‚≠êÔ∏è","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMsOx2dflZH7H7nJ9CUuBtWnWQcPKug09f89R1L&fid=0x0:0x89cb0cf8b3562f50"],"When":"2024-10-26"},{"Name":"Liza","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUU6psZuYm5issGPqVIywDJmiQmgvYke0cz4aCVVktU9NoaykdJkA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"It was a good experience. The place is very spacious with a lot of breakfast options on the menu. My vanilla coffee was too sweet and the food was fine, but nothing special. However, the atmosphere was inviting and made me feel like I wanted to come back and give it another try. Overall, it is a solid 4 stars.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipN9cxiRTV8WmygzGdzOG_SssIZ5PO-Ltn9W-49d&fid=0x0:0x89cb0cf8b3562f50"],"When":"2024-10-7"}]

[{"Name":"Earl Flormata","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUHEYR5crfzT5mFZF5yY6PmVwTawXCmDPm3U8WVZUqH5mb8rOP9MA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We ran a networking event in the back room and had an absolute blast. Lily was our server and she was straight up amazing. Super courteous and professional - and her recommendation of nachos was spot on.

25 people showed up for speed networking and had a fantastic time. We‚Äôre definitely fans and would love to come back.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipN-UTpwjthoTmRWekFa_St_kTOC3Hk8_agGbuBB&fid=0x0:0xfffdfc7b43c2d16f"],"When":"2024-7-30"},{"Name":"Sandy Y. (CameraGourmet)","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJQ9J8ig1HwUQBJbXRdKDIwR0OrTw3YtQtyHDEaRuCN8XnUDg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Steamworks at Mount Pleasant is a fantastic spot for unwinding after a long workday, especially if you‚Äôre into beer and casual social gatherings.  Each location of Steamworks has its own menu, and this one didn‚Äôt disappoint!
We visited during Happy Hour, which is a big plus since they offer it every day!  The Happy Hour menu has a decent selection of food and beers, making it a solid place to grab some drinks and snacks with friends.  You can check their website for details, but trust me, it‚Äôs worth it.
The patio is pet-friendly, which was a nice surprise, so we got to dine with our furry friend while enjoying the laid-back atmosphere.  The space is larger than it looks from the outside‚Äîplenty of room to relax.  The vibe is a classic pub setting, though the music can be a bit on the louder side, so keep that in mind.
Another great perk is the Costco gift card deal!  We spent $80 to get a $100 gift card and were happy to learn that we could use it during Happy Hour as well.  Overall, it‚Äôs a great hangout spot with a welcoming vibe.  Definitely will be back!

We did get a warning about everyone showing up on time. We ordered a lot of drinks and appetizers. They were kinda classic pub food and tasted good. Sitting on the patio had a nice breeze but the view of the empty lot seemed just ok","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMFH3i_ZPH5ECg4D3owUvdeFwBPSoKRmz6zz0iS&fid=0x0:0xfffdfc7b43c2d16f"],"When":"2024-6-11"},{"Name":"Spike Luk","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVljR41LewaD1cz5kVqUD3bmc9ybJSH00GIF-DrHusS8cKNejJe=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"First of all it‚Äôs great to have another dog friendly patio on Main.  The atmosphere is perfect for a casual get together with friends.  We didn‚Äôt drink today because it was early and I was on call.   We ordered some deep fried pickles and they were well battered and crispy.   It would have been nice with an IPA.  The jack fruit cerviche had great flavor‚Äôs.  Unfortunately it was served  like a soup.  Some of sauce(brine) should have been removed.  It made it difficult to scoop up the jack fruit and other ingredients with the nachos.  The chips were well made!
The cheeseburger was good.  The fries crispy but a little too salty.
Overall I look forward to coming back with my pup and having a brew with my meal next time.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMiWlHaL0GrrmvscavYq_Wy7-FnfYRSbXEiteRg&fid=0x0:0xfffdfc7b43c2d16f"],"When":"2024-3-31"},{"Name":"Viola Cohen","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWJP5sfHeOIOYvng7DC5P8yQBaeVdvy6VPI0OU3Ana9Y-VYgsPP=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"When my Brewer‚Äôs breakfast arrived with hot sauce slathered all over the avocado, the waiter had a real problem when I told him sorry, I don‚Äôt eat hot sauce. He huffily took the plate away and when he returned, I told him the menu doesn‚Äôt say that hot sauce is part of the meal. He said, ‚ÄúYeah we wouldn‚Äôt do that,‚Äù and then he walked away without even giving me the chance to say anything. If you don‚Äôt list the included condiments on your menu, don‚Äôt be surprised if the customer (who is eating plus paying for this meal) sends the meal back to the kitchen. I really don‚Äôt like hot sauce, ok? Don‚Äôt be a dick about it because you have to make an extra trip to the kitchen. Last I checked that‚Äôs a waiter‚Äôs job! The food itself wasn‚Äôt that great - the eggs were runny and I didn‚Äôt enjoy the sausage, so I unfortunately only ate half.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOsBailR7RnR-I5F_qnqlMBFiexpiY5T7FvpXZi&fid=0x0:0xfffdfc7b43c2d16f"],"When":"2024-9-18"},{"Name":"Sarah Miller","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUjlNoPvyL4WeimqpsKY7XLLF1otvX35I_rOkeXYhYzBMVR0Zd4Bw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Very nice, very new. Service was great. Very large beautiful dog friendly patio. The vibes were great and the food was yummy. Would recommend the donut holes.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOWojcAoM-UhLDJGPRxuhClLAKBxl8Y-BLRmBbp&fid=0x0:0xfffdfc7b43c2d16f"],"When":"2024-8-9"},{"Name":"Denny Hui","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXuGFgsc9U61TCKDV21ZHXILH-aGrlI-hjZswBeAYg3LhKf97Y3=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"Went on a date with my wife to check out Steamworks Mount Pleasant. Restaurant is a fair size with a big patio. Overall decor was good.

We had high expectations that food would be similar to the one in Gastown.  Very disappointed, no seafood or steak. Only seafood was fish n chips. Food was more pub style. So all we ordered were just starters and a few drinks.

Service was OK but the hostess last night was very nice, friendly and helping out where she could.

Atmosphere was ok, music was loud and played more electric house style.   Not really something I want to listen too when dining out. But that's just my preference.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPtgmjNTpZ4Zx713y5_9g5nVjulX5M7WKrEUvti&fid=0x0:0xfffdfc7b43c2d16f"],"When":"2024-2-11"},{"Name":"Cody Gibson","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVMpuaFaWAVP5czfa2WTIiKSb2tIzdCzPNPZ_llKsoeAoZ1Angc=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Dog friendly patio!! We brought 3 golden retrievers for brunch and they loved it! Lots of space under the table for them and big water bowls provided.

The food and service is also really good!

A great place to hang out for a couple hours and enjoy the sunshine!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOJkbcsTXNdGbrRuKcncBEeJSVsfLFbBpSELht_&fid=0x0:0xfffdfc7b43c2d16f"],"When":"2023-5-31"}]

Hope they learn how to treat customer.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Manav Grover","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUpQujOpbM_IWPhgNxBOdl1xJm9-1HRJZB-M26WHiEWWJuZ0S2jiw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I recently visited a burrito restaurant and was blown away by the delicious food and friendly staff. The tofu bowl was loaded with fresh veggies, and the sauce with the fried tofu was a hit. Plus, the portions were generous for the price!
My ultimate fave was definitely the butter chicken. it came with nan bread and rice, and man, it was the best butter chicken ever!
And let's not forget the Oreo shake, it was so good, that I couldn't put it down.
Also the owner couple is the loveliest ever. They are very warm and fiendly‚ù§Ô∏è
Can't wait to go back and try more from their menu!!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipM0Ybgg53NmifqVS8memvYclMTkMKBNDZ-hJiHE&fid=0x0:0x93f239faec17aabb"],"When":"2024-4-28"},{"Name":"Sukhpreet Singh","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLvVL6aC2qJ5ayDF1Sag7jA-r8ZAHhJNBwmeMWPf-TpCbok5g=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I can't say enough good things about 'Behind You'! This restaurant has quickly become my daily go-to spot. Mahesh, the owner, goes above and beyond to create customized indian style meals that are absolutely delicious. Working nearby, I appreciate the convenience and the warm, welcoming atmosphere every time I visit. If you're in the area and craving good food - vegetarian or non- vegetarian, 'Behind You' is a must-try!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPWJ5Yc2AdizpqQG-kjASCYwfo_DUxpZJOJ2KxG&fid=0x0:0x93f239faec17aabb"],"When":"2024-7-15"},{"Name":"Kirti Zunza","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLBNmZKJ2Z_Ak_fc1bV2fuy7ieWiRiWidKJifQBzWqrQgE9sQ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I came here with my family for lunch. We had Crispy cauli bowl, yam fries, and veg quesdillas. Everything was delicious and the staff was also very friendly. Highly recommended !!! Will definitely visit again to try other things.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipN6QGyOhjckpROzMPaWkPbYWyCF1PTuZ0pjEGa-&fid=0x0:0x93f239faec17aabb"],"When":"2024-5-25"},{"Name":"Ken Wong","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVT8za5P0BYxAAS85JwBqJWBq5wdtPBjHZGyrJW9-cMRXFgPHzU=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I had the Chicken Masala Rice. Lots of chicken, great flavour and spice level, crispy papadam. The lemon wedge is a nice touch. The bowl is deceptively large. I've had fried rice from Chinese restaurants and been able to finish them easily. Maybe Behind You's containers are a little wider or deeper or piled higher, but it felt like a lot of food. I was full 75% of the way through.

The owners/staff are really nice. They came to check up with me, to make sure the food is to my liking. Which is unheard of in a mall food court. The surprised look on my face was for that reason. Great food, large quantity, exceptional service and a fair price. I will definitely go back. They have a diverse and eclectic menu including sandwiches, wraps and pastas. I want to try several of their items.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMAbBWW9GHPTUCrzeOYnvadLl9RBsnWIfJFKiOG&fid=0x0:0x93f239faec17aabb"],"When":"2024-6-10"}]

[{"Name":"eddy wong","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX8Fjpj3y8teHQ4LqbC4PHR8whbU4-XOrTXEwklI9bGRqZLRD20=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"This location use to be amazing. I would have car nights here with other members online. Now that I‚Äôve grown up and moved out of the North Shore there are times that you miss that nostalgia from the years growing up.

It has been YEARS since I came back to this location. Not sure what‚Äôs going on with Vancouver in general but I‚Äôve had some recent bad experiences with service workers lately in fast food chains. Not as friendly and never any thank you. No napkins or straws or eating utensils in the bags.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNa22F7n-vRaUQkfV0AfL12ZMDzW1bfZPqzcY3n&fid=0x0:0xa5192350e0a75f1f"],"When":"2024-9-29"},{"Name":"Dave","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLkI-npWn7Hwe8eafes1Y_62doglomPoudwHl7Vxln4xxjsng=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"Ok - first time going to this McDonalds. I'm not a picky eater and have hit up McDees since time in memoriam.

My buddy and I had just wrapped up a ride on Fromme. We were hungry and McDees was going to hit the spot big time. We look up the address and see some reviews "they don't fill the fries all the way". No biggy, perhaps it was a mistake or a one off.

NOPE. We roll through the drive through. The workers are friendly enough - no issues with the interaction or the service. But the fries... My guys. Simply unacceptable. Our Large fries were missing 1/3 of what should have been a full container of tasty, delicious french fry goodness.

Needless to say we were incredibly disappointed. Why am I buying a Large fries when you're giving me roughly a Medium amount? Total bummer. The Big Mac was delicious though.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMboWEKRALf46SZYHkFWSXhJUcYzEl1dtzY8-Dv&fid=0x0:0xa5192350e0a75f1f"],"When":"2024-10-19"},{"Name":"Harry","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKFQCVxo9fyJ_2SNPGZBxlKOnayG_YrakvPiUrEq7jtNUyhgg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Last few times I've been here through the drive thru they direct me to the parking lot to wait. [{"Name":"Min T","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKHBCvyhMdMuGm8ISXRxIPWaPtZa7hX9LVxvDW4OOAn-tBBWA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"I recently tried Quesada and had an overall good experience:

Food: The $3 tacos were pretty tasty, with fresh ingredients and a decent selection of toppings to customize each taco to your liking.

Service: The server seemed a bit confused, which made the process feel a bit unorganized. Nothing major, but a bit more confidence and clarity would improve the experience.

Grand Opening Promo: They‚Äôre offering free burritos for their grand opening until 7 pm! I‚Äôm not sure how long the promo will last, but it‚Äôs a nice perk if you catch it in time.

Overall: Quesada is worth a visit for affordable tacos, and the grand opening deal is a bonus.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipM-fxgfcGOzqAdAd1qxPWFvsmACdfTigq8-gh1V&fid=0x0:0x71c9756adc8bf453"],"When":"2024-10-26"},{"Name":"dlov","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIUu7w2vIb9sN6vm6bG_vRlvq-6qDxIE8FjZ7-ufI_Sx9iv3A=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Ordered two burritos and a bowl yesterday and they forgot to put the chipotle tomato salsa on them‚Ä¶

We were very disappointed and would never ever order from there again, very mid food with no taste. Also the sour cream was trace amounts, if any at all. Practically all the toppings were chinced, I got to my last two bites before I noticed any corn in it.

It was just a disappointing experience.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPEK72kZBQaWyBDM9EtHdjNkDtG7d1o8uQc9Uyr&fid=0x0:0x71c9756adc8bf453"],"When":"2024-9-24"},{"Name":"joe burr","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWoL0VpVWD0ZP8bt0Y8Pb-v0jCc9IKI-3Np1nTnrQ3GPDlBxhk3wg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"I didn't realize this was like a chain place. $1.50 for guacamole per Taco is a bit high in my opinion! It reminded me of subway where you choose what want in your talk or everything is behind the glass and pre-cut and prepared. Assembly line. Don't think I'll be going back there if there's plenty of other places that have better tacos.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNw3e0ehbMyozx6t28QBvIwtLNVj5fJuCHTnbY2&fid=0x0:0x71c9756adc8bf453"],"When":"2024-6-3"},{"Name":"Maggie Sheng","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKBdrRSBRUzvfJEyn8SMzEIITWaHx-ZaFd4xxLzaEvVSOhCACDy=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Food looks pretty bad, and they forgot to give me guacamole in a Doordash order. I called and they said told me to come pick it up myself and there‚Äôs nothing they can do.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMUqJpo4ajjCYs2qBpPCwF2UI-XaUcR-EmoXrFB&fid=0x0:0x71c9756adc8bf453"],"When":"2024-10-26"},{"Name":"J P","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJPNOwczxQeYq8Qup51h2PTCgzkWZZqiOeXeOFsoHWK1IWAROM=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Will review again when it‚Äôs not a free promotional offer, however the free burrito was very disappointing. The black beans were undercooked and very hard, unacceptable for a Mexican restaurant. Undercooked beans are hard to digest and can cause serious digestive distress.

The portions were small, service rushed and they skimped out on the veggies.

It‚Äôs also in poor taste to demand a 5 star review while running a two day promotion, because to customers it appears like you‚Äôre trying to buy good ratings. The food, service and management of the promotion was disappointing to say the least. For fairness, i will review again when I try a burrito without any promotions.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOTBvO2FNeQ-dGcWjmjxRY1s8X_J6feo1tHU4Mr&fid=0x0:0x71c9756adc8bf453"],"When":"2024-10-27"},{"Name":"KANWAR DHILLON","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJbqIkFr5k-UBbGmAG86P31A5Div0iIS8JezzZTo0okgJkr0w=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Today i went to buy chicken burrito bowl and there were two girls name simran and mehak they both treat me well. They make very good bowl i never had that kind of bowl it was filled with ingredients. Also they make a balance between everything. I recommend everyone and ask for them and u will never gonna regret. Thanks","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"R R","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocI10NxLkIoZpNw1PV6O9eyT2efRyN8qKRwya4MtpTPKiEFUTQ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Not really ‚Äúfree‚Äù when you‚Äôre forcing customers to leave you a 5 star review on google maps before they collect the burrito, is it?

If you want some honest feedback, you skimped out on everything: veggies,rice, protein and even sauce for the ‚ÄúGrand Opening‚Äù free burrito so customers should expect that on a regular basis?

Only good thing is that Quesada offers options for vegetarians/vegans BUT be prepared for cross contamination.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Oleena Asija","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLqgnN4Z4P7uGob_rqujLTVv2PvMNPvLKFOqBwDXl38RTgHdQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"first time ever I tried quesada with my sister and You know wt we had the bestest experience. The girl, Mehak working over there helped me chosing the best burrito bowl ever! she assisted me and my sis with patience which normally lacks when I go to other food chains. I really really appreciate her efforts and at last i would love to come back here again and highly recommed this location for good customer service.","Images":null,"When":""}]

[{"Name":"Kordan Do","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocI9dMUun6oOUk3EkQVIKtJE9PfSdUqD49gGjJT6sr_UlH1I8Q=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I fell in love with this place at first sight! The food and drinks are truly amazing and outstanding. It‚Äôs inspiring to see it packed with people from lunch to dinner. I highly recommend the noodle set paired with Hong Kong iced milk tea.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOvxeghIZg04vG-VHL_TVNfk9QUlr971obEU8D_&fid=0x0:0x21bb8fe6746217cd"],"When":"2024-11-13"},{"Name":"Zhi Su","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWIOR9QcmuN7xVMHRRZGlnxULc0lgkhWHVqVbkqx4LTpIv5_InbCw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"This place is busy even before it opens at 12 noon. A line up forms just before opening. That said, the restaurant is deceivingly large with seating in the back of the restaurant. I had the laksa and it was really good. You can customize a la carte and there‚Äôs a seafood option. Lots of other options as well. A bit on the pricey side for what it is, but that seems to be the norm now.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNHVGZOR2yiFDdp9CpnNjpOE0-4jVwydowz2LRp&fid=0x0:0x21bb8fe6746217cd"],"When":"2024-8-13"},{"Name":"Stella Oh","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWvqyQ2KS_YIN6XYOMkDtQZO2ezjEJLWRODsOzNFIWuIhCYtAL-=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"An absolute gem of a Hong Kong-style restaurant! They had some of the most iconic HK noodles and non-soup entr√©es.

I loved that they could let me choose pork intestines or any other meat topping for my noodle soup. I ordered laksa and I found it perfectly hot and spicy and creamy. The hot milk tea was so delicious and more rich than that at other HK places in Vancouver.

Although we were the last ones there with 5 minutes to go until last call, they let us take our time eating until closing time. However, because they had finished cleaning and were chatting while waiting for us to finish, I felt like I should hurry to be respectful of their time. Next time, I would love to come for lunch and spend more time here. I was told their fish soup is amazing, so that‚Äôs what I‚Äôll try next time.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMPyyFb2ne2FbrAJRquJXkaHuA-Q-VB7NC0G5Tv&fid=0x0:0x21bb8fe6746217cd"],"When":"2024-12-23"},{"Name":"Kristy Chen","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWEfZ2rjxNiODjhooQ3vu4wU52UFmMssx1nBEw-QrGtiP3D8nPb=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Another comfort food place for me. Their soup noodles are consistent, nothing special but it‚Äôs one of those things that I crave every so often.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOMa0aP8N4oFCLMPFA6Sz3WodEl2J53Fn4UO1l1&fid=0x0:0x21bb8fe6746217cd"],"When":"2024-10-12"},{"Name":"Sandra Chan","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUS3d7aZA4lMhkB4lrjOTrDjB_p6PvngmeWQeM0VFHPfzqli2Uc=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"This is a popular place as the line up started before the 12 pm opening. We came on a Saturday for lunch. My bowl of noodles with seafood, deep fried fish skin (tasted store bought) and a complimentary hot almond drink came to around $25. It was very filling and tasty.
I‚Äôve returned to try other noodle soups and haven‚Äôt been disappointed. Love that there‚Äôs no msg in the fish soups!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNOabgbqqs0WQZIvI33z39Mmo1qVVEHrRUMk_jE&fid=0x0:0x21bb8fe6746217cd"],"When":"2024-9-28"},{"Name":"Genevi√®ve Chong","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXVT0KfSWGN35ZBiKD1WUTgdOyzwm6roDOIFQmcjeLAFFOPYxN3BA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Had a great time, and the soups are delicious. Our server, Fai, was the absolute best!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPNDD85YRacZMIvTyHlgvWVJVmBq7SPfhh1iYnd&fid=0x0:0x21bb8fe6746217cd"],"When":"2024-12-18"},{"Name":"Kwokmun Lee","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXwgemhPBQj04dXJGaCC3UXO7mu-wx6E6tR0EsqeLukxknEduY=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"We would come to Deer Signature every so often if we are craving for some noodle soup. Lots of ways to customise your bowl but keep in mind that the portion is quite large. We like that they have an option to include a small side for a small price.

If noodles don't tickle your fancy, they also have rice meals and some Western options. The food is really not bad for a cafe. Service was not great here on most of our visits.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Munchica","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXbQ6ACs51IPQJlRLrmnunOErED8bimOf5-y1uov4EWpuZvjQQjrA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba8-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"This place offers customizable HK style noodle soups and other classic HK cafe food. The quality is average. They have late night specials and the food is like Asian comfort food. Quite enjoyed their red bean ice which had real fresh red beans in it. The broth of the noodle soups were rich and the portions were generous.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMNwmKgNOBRUcteVk8g1NcmePErLHHv8aEC1aX2&fid=0x0:0x21bb8fe6746217cd"],"When":"2023-2-3"}]
