[{"Name":"Ed","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUhww4Vy8Jav_UlW2tMDOJhLRAoRr0CBxMKXW0KEKtBac__hE6N=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Had a craving for pho on a chilly night so headed over here with family.
Got seats immediately ( weeknight) and service was friendly and quick.
Ordered the house special and it came shortly.
A good pho is always defined by its soup and the quality here is spot on. Lots of beef, noodles, bean sprouts & mint leaves made the meal complete. Finished everything with a happy smile.
Will come again.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOW4mufNoAf1yMMP263joT_1dYWzI8NvU1bgixX&fid=0x0:0x995b45f39cde35ff"],"When":"2024-12-19"},{"Name":"Ponda Baba","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWB1Z_E00v52246I1gIoMBkczOxjQZj6Oq_4BUoL4Tw6wid095m=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Oh dear lord what incredibly crispy chicken wings. And what an amazing lemongrass chicken banh mi. Food was so damn good. We went at 330ish so it was a very in between time and the server and the cook were eating in the restaurant. A little odd, but worth mentioning I think. Makes it a little awkward asking them for something. Visit with confidence. Food was crazy good.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipM_U6ERyu4F491irQKzF_LeFDThsbYs70unX6fV&fid=0x0:0x995b45f39cde35ff"],"When":"2024-7-24"},{"Name":"George Cookie","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWAbri0D7DgObTN0l5bI_oleVemAatSMPB9CgchOjVn-CXCiTL0=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"You can taste the freezer burn in the soup noodles ingredients.  Bland and gross. The very overpriced deep fried spring rolls need an oil change...you can taste other stuff that was deep fried in that long overused and overdue for a change oil. I regret coming here and I sincerely hope to save others from what I had to pay for in this sorry excuse for a Vietnamese restaurant.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOksrM-loC6v7m6cNbZJ87bN6HgaisKJrh8IT4R&fid=0x0:0x995b45f39cde35ff"],"When":"2024-9-9"},{"Name":"Zoe Lam","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVhUeHpHa-y3q-LK7VOUs3r6WUbNY28xOuVhKKD5ofcNGqzFf75=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Many different style of dishes when compared with other Vietnamese restaurants.
The calamari is really well fried and yummy, I like the spicy mayo sauce! They added lemon juice with it and makes the sauce less greasy.
The pork belly is so soft! I like the texture and goes so well with rice.
The bun is a little bit disappointed for me. The bun is soft but the seasoning of ginger for the filling is too strong. The taste becomes a bit weird.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNk9GgsU_0oGZrQl-otfmnXu_y1veGBP4uginOI&fid=0x0:0x995b45f39cde35ff"],"When":"2023-9-14"},{"Name":"Harry Lee","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVC_5ha5kkBIoownh6obr5ziv_zIpgXCp4SngWz9IVbgBCpYuO9=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Nice decor with a warm family feel. Good variety in the menu from sandwiches, soups, fried noodles, and rice dishes. Started with the calamari. Lightly battered, crispy and tender. Very nice. All my dishes had subtle delicate flavours. Reminds me of home style cooking. The house special beef noodle soup was especially good with generous amounts of beef. I would come back

Drop me a comment or a like, if you found this helpful.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMwhcOeIfyFMKll3dqyTzKSVesy2FWEpQxbztlU&fid=0x0:0x995b45f39cde35ff"],"When":"2022-4-5"},{"Name":"Patrick Quimio","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocK_EudfzuEhN7SqIS0s4vEaKPgJZDjjOUkhRG1OuGteFgaArA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Great food, busy but prompt service. Spicy tofu curry was a medium, a solid medium of 4/10 spice level. Braised beef with rice was soft and juicy. A bit stingy with the rice portion but the pickled vegetables were delicious. Would come again","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipORsDPTcOUKjPApE4X4evdd8Y3jkVv6XoQrO-zl&fid=0x0:0x995b45f39cde35ff"],"When":"2023-11-18"},{"Name":"mariana aigner","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXxpjkuEqY8xWItm1Gx7iUqjrUi5WC57ZB5BNFYPsuZq45AnBQEfA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Talk about amazing food and service combo!! Loved the vibes, the shaken beef and the beef pho are essential!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipN1h2ymv1pbLjQqutuK9mGygkQ-OXwgOV9sJ9tD&fid=0x0:0x995b45f39cde35ff"],"When":"2024-11-13"},{"Name":"Pooya Mohammadi","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVEMZryWVPX5Tm2bYag-esW8MaLoN9KJ4NS1DCL9dnAcrEe61w=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Viet House looks like a local, family owned small Vietnamese restaurant.

‚úÖ Food to price value is good and you‚Äôll get enough delicious food for what you pay.

üîµ The atmosphere is nice and small and you‚Äôll like some Vietnamese elements on the walls.

ü§µ‚Äç‚ôÄÔ∏è The staff is somehow nice and know the menu sufficiently.

Recommendations:

* Coconut Curry (if you like curry & coconut togetherüòÅ) $15

üî¥ House special fried noodle was not good and the noodle tasted like being in a broth and didn‚Äôt taste good.

user_reviews:
[{"Name":"Hye","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjULQQSi1mhNFty7n8ZPesKkMpD31jiIGazltx_wRmE-swaOwr4=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"I had some expectations for this place, but the food we tried was very disappointing.

The Laksa lacked flavor and toppings‚Äîit was honestly the worst Laksa I‚Äôve had in Vancouver. The Sambal Eggplant was okay, but it felt like it could‚Äôve been better seasoned since the eggplant tasted a bit bland. The Crispy Pata was also disappoing. The skin was very crispy, but the meat inside was so dry that I didn‚Äôt want more than one bite.

Thankfully, the Salted Egg Popcorn Chicken was fine. I enjoyed the chicken and the yum yum sauce.

The atmosphere was nice, but since I had to order at the counter and considering the prices, it was definitely not worth the visit","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOBaR3rCgodlqP_erse6cjodi3B0q-EItGjhwU&fid=0x0:0x95ea3092b47bad5d"],"When":"2024-12-5"},{"Name":"Anna Villanueva","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjU4tZhNczx0I9AviSFHIIm0R3EPxJ-qLsUgyE6NLIIdveimt0-U=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I love our whole experience with Potluck Hawker Eatery. It didn‚Äôt only filled our stomach but our soul with their mouth watering South East Asian food. We tried the Nasi Goreng, Salted egg Chicken wings and the Char grilled Broccolini. I recommend all of them. We got to tried their Mango sticky rice drink and the thai iced tea which is totally recommended, too. It‚Äôs really hard to find a good food with a good price. And this is a hidden gem here in Cambie and 18th Ave. My fianc√© and I will definitely be coming back here and we love to try the Pata.

PS. We really loved the Milo Roti, must try too!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNaGk2jDvnSznFHmDIdmXjfLIt3j-TgXKPt1wiQ&fid=0x0:0x95ea3092b47bad5d"],"When":"2024-8-2"},{"Name":"Shonnah","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVryghpg_5X3Yv-cncwU7OGN26KCAvVhjXajvFLZ6BLUMNFRgyF=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"I‚Äôve been meaning to try this place for a while. Interior is quite bright, i‚Äôm a fan - it has a fun, casual vibe. We came on a Tuesday and the place was relatively busy (the place is small), so I‚Äôd recommend making a reservation or calling in advance.

We ordered the salted egg yolk chicken wings, straight outta Bangkok (sub pork belly with prawns), lem@k‚Äôing good chicken and purple haze. The salted egg yolk chicken wings were pretty solid and well fried. Batter was light yet crunchy, not too oily and chicken was moist. My only feedback is that I wish it had a stronger salted egg yolk flavour. The straight outta Bangkok was essentially a pad thai. It didn‚Äôt mention being spicy, but I found it to be a medium spice level from the peppercorn. I felt there was too much sauce as it was too strong (salty and sweet) and there was nothing special, I‚Äôd say this was my least favourite dish we ordered. Chicken curry was very good - I‚Äôd recommend ordering a bowl of rice with it. It reminded me of a Chinese curry where it‚Äôs on the sweeter side, with a mild spice. The flavour of the curry was on point and the chicken absorbed the curry flavour very well. Lastly, the purple haze, which I also really enjoyed. It had a sweet glaze, mild spice and was quite garlicky. The eggplant was cooked well (great texture) - even the non-veggie lovers at my table were a fan of this dish.

I would say the flavours to most of these dishes were quite strong, predominantly a sweet and salty combination. Portion sizes were enough where for 3 people, where we all left quite full. I do wish they had some more basic dishes like Laksa or Hainan chicken, which may be on their lunch menu but that‚Äôs just my personal preference. Service was quite average and I do feel like the price was a tad high for how casual everything is, doctoring in ambiance, how the food looks and service. Would I came back? Yes - I‚Äôm curious about their lunch menu. Would I go out of my way to come here? Probably not.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipP4Tj8W9XsU89v5b7ipKNZIPVL4h4EXARqlGcw3&fid=0x0:0x95ea3092b47bad5d"],"When":"2024-8-21"},{"Name":"Snoopy Kitchen","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjU3h-I-trbYva-Tzrs-UNhkQe4Nn1jgsblAcoQ0hPrnUWvugM3Y=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Refreshing Singapore/Malaysian small restaurant.  Crispy pork knuckle is a must.  They also have black pepper crab or salty egg yolk crab which needs to be ordered 48 hours in advance.  Will try them next time!

Staff are friendly and make good recommendations.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMF9moKc_tmW17S2QSpen__vEaFXxGQsmjuHe5P&fid=0x0:0x95ea3092b47bad5d"],"When":"2024-9-1"},{"Name":"Camisha Kuang","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUllvsjDMoK5NtNE_g-wyZbboDU2izLwl7Ox5JFjX8ZcZqI-71CTw=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"My husband and I have been meaning to try this place for a while now, but has always been busy! Luckily tonight we managed to get seated right away! We ordered the jammy clammy (saucy egg noodle with clams), salted egg yolk wings, and roti. Food came quickly; everything was super flavorful and delicious! Service was also extremely attentive and friendly. For instance, the server noticed right away when our table water jug was empty and came by with a fresh one for us without us even flagging her attention. We will definitely be back!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipN72DjGxq0tKP7a15wjpZ-Tblem8U98GYQ2Q9Bx&fid=0x0:0x95ea3092b47bad5d"],"When":"2024-7-7"},{"Name":"Caitlyn Irwin","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVI21mHw9N4NnQjSFbfR-DGdannM_ypt2tQTBR4BY64Nd3gMXTd=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Absolutely loved this bright unfussy restaurant. The Brussel Sprouts appy was so deliciously crisp, with fish sauce for umami as well as a gentle heat and topped off with pork floss for perfection. Also had the Spicy Adobe sandwich- yup, a wee bit spicy for me but soo delicious through my tears.  I can't wait to come back to Vancouver and see what new creations are on the menu.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOAheWgZFlosjH93Yn4NFMJfUCzhE_6KDVnDC4f&fid=0x0:0x95ea3092b47bad5d"],"When":"2024-10-22"},{"Name":"Czarina C","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIo8eXVmqWaj9Vbf_tvPIBEFEtkzcAFaaJ-V14rHyPNFAf-9Q=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"This is the cutest gem in the heart of Cambie in Vancouver! The flavour profile is singaporean and southeast asian fusion. Must try:
-roti canai
-salted egg wings and caramel fish wings(it was so good, we ordered it twice!) and padthai!

The clam-mee jam-mee also had a really good heat to it and purple haze (eggplants).

For dessert, we had the warm mochi and the creme bruleee to end the date!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMBDl1sBhgod05zu-jbUhyB6XpTDX3urpihUm0J&fid=0x0:0x95ea3092b47bad5d"],"When":"2024-8-24"},{"Name":"Yumi Hirao","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocI2QVWvR47qjHpuW78A8nuy96ITOGamqXXmeFcE4O2uBwOZpg=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We ordered a Salted Egg York Fried Chicken Sando and Laksa. Food was tasty, staff are very friendly and polite. I came with a big baby stroller but he gave us a big table which I really appreciate! Thank you very much!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNSygVDPCQETOIinZaM8rb_rNoydakrwbGsCWS5&fid=0x0:0x95ea3092b47bad5d"],"When":"2024-8-13"}]

[{"Name":"Brian Shaler","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVanm_SU1M6cSuCRW78pg1T2oWnXPERDUCzn8bF70zKPszCwZw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"A long time Hong Kong cafe serving up classic fried rice, noodles and soups. Its your classic HK cafe where the consistency is better than the food. At first I was surprised by the high prices, however, I will say the portions were bigger than expected. Definitely decent value here.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipM1k__7lxynFJadmp9SyPHNZNKd3Jv9CVtMl3Cl&fid=0x0:0x667dd50bb13625bb"],"When":"2024-11-25"},{"Name":"Sinyo ganteng","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVK6DhObLW3StVcJ_e9Ph42mdmAq5cSoW-d536hao-jSu7WAn8I=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"this is a pretty good Hongkong style restaurant, Foods are very tasty. Their chicken steak is perfect seasoning. Thai style Fried   rice  is also yummy. portion is okay, some is lot's but also bit little for other items . the price is a bit over, in my opinion. their service is also a bit slow. Atmosphere bit old, wish they renovated .","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNl5i7xTVUIhKHSfGitZRGCUOOS-Fcvag7kr-IF&fid=0x0:0x667dd50bb13625bb"],"When":"2024-10-21"},{"Name":"Sergio Phan Lung","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWPDVe_7BjNWmfngiczr7WEa4oFymN1mLH86T4W1tfnZEx87-8=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Solid place for Hong Kong style lunch or dinner. Had the beef brisket with noodles, as well as macaroni soup. The beef was great. The noodles were good but nothing crazy. Macaroni soup was just okay. Service is good if you can get the servers attention. Will still come here if I'm around.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNcpZDHqKCZOT0Vtzxl_SoJZAMkaV2i-jTQghvT&fid=0x0:0x667dd50bb13625bb"],"When":"2024-10-21"},{"Name":"minnie li","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKRoQOlIxvrw__7xun_s22_XplGfNg8u2NALefXOOF5MWkjHg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"This Hong Kong-style caf√© has been a long-standing establishment in Vancouver, and I‚Äôve visited it after COVID. Unfortunately, this time, the experience was quite disappointing. The food quality has significantly declined, and the portion sizes are shockingly small. I ordered the tomato sauce spaghetti, and the plate was so shallow that it felt like a kid-sized portion compared to other places. The other dishes weren‚Äôt much better‚Äî the chicken noodle soup we ordered was bland and lacked any flavor.

The one decent dish was the Portuguese chicken rice, but even that had very little chicken in it. Considering the prices are around $20 per dish, the lunch portions were surprisingly small and not worth the price.

Additionally, the service felt rushed. The servers were busy and kept clearing our dishes while there were still a few bites left, which made it feel like they were urging us to leave quickly. The overall environment was uncomfortable, and it seemed like they were rushing everyone out the door.

Overall, the food quality and portion sizes, combined with the rushed atmosphere, made this a very disappointing visit.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMqnVN2QSw5ecq50RCrMOope2haTJMCX_8cHGLk&fid=0x0:0x667dd50bb13625bb"],"When":"2024-9-17"},{"Name":"Brandon J (B2)","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXk5xWmfyZG2f0bMXantsSbItuWlqAW0g04s4GGiRJ4pkAu9yQn=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"Caf√© Gloucester used to be good before the pandemic and boasted in their curry beef brisket. So I decided to come for breakfast to see if they were still good. They have interesting combos where you can mix and match different menu items costing 15-20$. I ordered steak and eggs with hot Hong Kong milk tea and a friend ordered satay beef spaghetti in soup and luncheon meat egg sandwich. My order came and the server gave me chicken steak, which I did not order, but ate it without exchanging because I was too hungry. It was tender to the bite with a crispy fried edge crunch. The mushroom gravy was slightly salty, but overall was simple and complimented the chicken. The noodles were okay as well as the sandwich, nothing out of the ordinary, but simple Chinese comfort food.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNyLmjLVZzUBPTOC5k-0NiiMVZ5HCjt0di8kTSM&fid=0x0:0x667dd50bb13625bb"],"When":"2024-9-21"},{"Name":"ÁÑ°ÈõôÁöáÂêéQueen Beoly","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXBaBsZ9_knFBARzUI-bXIEIse1LHA2KSwfBBdHD-8TgplirOKj=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"4/5

The chef definitely experienced in control the wok, all the food have wok-hei. Fried on point .

Tomato Pork chop rice taste like childhood memory. Braised fish seasoning was nice.

The bitter melon dish could have better seasoning tho.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPt3wjY393DFhjXPmnBJxL2FQTEdUN6Q1mYH6VH&fid=0x0:0x667dd50bb13625bb"],"When":"2024-11-18"},{"Name":"Anthony Szeto","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIOIfBQIJIjsWRooBTLTPXU967iECEki_cy7Je7AAbxzMbCMw=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"Usually the food is fine but I ordered a Club Spaghetti from them via Uber eats. Not their best at all.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipM2esikfv7IcTMGWbYFsnbaxlLz3Z7XT5s3QExb&fid=0x0:0x667dd50bb13625bb"],"When":"2024-9-10"},{"Name":"Frank Zhu","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWzhcETXdDUtwjYh7uebc0kW4wIe7ENaUquXny4w9cB-W-4Uq45=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Excellent HongKong Mike teaÔºàÂ•∂Ëå∂Ôºâ and the soup covered by the bread.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMWNDwPJgYhXupEq2nqtYRrTiSQCxjsanie_Lri&fid=0x0:0x667dd50bb13625bb"],"When":"2024-12-21"}]

[{"Name":"Derek Shek","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWP9Pjija1abf8rOsOgAPBkesWOZ8sALAjyQJKt0I-DTaykDkHV=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"We‚Äôre regulars at Fat Boy Kitchen, visiting almost every week because it‚Äôs a hit with the kids and they absolutely love it. I‚Äôm personally a fan of both their breakfast and lunch offerings, but today I decided to try something new from the menu‚Äîthe spicy beef noodle.

It was a revelation! The noodles were incredibly delicious and authentically Chinese, with just the right amount of spice to elevate the dish without overwhelming it. The flavors were spot-on, and the beef was tender and perfectly seasoned. I enjoyed it so much that I finished the entire bowl and found myself still craving more.

While I‚Äôve loved most of the dishes I‚Äôve tried here, the spicy beef noodle has definitely taken the top spot on my list. Whether you‚Äôre a regular like us or just passing through, I highly recommend giving Fat Boy Kitchen a try, especially for the spicy beef noodle‚Äîit‚Äôs a true standout!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOCgfWBxv34CBLvcNoI4fT91a3PCQitH2XQluoy&fid=0x0:0x4e4b7bf614db82fb"],"When":"2024-11-12"},{"Name":"Winnie","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVdhdAZj5kAJq7u9NvVhNxLrp7yafognrc6dJzsqDpR7yVPbJry=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Value: it‚Äôs fair, you get what you pay for.
Food: don‚Äôt expect it to be super tasty or amazing, there is a good amount of food portions BUT this curry rice I ordered was definitely NOT it. Zero taste of curry, only a hint of smell. It was more like a very diluted curry paste with lots of corn starch added
It came with 2 nice portion of deep fried chicken thighs.

Location: its parking is limited to street only. it wasn‚Äôt hard to find parking in residential street, just walk a block.

The seats were not that comfy as it is quite sunken down, the place smells like bamboo shoots.

Had the steak aswell, it was tenderized. It was a pass.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPCSs2Q2vCMIEiAIUalpUDHAjd3MX9tPJsTRccz&fid=0x0:0x4e4b7bf614db82fb"],"When":"2024-12-16"},{"Name":"Nathan McCain","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXMaTd10qU1yoxV34Ts6SnYTvzeaAiPCQDHNmqrHxF1m_kacFSH=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"I‚Äôm not the thinnest boy myself, so I figured this place would be up my alley, and it mostly is, albeit with a caveat or two. Drinks are good but I wish the tea was a touch stronger, and the food is a touch less seasoned than I was expecting. I was also really craving the fried chicken and had to settle for pork katsu‚Ä¶ bummer, but it was still very crispy and enjoyable. Satay noodles were really nice and the value is certainly there. Worth a stop.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPzUihN04F2b3QhZXP1xLyhs5qmQiIhZ9UJWvPU&fid=0x0:0x4e4b7bf614db82fb"],"When":"2024-9-22"},{"Name":"Ling To","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIlFxJCKp6bjqARUOXgwrUpHcbKAm9tBpTn_ze63uacIdbffw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Food came out quick! Noodles soup was piping hot.

The takeout utensil was overkill though when you're dining in.

Also, the tiniest washroom ever! Thought I was on a plane. Bench chair probably needs to be replaced as I sunk in (no support for your bottom).","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOXHqaQYQKP_UuDwSoKs_osIjPtVP1Gn0P2vYn3&fid=0x0:0x4e4b7bf614db82fb"],"When":"2024-9-17"},{"Name":"Markus Chan","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJXROvRsGKOxwBtK9XUZxhEqi9KXQ7EWM8JfBaI86dyPJTQyQ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"Food: 100%
Service: 90%
Atmosphere: 20%
Parking: 60%
Food tastes great! I had noodles and scrambled eggs, and the restaurant had good chefs. Fat boy‚Äôs kitchen‚Äôs chefs make good food! The service is good too! However my rating is certainly a 3 star. ‚≠êÔ∏è ‚≠êÔ∏è ‚≠êÔ∏è. The atmosphere needs to be improved. There are only 9 tables at the restaurant, and there is a LONG queue. We had to wait 30 minutes before we got a table.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Ryan","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWCDMUY42ah4aAgta84ssT2DYa3PFsR3r4fbxhBdcs3AXShIgTOYw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Showed up here for breakfast not sure what we would expect and was surprised at how friendly the staff were. The breakfast special was great‚Ä¶and the refried beans were a unique touch to your typical HK cafe meal. We also ordered the chicken steak laksa and the soup was full of flavor. Lots of laksa soup bases at HK cafes are diluted‚Äîbut not here!

The staff even offered our child a lollipop on the way out!

Our only complaint here - the front door is EXTREMELY SQUEAKY and each time someone enters or exits the restaurant, all the guests are greeted with a painful screech. Some WD-40 might do the trick

Otherwise good. Will definitely come back!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPUPWeQC80Z3L-GaRLZeO1UBlhOsI-4FzIGEpha&fid=0x0:0x4e4b7bf614db82fb"],"When":"2024-8-28"},{"Name":"mikey a","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJObrIzQB7RpeiCI7iZ2YIOKHqxR2WdQ_ovLiinwMw8pWyX5Q=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Was really hype to go to this place for breakfast,  boy!!!!!! It was bad.not worth the money:( it's not a pork chop it's a pork loin... and a bad one at that, eggs had no salt and no butter or jam for toast .... nothing, if you are in Vancouver and looking for hk style breakfast or even meal don't waste time or money, parking is bad as well. Felt bad taking the family here. Oh well season learn","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMil4Hx5LqocvUtQoqc9uoFdIgzNhX1WGNSVXSz&fid=0x0:0x4e4b7bf614db82fb"],"When":"2024-8-8"},{"Name":"Ebony Renee","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVOePN2EaDQ5Me8LlpM31hBnHkNAOa4FZ9b9Nkx3h0UwFR3kUjYfg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Searched on Google maps for a spot to grab lunch, and wanted to try due to the name of the restaurant, the reviews, and the way the food looked in the pics....this place definitely didn't disappoint!

I ordered my food to go and didn't realize how much you get! That curry sauce is perfect to dip fries and nuggets in.

I'll definitely be back to try more items!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNlkLGjrNDHytrpWa_gUWK31qxAWsH_KohT90yU&fid=0x0:0x4e4b7bf614db82fb"],"When":"2024-4-11"}]

I think it is empty for a long time, no stock? Why they operate the store so poor, they never think for the customers, everyday they clean the restaurant, no one finds no hand sanitizer in the container ? I never come here again.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipM5cEuibWtfTbBBqLudSArxl44ioYd-Xmf_8zGF&fid=0x0:0x72077a8aab1b47ee"],"When":"2024-9-28"},{"Name":"brook lynn","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXJGy0oLTpXgVEg73RGC4Fr54JPSyq1qQWE5iA-n182JpmBhfeo4g=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"ridiculous.. i usually order here a lot, but never again this time. i brought my food inside and my drink was all over my floor and the rest of my food leaving it inedible. i worked at mcdonalds for 2 years and never has this been an issue. how hard is it to get a drink tray? or warn the driver that the drink could spill? this sucks","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPw0Zd5qj7pOK6Uis-OXE4EqfM4-6B9B7gSECRH&fid=0x0:0x72077a8aab1b47ee"],"When":"2024-12-9"},{"Name":"Ryan","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWpwQlCo-1a84xml8SG0OhsKLMM8jjmMMx0eed-rBLLhfcQkz2NTg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Ordered delivery . No honey mustard dipping sauce ordered given. Second time in 2 weeks they seem to sub items without any confirmation . Guess they ran out of drink holders too as my drink was just put in the bag and spilled all over my nuggets and burger . Poor management on likely inventory control or just lazy staff or franchisee cutting corners to save money . How hard is it to bag drinks separately if you don‚Äôt have drink holders sk a they don‚Äôt spill and make a mess and result in soggy inedible food . How hard is it to provide dipping sauces selected and not sub without confirmation from customer ?","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPiboBbCK8t7JshqpjITvQlkwBwK-02b3Vt5Afj&fid=0x0:0x72077a8aab1b47ee"],"When":"2024-10-13"},{"Name":"Nas n","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLcVyLYTX378bWV_WiK6KtAP7az_DT6fngQYhUpoQ37gyPqjSU=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Pattys are now translucent floppy disk. I had to look with tweezers to find the meat. Profiting corporations now are taking it to another level.

Paid 30 dollars for 2 meals $30 bucks could get you 2 perfect sized sandwich at happy hour in cactus club for example of course not including the tip.

But their menu photos haven't changed which is just ridiculous!!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMAQipdVGtMu8txSJ6bDs2RJybghgx-sStc4WRt&fid=0x0:0x72077a8aab1b47ee"],"When":"2024-7-19"},{"Name":"Philip Raymond Lim","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjV5EIBAgpBLsauhPMdjXym7mJ4fA8mtryDtWQIJCZfJxYXxupU8=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"This place is close to my workplace. Hmm, the guys forgot to add my chicken on my salad. I also found out that the chicken has been processed, so it‚Äôs not a fresh one. They added some ingredients, spices, probably high in sodium etc. so it‚Äôs not my thing as I‚Äôm very conscious with the nutritional value of what I eat. Calorie is quite high.

But speaking of atmosphere, I like the place. The service was descent. They also gave me my other serving of chicken when I showed them the receipt versus what was missing from my order.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMnWq5kXMPzBdBKjpT5Xu0wAIfOHavDYAKGc4R9&fid=0x0:0x72077a8aab1b47ee"],"When":"2024-6-27"},{"Name":"eddy wong","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX8Fjpj3y8teHQ4LqbC4PHR8whbU4-XOrTXEwklI9bGRqZLRD20=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"It‚Äôs going to be a hit or MAJOR MISS here. What do you expect? It‚Äôs minimum wage workers with big egos. It‚Äôs a difficult job with all the food apps. To top it off there‚Äôs a drive thru and mobile apps. It‚Äôs not what it use to be. But they do have a spacious seating area. That‚Äôs a bonus.

When I was at the cashier and asked I like to order a JBC, she replied, what is that? She definitely wasn‚Äôt new I came to this location many times. I only ordered up front because their app wasn‚Äôt working.

But to be fair, whenever there is an issue, I‚Äôve always had a better experience with the staff re-making the order. That‚Äôs an extra star gained.

I don‚Äôt think they are incompetent workers like what others are saying. I think they just need more direction. They have a care free I don‚Äôt care slouchy attitudes but all of a sudden when there‚Äôs an issue and the lines and online orders build up, they fix it right away.

Like I said, what can you do? Not many people work these types of jobs anymore. Would you? Just hold the manager responsible and if the manager doesn‚Äôt do anything request the franchise owners contact. And if that doesn‚Äôt work contact costal health. They have all the info.
So far I haven‚Äôt needed to use the owners contact‚Ä¶ yet.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMquKYPd4yTE_XmBo_Wm92CWFRbvm38n6uftUEa&fid=0x0:0x72077a8aab1b47ee"],"When":"2024-3-3"},{"Name":"Swimming Lion","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIoNuKoBPU8hDsJrOBlEDRPQawlWHi3C9rUvrLYtz7paaZM0w=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Last couple of visit was quite disappointing so haven‚Äôt been there for a while.
This time is surprisingly good. Service is fast. The salad is very fresh and the restaurant is very clean. The burger is juicy.
Always love their chili

Plenty of free parking","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPcOA9nTlf9XCPM0G7CkXsAhNZ4_rkXwgABGC6c&fid=0x0:0x72077a8aab1b47ee"],"When":"2023-12-29"},{"Name":"Den D","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIufPSQrxthBd2yLrO36eaf9AzCaAuxn86kyl-ElyZDp685EQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Great location, very friendly and efficient staff, food is also really good. In general I find Wendy's burgers more tasty than other fast food places. Absolutely love the square Dave's burgers and the chicken nuggets are tasty as well. The fries could use some seasoning though they are cooked perfectly. Will be back!","Images":null,"When":""}]

Will come again and try another favors!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNoiDFQfEx9_8gkpL9PxEwxfwACwQW3z_8l4rRk&fid=0x0:0x4979dfeffb54f65f"],"When":"2024-5-22"},{"Name":"Ginger Powder","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVaVdDkYC1tibGzSudbDpBumkQHeb6FrvjL-attxJ94VuhOmW1M=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"I'm purchasing at6540 Fraser St, Vancouver, BC V5X 3T5,But the map doesn't have a mark, the chicken bones are black and already smell bad","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMF2QnZF6ezPm37D10H4lJ12I16_tyJjjZRDwCD&fid=0x0:0x4979dfeffb54f65f"],"When":"2024-8-16"},{"Name":"Faye","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocI-LV0Bj-Xa0ouNWpag7B4NioaP6fRKA5H8Op-Z7SvGiyIU3A=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"The chicken was cooked through and was quite juicy. We ordered 2 boxes of 4 flavors for $29.99 each. Each order had about 16 - 17 good-sized pieces. We tried the original, Prinkle snow, sweet and spicy, and honey mustard. We didn't find any of the flavors too spicy. The mustard slightly overpowered the honey but overall, it was good. It was enough for the 4 of us. The order process was different as you ordered on a tablet and then the counter person handled the payment process. It's a tiny place with seating for maybe 12 - 16 ppl.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Amy Yue","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKutYpQzEHBgmBeljhr8d5raUFp47Iuwn8wsbo972QdNFhiYQ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"Not the best but not the worst.

We have our go to Korean chicken place but decided to give this place a try since it was closer. Had high expectations because of the 4.8 star overall review. It did not meet expectations and would not order from here again.

Things that fell short:

The sweet soy and Korean honey mustard has a slow burn spice. I called to ask if there was a none spicy version and the lady said they recently changed their powder so all chicken has a hint of spice. I wouldn‚Äôt say it‚Äôs a hint. My child couldn‚Äôt eat it. So if you are adverse to spice I would stay away. Go to a place that has no spice in their base batter.

We ordered half half. While this refers to flavour, I would say there‚Äôs half large chicken chunks and half crispy bits. Great for those that like crispy bits but we prefer actual meat.

On the plus side I would the fries are really good. Crispy hot flavoured. 5/5.","Images":null,"When":""}]

The milkshake tastes like chocolate milk, plain liquid, no thickness to it for $8. Waste of money, will not be returning","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Scott Gong","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVU6Nrm_sRXxa4lpEjkIrZxamz6LceMGV7mYsCaPEW4FMeyz2s=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Most over-priced burger and fries I have ever had in my life. I paid $20+ for those two low quality items, and I spent 20 mins waiting for my order. Unbelievable.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipN631R1cPS3wdtE7V2X44E-JEd_XK6KnfeYAx-X&fid=0x0:0xfba7b2899b4f414c"],"When":"2022-8-25"},{"Name":"Hoori Barkh","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVsmGMB0Ma8Q_QX1b7LIeHjfj2OE3c7JiglHyQcJ3rqf9KbgA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"Skip Vera‚Äôs!
Ordered online and paid, when we got to the store apparently they never received our order so we ordered again and paid (1 week later I‚Äôm still waiting for my online order refund).
Took a while to get the food ready (that‚Äôs fine, made fresh-ok) but the quality of the burgers was just mediocre. Nothing to complain about but nothing to rave about either.
Restaurant was completely empty on a Friday night. Surprised they are still in business to be honest.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Eric Grant","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWhVR02aPzwVvQvqn63QlXyk0bgYy0E-LewKb9qSI5x_FX_h9ejyg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"There are many great mysteries in life. How were the Pyramids built? What is Love? And most mysterious of all, how is this place still in business? It is always empty. Never go to an empty restaurant.
Only thing I tried was the chocolate milkshake. Was disappointed with the size, price, and texture and the time it took to make it. Why does it take 15 minutes to make a milkshake when I am the only one there? If you are going to get one make sure to ask for it well blended or get a spoon.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Esmed P","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWPaVfVvhS7UlShhw7n3W_Eju3p15-TBYDAUGYnwKIb2zgwxN8=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Went during my lunch hour & ordered. I wait, & after 25 minutes pass watching the person who took my order have a conversation with another staff in the kitchen, I get up & start to hover at the counter. I guess they noticed, because I saw only then, did they start cooking my order. There's no ketchup available, so I asked for some. The lady seemed confused, then insited they keep it behind the counter. Finally after waiting another 20 minutes, I'm given my burger with smallest amount of ketchup possible, after this lady had sassed me about literally, 3 drips of water which fell from my fountain drink after pouring myself water. I didn't bother to try to ask for more kerchup I wanted. Bottom line, do not go here, unless you want horrendously slow & rude service.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Brian Taylor","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVS9FnL1Xm2VSimjexdVbc5QM_VHkzVtM3eQen6wRNt-IyDFLYSYA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"I'm not sure how this place stays in business. I used the Vera's app to order a burger and got confirmation of my order at 6:12 pm, but the burger wouldn't be ready until 6:45 pm (not that the restaurant was the slightest bit busy). I showed up at the restaurant at 6:35 and the staff weren't aware of my order and asked what app I used. Really? Once the order was located they proceeded to make the burger and it was ready by 6:50. I had ordered a Vera burger ($10.50) with a few free toppings, cheese ($2 extra) and bacon ($2.50 extra). When I sat down to eat the burger I thought they'd forgotten the bacon so I brought it up to the counter. It was pointed out to me that there was a piece of bacon on the burger, but at most it was one square inch! For $2.50? The burger tasted fine and I've enjoyed Vera burgers for a long time, but if there were a Five Guys anywhere on the West Side I would never go back to Veras.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Tano Pham","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLZTH6gNWlc-cb4ja-Rt0oeskyJW7A4uEUVtm6QYAF2hoCk8A=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Absolutely terrible service on a non-school day at the UBC campus location by this employee. Had ordered my burger 35 minutes ahead on the app and she did not accept the order until I physically got there.
What is the point of skip the line function of the app if takes your money and not process your order","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOuESOGkrJ4ca-F7MGAy2wyT8MDyLvBk6Wdks6G&fid=0x0:0xfba7b2899b4f414c"],"When":"2019-2-23"}]

[{"Name":"Tyler Elson","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLSSBo-tZ1gC9mrWPqvDg34yQXrh3mFJjkPp9uPSopcCw8Jeg=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Good food for a great price , quick service.
Also a owner standing up to the governments stupid ‚Äú GST holiday ‚Äú that is nothing but a scam to get votes next election. If the government truly wanted to help they would cancel the carbon tax and lower income taxes .

Will be back for lunch another day soon .","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Alikhan Nurani","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIi5bsJx16Uac6BDEDMXQkcR_qdps98hH1P9AWHLlOqaHBFSA=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I took my wife out for lunch today at Dylan's Diner, a charming little cafe that isn't pretentious at all. As soon as you walk in, the nostalgic aroma of coffee from the 70s hits you, and you just know it's going to be good. We enjoyed an old-school open-faced roast beef sandwich with fries and gravy‚Äîabsolutely delicious! The all-day $8.95 breakfast looked amazing too. Thanks, Mr. Chef Man, for cooking such good food! Highly recommended for a comforting, no-frills dining experience.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Niko Nesin","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVBEF-WvP2fKlbizeQFHFqp1pfhz-1wVKca7zLmvwnt0ULgjVwzUg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"Reminded me of the 80s movie dining experience. The food was OK, a bit expensive.

It's like a vintage home-cooked meal; the soup bowls with a sandwich combo was really small considering the price, and  it was too salty for my taste. My cooking is better so I'd suggest to pass this place, if you know how to cook.
If you don't know how to cook and want vintage dining experiences, this may be for you.

Took a while for food to arrive, even though it wasn't busy.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Bryce Koch","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVQVJrGeUXBZUx3Mgbd1I7EKwoq7eVZx6ClJbgCOcauML2vH5rfyw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Amazing food! My partner and I both got the super burger and it was HUGE! and so many fries. The portions are amazing for the price. And declious as well. The person working at the front was funny and very friendly. 10/10","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Victoria P","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVhCX8c-32Ugetf0VZblvt0Ulvofd-LVbIgI9XtZJBVqBZj1qVk=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Our first time here! It‚Äôs the perfect little ‚Äúdiner‚Äù with fantastic prices. Prefer this vs. Denny‚Äôs ‚Äî so glad we gave this a try! Will definitely come back. We split a monster hash and it was delicious! Delicious food and kind service as well.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMs6zX87uVwij9WPzNN4DYAFIJAH5F1G003d_Kn&fid=0x0:0x80419c6d1463895c"],"When":"2023-2-26"},{"Name":"Josh Talbott","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWl8CMH3GMlGfawJhTOCXZ6RdLxJ_HDcb19yCsoUFSB4-Ns5Q=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"I was charged GST when it's the GST holiday, apparently they "opted out" of being there for Canadians, The owner is an immigrant. Free surface parking in their busy small strip-mall lot. Street parking available. #letsguide #covid","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMcPSGmHznrQIuf35wpeC3xKrhyYAe4SuvkgRC5&fid=0x0:0xe750afb01549968c"],"When":"2021-6-6"},{"Name":"Ali Hekol","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJNpjmHKKNGgoRoG_eiAWIB5ml3ZaL0DfLc3Ic6ruotuuQygQ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"DONT COME TO THIS LOCATION PAST 9:30!!! I like this location because it‚Äôs so close to my house but other then that it‚Äôs very annoying and inconvenient. The workers will always start closing WAY to early, most of the time the lights are out by 9:45 when it says they close at 10. Tonight I went in to get a meatball sub and they informed me that this is unavailable past 9:30 because it is too soon before closing‚Ä¶ where does it say that on the subway website? It is not my problem they want to start cleaning up 30 minutes before they are even supposed to close and get home earlier, this location needs to start staying open WITH EVERYTHING FULLY AVAILABLE LIKE THE TIMES LISTED ONLINE. I know I seem crazy but this is fr super inconvenient, i didn‚Äôt cause any trouble with staff, i just said okay and walked out. I was forced to go to a WHOLE DIFFERENT LOCATION just to get my meetball sub. STOP CLEANING UP TOO EARLY OR CHANGE YOUR HOURS TO BE ACCURATE!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Dave Wood","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocK2Rv0AmSTn2G70hZ0GDw6F09vldvgpFgFMLPpzG1ZCQBvryA=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Ordered on May 31. Hardly any veggies on any of the 3 subs, tuna was a blob at one end, bread wasn't cut well. Poor assembly, substandard quantities, not engaged with customer. Needs remedial training.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNGk6gqhiyNUpJmw4JZ_h5eTBDpzaEk90XhlHOz&fid=0x0:0xe750afb01549968c"],"When":"2023-6-1"},{"Name":"I Cho","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVfkuQCgpQxqRFQLoXCNfqdwVb3AKxF4irc7m63V9Y5m_uS-uY=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"I ordered a half size of BMT showing a picture of half size of BMT and he was making a foot long so i told him i ordered half. He started yelling at me and said you didn‚Äôt tell me half but i showed him picture and said half order when i was ordering. He kept yelling at me and saying it‚Äôs your fault , you didn‚Äôt say that. Old guy who looks like a manager was so rude and crashed out on me even if he‚Äôs fault.
Im not coming this location anymore.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Adam Durante","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWoeaVsK-bN-3a6oaiIu_JEPHIuWPh6m_NNo6rT75BjgXtkQ6c=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"This store was participating in a deal:
Buy a foot long and get 6 free cookies. Order must be placed online.
We told the girl working behind the counter we‚Äôd order online so we could take advantage of the deal, she acknowledged.
We proceeded to order online but when the ‚Äúticket‚Äù showed up in store the cookies weren‚Äôt on it.
The girl told us, ‚Äúsorry I can‚Äôt give you the cookies‚Äù We tried to reason with her since she knew our intention.
I suggested she call her Manager for a second opinion. I told her that I intended to Google Review.
She called  the Manager and advised us once again, ‚Äúsorry no cookies‚Äù

I‚Äôm writing this review on principle, it‚Äôs not about the cookies. It‚Äôs about a Manager/Owner of this Subway prioritizing the profits from 6 cookies over a Google Review.

#itsnotaboutthecookies #sillymanager","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"shaun antoniuk","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIFXx9OJT8KdQeK-jEML84xlWXgCq2OAzGIXUuGKVVij6sOsA=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"The owner is Intentionally ripping off his customers. He doesn't give the double cheese as is required for 90% of the subs on the menu, and he doesn't give the amount of meat he is supposed to give. And when you ask for him to make it correctly, he will instantly reduce the amount of vegetables on the sub to almost nothing.  This should be reported to head office as he is stealing from his customers.
I work nearby and watched them intentionally short me and every other customer that came in many times before finally calling him out.","Images":null,"When":""}]

[{"Name":"Akeymjot Singh","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLepiJUo0etQV-hYwl1zBMjdtenUSL_zBA6-POUR_aw0hGcQQ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Hi everyone,

I always have a great experience at the Tim Hortons inside this gas station. The staff are incredibly friendly and always greet me with a happy face, which honestly makes my day every time. The service is quick, and they never miss a beat.

I usually order a steeped tea, and they make it just right‚Äîperfectly brewed and consistent every time. It‚Äôs my go-to place for a quick pick-me-up, and the welcoming atmosphere makes it even better.

Highly recommend stopping by if you're in the area!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Mohammadjafar Zahedi","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocK1evkwPjHKEG-OyOy9w1KKyT_IZb2_YK8tHbeEDQmQOonodg=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":""I love visiting Tim Hortons! [{"Name":"Moe Ayyad","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVtXOmAhvsk-Qgo1eADaY0TZbUONs-HVvrKR-rjjHSs0dWppnE=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Our favorite restaurant in Vancouver. Been there so many times I lost count and yet the quality and service have always been consistently excellent. The portions are big as well

Honestly, I can recommend any item on the menu but I'll stick to 3: The XD burger, The Chicken Nash (make it double and hot), and the addictive truffle fries.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPRo7oy0jAdjia53F9akmP0XeJK7cCCsfb8KTmf&fid=0x0:0x4308681e2f57f8b7"],"When":"2024-11-11"},{"Name":"Atlac Mdzh","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVmp8pn6U1S_KsOxdPvVN179SqKOQPaim2AxrOd-rorYkvJMKVF=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"One sentence! Super super super yummy! If you are looking for a cheat meal , a great burger, chicken sandwich or potato this is the place! I crave their fries and steak sandwich every awhile! This time owner was there he was friendly and welcoming. Make sure you get their fries its amazing. This time 3 of us got the deal they have 3 sandwiches and 1 fries+ 2 drinks for $65 or something was a good deal could be enough for 4 people even, 3 ladies full. Portion of food is good enough even the fries they are generous! Try it snd have fun! I think this place is also Halal prob so another good point . TY for hosting 8 of us in a short notice","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMmJm4pkF6IRA0ZoixRaMTUStdAoKxwBlwjlVO3&fid=0x0:0x4308681e2f57f8b7"],"When":"2024-7-29"},{"Name":"Sazzad Hossain","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocK5JzPg_HbQTCfL-RL2N4qcAmAyjkRuMRE7Ps-o51NovewMwA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Heard a lot about this burger store and tried today. Found a bit overrated. No doubt their burgers are good but I wouldn‚Äôt call it extraordinary. Price is reasonable considering the size but again I think it is unnecessary to make a burger such big. I would say better make the burger a bit smaller and offer the side dishes with the same price. Anyway, worth to try once but not going back again.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOpeJL_j1Z95Eg4Wp4NrCi1TvXGXm-FUsmdLW79&fid=0x0:0x4308681e2f57f8b7"],"When":"2024-9-8"},{"Name":"Alp Aky√ºz","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXTpDw_1NF2XcXz1wlm93KiBPPyp6Hj8SeUv-OW0gp6GjQzsSM=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I recently visited this spot and tried the single smash burger and fries. The fries were a generous portion and tasted good. The burger was also quite good, with a nice balance of flavors and a satisfying texture. The prices were fair, making it great value for the quality of the meal. The food was prepared on time, and the service was friendly and efficient. Plus, it's all halal, which is a huge bonus.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipONeAM2tKzccy5sm4y9AelFnBMmZUGKhKhTBm8&fid=0x0:0x4308681e2f57f8b7"],"When":"2024-8-6"},{"Name":"Chelsea Ribeiro","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWSGW1MjStLEM4Ti82xPt3ZIr1Jy0lyuEz1vEsloL6KwADrC1Jr=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Delicious, flavourful food with great pricing. The atmosphere in the restaurant is excellent and staff are super attentive. 10/10, would recommend.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOGg6k9KnRwLCZBRCMo_rPnKV89q-x4c4f1n0KD&fid=0x0:0x4308681e2f57f8b7"],"When":"2024-12-7"},{"Name":"Shurouq","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXOTYFD62S2SHY9n8pNVDB8rH0a77a2MTGd9SQZLF7RQu3y_spd=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We went to Vonns on December 13, and I can tell you if you don‚Äôt go for the food, which is AMAZING, go for the service! Deepka was amazing and lovely! We had the classic cheesesteak and the Vonns cheesesteak, the truffle fries, and the chicken taco. Absolutely delicious! I loved the drinks too, I recommend the Malaysian strawberry soda","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPnCZlI7q8K-qZRBzg8pkKrdfaO6A3EF1iyBhYW&fid=0x0:0x4308681e2f57f8b7"],"When":"2024-12-13"},{"Name":"Nhi Lai","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUJIBRRqNF3Ys2JLjwN2oCzCf3fQatAE5tjRF38mpxWh1ylSU5M=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Amazinggg!!!
I love the üåÆ , they gave three sauces so you can choose. I tried the burger as well but it was not my favourite. The service was quick and friendly
I love the open space and there is a hand washing area for customers","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMPKcM7OPHv_xkSvR5a6VWZmTfrCzUtCWrJwZno&fid=0x0:0x4308681e2f57f8b7"],"When":"2024-9-18"},{"Name":"Steph D","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX4QdnTA6-gZzOcweEkv5cU5WuO7WUC4_IgjVd6RxBrhV9lQhGY9Q=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"There was a group of about 6 or 7 of us that dined here; the restaurant was pretty empty when we arrived and service took a while. The server eventually came over and we ordered appies first. Later, the server comes by asking if she can take the menus away even though we haven't even ordered our mains yet.

When the restaurant got busier later, the music in the restaurant got turned up and we had to speak louder to hear each other, although not shouting. The server came by and asked us to be quiet because she said the table across from us had complained about us being too loud, even though they didn't and the server used this as an excuse.

I have never been asked to be quiet at a restaurant, especially when the music is so loud that you have to raise your voice to hear each other speak! We were all quite taken aback by being asked to be quiet so we quickly paid and left, because they clearly didn't want us to be there.

We definitely won't be coming back to this restaurant and have told our friends of what happened and to also not go here because of this incident.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipP-v-T1thA6_Xm4MRAeuwVGuFeWjpcPthjjAkeV&fid=0x0:0x4308681e2f57f8b7"],"When":"2024-9-26"}]

user_reviews:
[{"Name":"Ahmad Awais","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVKCENA3EQDxfNwGRkIzdwRQJIr8-nzzvbQk_P3TVWN1UAiJIKg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Looks like I found the best halal platter in town! Fresh Donair‚Äôs new branch on Robson Street is a gem that truly delivers on taste and quality. The moment I stepped inside, I was greeted by a bright, welcoming atmosphere. The staff was quick to offer help with the menu, which showcases a variety of mouthwatering options. Still, it was their chicken and beef platter that stole the show for me.

Each component of the platter felt meticulously prepared. The chicken was tender, carrying a balanced seasoning that highlighted its natural flavors. The beef was equally stellar‚Äîjuicy, lightly spiced, and cooked to perfection. Even the sides were on point: the rice was fluffy, the salads were fresh and crisp, and the sauces offered just the right tangy or spicy twist to elevate every bite.

It‚Äôs not often you find a spot that nails both quality and quantity, but Fresh Donair does exactly that. The portions are generous, enough to satisfy a hearty appetite or split between two people. On top of that, everything comes at a fair price that doesn‚Äôt feel inflated for a Robson Street location. You can sense that value and customer satisfaction are high priorities here.

What really stood out to me, aside from the delicious food, was the cleanliness and attention to detail. The dining area felt spotless, and the staff clearly took pride in keeping everything tidy. It‚Äôs comforting to see a place that cares about more than just great taste‚ÄîFresh Donair also ensures a safe and inviting environment for its guests.

For anyone looking for a top-notch halal option in Vancouver, Fresh Donair on Robson Street is a must-try. The environment is welcoming, the food consistently hits the mark, and the service is genuine. I left feeling completely satisfied and excited to return, eager to explore more of their menu. If you haven‚Äôt checked out this new branch yet, make it a priority. I‚Äôm confident you‚Äôll walk out thinking you‚Äôve found a new favorite, too.

In a city as diverse as Vancouver, it‚Äôs refreshing to find a spot that delivers on all fronts. Highly recommended!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNPQlsnvqCaWCsXX88puK7xCTVuuUSk90NR2FHI&fid=0x0:0x2d91dbc13c2f81ba"],"When":"2024-12-25"},{"Name":"Hugh Holtz","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLnMF127VyUqWPMyGLShLF1ZAm5tCY9_nmrmqVXl6PFsNcINA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"It just opened today, and we thought we‚Äôd give it a try. I was received so pleasantly and professionally that me and my friend decided to have a meal. We had fried chicken, I had a sandwich and he just the chicken. Price was extremely reasonable and quality was top notch. It took about 20 minutes for our order to be ready however that was due to everything getting cooked from fresh. Chicken was absolutely perfect and delicious including the sauce and fresh and toasted bun; topped with a delicious homemade coleslaw. Very satisfying portions and taste. Will definitely go back and strongly recommend it. Well done üëèüëèüëçüëçüôè","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Tina","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUAKiC5J1ql1LsLTTfBwgvAj6sVGUusHXghumDKVG9ZTQ8QjcD_1w=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Their crispy chicken burger is SO GOOD. I think they use a brioche bun? The chicken is tender and juicy, and they‚Äôre very generous with the portion. Can‚Äôt wait to try other things on their menu","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNDbbHjcH4uI9a9Ov8QzqkUm_yjtqEqYroUkO-E&fid=0x0:0xb1db48abf9732a09"],"When":"2024-2-4"},{"Name":"Saadiq Daya","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjV3DKqBF6FlfD1uoJFijv1AasTE7x1Yai7PIt8hzShJr7eE_dUr=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Awesome spot for fried chicken - some of the best chicken I‚Äôve ever had. Wasn‚Äôt oily, well seasoned, fries were so good as well as the sauces. The owners were very friendly and let us stay after closing. It‚Äôs good to see another halal fried chicken place making unique recipes and good service","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMbPi9dKo6xVjdJRueEQT7OSpkjCWmClyncCi3H&fid=0x0:0xb1db48abf9732a09"],"When":"2023-6-6"},{"Name":"Ayon Rayhan","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUk1t0mMEnXcBwA4oO2vbDly8NCDTs72Gk7ZzS-nvuFcnUdEkL8=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"The hype did live up. Went to vancity today, the owner was very friendly and nice. We got the whole chicken flavored to go but forgot to take photos as we were very hungry and finished the whole chicken in minutes. The chicken wasn't oily at all and the flavors were on point. We took the spicy and lemon pepper but surely will try the other flavors too down the line.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNKnAjoq9YiGJCEU2M6yQhMP7Q4s8S8VdxDdAk&fid=0x0:0xb1db48abf9732a09"],"When":"2023-5-10"},{"Name":"Saskia Asyari","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXOw-vGRppaZWH-87l0DTjRp6cH2-cGmCr2why8D5leomPAj1GywA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Heard a lot of people said that this tastes like Korean fried chicken and I‚Äôve been wanting to try their fried chicken ever since. Finally gave them a try and I ordered half flavoured chicken (honey garlic and the owner gave us free lemon pepper herbs topping, thank you!) and poutine. I must say that the chicken was the bomb! It really tastes like Korean fried chicken (at least from what I know from Korean restaurants back home). It‚Äôs so crispy outside yet so tender inside. Interestingly, it‚Äôs not greasy nor overly oily. Definitely coming back maybe to get the whole chicken instead and the chicken burger.

Oh and they‚Äôre halal and only use organic non-medicated chickens too.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMqb-zTgUvZdt10sHYFx5DTG-m05-1GEMoccHWC&fid=0x0:0xb1db48abf9732a09"],"When":"2023-2-10"},{"Name":"Joe Tian","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUG9eOyJXWNkkgsKP9c-KtmxyDuwIAnqVHHWZ8xRw17CUN7ShtxBA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"After what seems like a year of renos, this chicken place is finally open. Previously a donair shop, a family seems to have taken over selling fried chicken. They have seats but currently only accept takeout. You can order at the door through a speaker, or online. The father/husband seem to be in charge of the entire shop while the wife is feeding a little child and keeping them entertained. You can watch TV while you wait for your order.

We got a full flavored chicken(cheese) and half crispy. We got a side of fries with gravy. A side and a drink comes with your order too so we for mac & cheese. My GF pointed out that they also fry mars bars, which is kind of hidden away on their menu. Their entire menu is just boarded to the wall outside.

The chicken is so good! Its like korean fried chicken, and a good value too. The chicken is bone in and just hacked up in big chunks so expect to nibble some bone(i prefer this because i think its fun to do). The cheese powder is kind of sweet, and theres dried herbs mixed in. Crispy chicken is good too but id probably just get flavored next time.

Fries seems to be those battered fries you get from costco. If you have had those then you know what to expect. Gravy is a little lumpy. Mac & cheese is just KD, it's a little under-seasoned.

The chicken i think is the highlight and everything is made to order. I would've liked some home-made mac & cheese imo and options to pay for extra sides. For the value i think it's incredible! So nice to have it so close-by us and we will definitely take advantage whenever we can.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOjWM-HcQKQhlTThXGDB2-Jvuu9_2W9wNo2iMYn&fid=0x0:0xb1db48abf9732a09"],"When":"2021-9-25"},{"Name":"Manal Khan","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWJimdRZbpdkrN736htkLxSq3QxSKCjdl7jrbpQtWHwNC9-zx-SHw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Literally the best fried chicken I've ever had in north America!! In Vancouver, such good quality chicken and a family marinating and frying it so carefully, putting in labour and LOVE. Halal chicken also for Muslims who might prefer. Must visit.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipN0KJ5Iy_66b8xGzlIj3TBaNJZTM-FNXndj4SxW&fid=0x0:0xb1db48abf9732a09"],"When":"2022-8-26"}]

[{"Name":"H H (Anonymous)","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX0CCOw3xZUC4Jf140dg5ctXIilfoV-e5nt-AjupQqNUDd2WrdF=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"UPDATE: I noticed that 2 new comments with five stars were written right after I put a review out. One says that it‚Äôs written from a UBC student but we were the only ones in the restaurant. Really??
‚Äî-
I came here with my friend for the first time because of the high reviews, but I was very underwhelmed by the quality of food.

We ordered 1 Carbonara pasta with 4 beef balls and a Creamy Pesto Sauce as well. The lady taking our order was extremely rude, holding her arms together most of the time (not even a proper eye contact too).

The portion of the pasta we got was smaller than expected, and the pasta sauce was very bland. I was also expecting actual beef meat balls for the protein, but it felt like eating processed, microwaved meatballs.

I can‚Äôt believe all of this including the mango lassi costs $56. We even tipped which made it $64 but we both felt that the food was not worth the price.

The only good thing was the mango lassi. It tasted good, but not worth the price considering it‚Äôs around $6 for a regular cup.

Overall, I‚Äôm extremely disappointed about my experience here. I noticed your team sends auto-generated responses for customer feedbacks, but honestly it really doesn‚Äôt reflect well on your new customers.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipObiPeftIl5M13d-Zi5CL5dxWo1asSNBVO640QA&fid=0x0:0x903faab4aef83611"],"When":"2024-10-21"},{"Name":"Priya Seenivasan","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJMhKuaV0UByu_19lq9S8Z0RymGWLGeMkZW32FqcwJdXwdJC4O6=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"The food was very tasty and the portion sizes were very generous for the price. The server gave us FREE Mango lasi and it was the GREATEST Mango lasi I've ever had. The food was hot and fresh and would 10/10 recommend if you are hungry. There are a lot of options for both vegetarian and non vegetarian and we had both of them and it was super good. They also play very good music for you to enjoy while you are eating. All and all the entire time was very nice and the owner and workers were very hospitable.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMZaBRVpHaOh3_rK63YSkIbFpjWPmoknQX1xSOn&fid=0x0:0x903faab4aef83611"],"When":"2024-7-22"},{"Name":"Crew Member","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIW14Rkre9qUFJcBu_goFVES8rqZEo_nhoqcvS5y7IN5FVczw=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"This is my second time here and as good as it was the first, it is just as good now. The owner greeted me the first time and remembered me after over a week. I had the butter chicken poutine the first time on takeout and this visit I took my partner to share with her my love of this place. We had the butter chicken poutine and the peri-peri rice bowl. Will come again to try the various other poutines on the menu. I also wouldn‚Äôt hesitate ordering Indian food from their menu as well if the butter chicken is any indication of the taste and kwality. And yes that‚Äôs Kwality spelled with a K because it was that special!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPFnFhaMwSrlDtTe_QXzwAmwsSniPSZ1JtJ3WuF&fid=0x0:0x903faab4aef83611"],"When":"2024-9-27"},{"Name":"Karen Castelino","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjV7hhw7USB5QEJWbaxhDcx84xG1_szAmojdVvw-2W8v9vRmg6g=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"What a lovely spot for a quick lunch. The owner Sanjeet is very welcoming and happy to explain about the mixed menu items with passion.

He LOVES street food and he has a mix 9f Indian, German, Italian and Mexican street food which is pretty cool in one place.

Today I tried the Ghar ka Chai which was just like how we make it at home and they asked if I wanted sugar in or outüòÅ Definitely like af home. They serve it with two biscuits to dip in the Chai, just like at home.

He charmed me into trying his butter chicken samosas and I said, Why not?! They came out piping hot, with a green coriander chutney and an imli chutney - perfect zingy accompiments to the tasty samosas and quite large sized they were too.

He also gave me little tastes of his new spring rolls that had a chicken filling and a vegetarian filling. A nice little amuse bouche.

Today anyone who's come in so far has also got a little shot glass of mango Lassi- and it really hits the spot on a hot day.

A nice addition to West 10th, I'll be back again and might bring a friend or two with me!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPFHT9vS7Xj7xZWcpTHB855Vl5ncFMvQXMmLcUq&fid=0x0:0x903faab4aef83611"],"When":"2024-7-19"},{"Name":"Yvonne Chuang","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWqpGy6jnb7nEEZ8_2ji_kDkPiEtwUfRn1WZ4LYfiAMdNRgZihb=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I had a wonderful experience at this restaurant! The portion sizes were generous and offered great value for the price. The food was absolutely delicious, packed with authentic flavors. The owner was incredibly friendly and attentive, which added a warm, welcoming touch to our visit. To top it all off, my kids were delighted when the owner surprised them with free ice cream after the meal. We left with full stomachs and smiles all around ‚Äì highly recommended!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Valerie","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWsTdxaXYpowkoRFDEpRVok8X0NZLQqRjReyfUxLgMaFFBwHbFY=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"The food was delicious! I ordered the mango lassi and the 65 chicken rice bowl. Everything was freshly made, and the workers are really nice!!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMP_KmSZB_VaqJZXpIu6pOs6SS1hZxRljgWuX2r&fid=0x0:0x903faab4aef83611"],"When":"2024-9-29"},{"Name":"Tommy Byun","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXQhlW94B8T2fhww-HWh0iFh-RYIvFitfF4mjJX2E5t_heAv3Lb=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Casual Indian-Italian fusion restaurant on the way to UBC. It is relatively new, and it felt like it is targeting more of take outs and dine ins, as I was the only person dining in during a weekday lunch time. It may be different for a weekend dinner.

I ordered popcorn chicken poutine, peri-peri burger, and a coke. You prepay, and they bring out the food. I was talking to the owner a bit, and he was nice enough to let me try their mango lassi, which was pretty good.

Popcorn chicken poutine was really good considering the price (menu says $9.99, but the staff told me that it was increased to $10.99 when I ordered, which was kind of weird, as food delivery app has it even lower, at $8.99). It had good portion of the cheese curds & popcorn chicken. I would order the gravy on the side next time because the dish was salty overall. I would order this again for sure on Skip the Dish if its $8.99!

The Peri-peri burger was not good. It was dry, the bun was cheap, and vegetable was minimal. I would never order this again, unless the burger improves, as I commented this to the owner when he asked how the food was.

Next time I come, I would try other interesting menus like fusion pasta & wraps as well. I will provide further review with another visit.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNeG9fj15NenmiUzLSavO5taxKqF3HlEJWBf5wS&fid=0x0:0x903faab4aef83611"],"When":"2024-5-13"},{"Name":"Monesha Basker","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIJdHrdFjVHsxCfq5iniLbrtk_RySGMC8r7uyasrbD_xG-PMw=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"The food was delicious! It was very appetising. The service was also very nice, very welcoming. Would recommend !!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNQXn-Kt9TKt75SNVgXLgZn6SXC0MiR73v_Cy3l&fid=0x0:0x903faab4aef83611"],"When":"2024-9-29"}]

user_reviews: [{"Name":"M B","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXIxiCIy7Ch29LlP7VXHtco7aO8YNkp89Hd11g67GLT8n9AIrZy=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"They used to serve lettuce and tomato, in fact I think the menu still lists it with the burgers. Last time (August) I ordered the Pork (pictured), this time the Farm (October) and both came with meat and rice, and a tiny bit of slaw. No salad. I didn't realize how much the lettuce and tomato balanced the meat and rice combo. Now it is too dry yet also sort of greasy (not sauce) to eat. No freshness. Not for me anymore. I always get take out, as inside feels grubby, the floor is sticky when you walk. That kind of things always makes me wonder what the cleanliness behind the scenes where your food is made is like... Without the salad it is a spoon of meat and two spoons of rice with a sprinkle of slaw so very overpriced at $13. It is the size of the palm of your hand for reference. I also eat with my eyes and was disappointed with how the burger looked, and sadly tasted. I used to crave this place.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile\u0026image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMYJ5S0DbHsJ0w9h1XuMRlCQCM8C4m_WwGggX4b\u0026fid=0x0:0x25762a4aae318566"],"When":"2024-10-10"},{"Name":"Dennis Li","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXJgBHuKaxB6_AGRs3DyAn5DYWAJVYL8OdZQBLbOlZjEJJMR8F5KA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"This restaurant is participating in TooGoodToGo app, this photo shows the surprise bag order, half the price of mini beef bowl, not bad but a little small","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile\u0026image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipM0PIYdSvzNdUvylTulTbOJ5JGQdxLKWUlz6DNc\u0026fid=0x0:0x25762a4aae318566"],"When":"2024-11-10"},{"Name":"leesa tran","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUWsWaHyhzcw7kKPh9V3HkvTK5TTa81TdmCDp9IylYllx4puXIy=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Ordered the beef burger combo and it was really good. Very warm atmosphere, from the design of the inside to the friendly service. Because the place is relatively small, it‚Äôs probably not a good idea to bring a large group, but it‚Äôs a nice place for a smaller hang or even to chill by yourself. I have been curious for a while and just tried it with some friends. I probably will be back.
They have a great drink menu with lots of specialty cocktails and nonalcoholic drinks. I got a nonalcoholic pineapple guava soda. I don‚Äôt like drinks that are too sweet and this was good for me, but some people might find it weak compared to commercial fruit sodas.
I got a soup and sandwich combo as my entree with the Eggplant Caprese sandwich and the Crab Bisque. I really liked this take on a caprese sandwich, and the baguette was very fresh and soft. The bisque was very good too. Rather than being a super creamy bisque, this was more tomato-based and a little tangy. Good flavour with a fair amount of crab meat. I also liked the little side of coleslaw that was included in the combo.
Wasn‚Äôt really planning on getting dessert but then I saw they had a Chocolate Banana Bread Pudding, and I will rarely pass up on bread pudding. It was delicious but, as you might expect from bread pudding made of banana bread, with ice cream, with caramel sauce, VERY rich and heavy, and I had to get some help to finish it. I think this would be ideal for splitting between two people.
For this meal, with tip, I paid $48, which surprised me. I thought it was a good meal, but not $50 good - I‚Äôd associate that kind of price with a more upscale experience than this. I can understand the soup and sandwich pricing, the dessert was a little expensive, but what really strikes me as obviously overpriced would be the $8 soda. I understand it‚Äôs made in house, but it was just a fruity soda - no fruit bits or anything fancy, and no alcohol. It was a nice refreshing drink, but for $8 I wouldn‚Äôt say it was worth it.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMA-33yhxlhuJWzrEmE3NBivENZ-qwhvFcoFjxN&fid=0x0:0x57c0ba4874667b57"],"When":"2023-5-20"},{"Name":"Keith Ver","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXVdqxLCf1LEt0AU82myo-eUqDcb2LcbdnfhupJTEW0sPAQ-qQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Good food and good service! Loved the ambiance of the whole place. It gives me this vibe that you know you'll be ordering comfort food. Not only will it fill your tummy, but also your soul.

I ordered beef bourguignon and it reminded me of Filipino dish called Caldereta üß° - minus the mashed potatoes that is.

The whole place is accessible as they're located along Main street. Will definitely be back!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOT835yv9VmYFeqt5AwiAEPtu_4O-xMZON9EBlg&fid=0x0:0x57c0ba4874667b57"],"When":"2023-6-5"}]

Apparently the landlord didn't want to extend the lease. I hope they find a new space in Vancouver. That said, the service was fantastic and deserving of a good tip. I loved the eggs Benedict with hashbrowns and pork belly, I forget what they called it but the food was memorable. And it's in a perfect location near the marina at Jericho so a great place for a walk to burn off the calories","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipO44BS-QhzVwExBGdBt60sVJ7rQI5WrhEEj06X1&fid=0x0:0x8724e7521984580"],"When":"2024-12-15"},{"Name":"Laurel Windover","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWnEhLdsjZ16qCFrqZXUCMvuEzXtbI46OBVg6YSX7imdPsfZHYlwQ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"I love the casual patio and the menu is priced right. I asked for the salmon burger as a salad instead of a burger and it was delicious!
The service was a bit slow the day I was there though. It didn‚Äôt appear to be too busy but we waited 40 minutes for our food and nobody came to do a quality check after we were served. In fact we didn‚Äôt see the server again until quite awhile after we were finished eating. That said, it‚Äôs a cute, casual spot in a great location and I would definitely go back!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOg4RgddnYKK-Gjr0FDLECUohwzN85d-LhzmZqd&fid=0x0:0x8724e7521984580"],"When":"2024-7-8"},{"Name":"Tina Fischer","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjU_PBoE3UhL3iJ077dZx_qOA7mXIKHJuwtODDKop9ishOSiUuMS=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Classic breakfast was awesome!
